title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Fry with a little oil until tender and brown.

title: quick coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed using 2 layer pans.
Split each layer in half.
Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut.
Chill.
Reserve 1 cup sour cream mixture for frosting.
Spread remainder between layers of cake.
Combine reserved sour cream mixture with Cool Whip.
Blend until smooth.
Spread on top and sides of cake. Store in airtight container in refrigerator for 3 days before serving.
This cake is well worth waiting for!

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into square casserole dish; cover with aluminum foil and place in freezer until firm.
Allow to sit 5 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all together. Spread in 9 x 13 pan. Crush 4 cups corn flakes. Sprinkle on top of mixture. Melt 1 stick margarine. Drizzle on top of corn flakes. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken pepperoni
directions: Bake chicken breast in casserole dish for 15 minutes at 350°. Add pepperoni slices, Prego, cheese (in that order).
Top with mushrooms and bell pepper, if desired. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool about 15 minutes.
Serve over cooked spaghetti noodles.

title: easy batter rolls
directions: Add sugar, salt and margarine to scalded milk.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
When milk is cooled to warm, add yeast mixture. Add egg and beat.
Add 2 cups flour and beat smooth.
Add rest of flour to make a soft dough.
Let raise until doubled, about 30 minutes.
Flour hands and pinch off pieces the size of large walnut and roll into balls, keeping hands floured.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan, 4 across and 6 down, leaving space between.
Let rise until doubled, about 30 minutes.
Bake in preheated 400° oven about 15 minutes.
Makes 24.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Wash berries.
Cut orange into quarters; remove seeds.
Do not peel orange.
Grind berries and orange.
Add sugar.
Refrigerate.

title: chinese red beets
directions: Combine all ingredients except red beets.
Cook until thickened.
Then add red beets to thickened mixture.

title: savory lasagna
directions: Brown beef and sausage.
Add onion flakes, tomato paste and 2 tomato cans of water.
Mix well.
Add seasonings and spices. Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cook noodles as on package.
Layer noodles, sauce and Mozzarella cheese in two 9 x 14-inch pans. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Can be frozen for later use.

title: baked brisket au jus
directions: Place brisket fat side down in roasting pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Top with onion and celery slices.
Stir together tomato sauce, tomato paste and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over beef.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cover and bake 2 more hours, basting with juices occasionally.
Add coffee and bake, covered, 2 more hours.
Check every 30 minutes for dryness.
Add 1/4 cup water if needed.
Remove brisket from pan and let stand 20 minutes.
Slice brisket across the grain with a sharp knife. Strain pan drippings and serve with brisket.

title: congo squares
directions: Mix all ingredients in the order given and bake in an 11 1/2 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish at 350° for 30 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: diabetic fresh apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 9-inch uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 30 min.

title: judy's chocolate cake
directions: Mix together; put in pan.
Sprinkle brown and white sugar and chocolate chips over batter of unbaked cake.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Combine rhubarb, marshmallows and sugar.
Put in buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions. Pour over rhubarb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. Yields 8 servings.

title: spinach balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook the spinach as directed on the box and drain well. Mix rest of the ingredients and add the spinach. Chill. Shape into balls and place on a lightly greased baking sheet. Bake 20 minutes. Serve warm. Makes about 60.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hot dish
directions: Mix the above ingredients and pour into greased 9 x 13 pan. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake, uncovered, for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: raspberry jello salad
directions: In the bottom only of a 9 x 12-inch baking dish, make a graham cracker crust with crumbs, butter and a little sugar.
Press in; bake 10 minutes at 325°.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: mini tostadas(microwave)
directions: Spread 1 heaping teaspoonful beans on each tortilla chip.
Top each with 1/2 teaspoon taco sauce and 1 teaspoon cheese.
Arrange 6 to 8 at a time on paper towel-lined plate.
Microwave on Medium for 1 minute.
Turn plate 1/4 turn.
Microwave for 1 minute longer or until cheese melts, turning every 30 seconds.
Top each with tomato slice.
Yield:
2 dozen.

title: dump cake
directions: Dump fruit into well greased/buttered 9 x 13 dish.
Dump dry cake mix on top.
Spread evenly.
Cut stick of oleo into parts and place all over top of cake mix.
Bake for 40 to 50 minutes, at 350 degrees.
Serve warm with ice cream or as a cobbler.

title: hot pizza dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and top with cheese.
Cook in microwave up to 5 minutes.

title: mexi-dip
directions: Spread beans in bottom of pie pan.
Cover with mashed avocados. Sprinkle with garlic powder.
Add sour cream over top, then salsa, spreading over sour cream.
Top with grated cheese and black olives.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: easy vegetable soup
directions: Brown meat and onion in large saucepan.
Cook until onion is tender.
Drain off accumulated fat.
Season to taste.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Simmer until noodles are tender (covered).
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Bake at 350°.
Place
on
greased cookie sheet in small balls, then mash down with a fork.

title: pickled jalapeno peppers
directions: Wear rubber gloves and avoid rubbing eyes.

title: oven fried onion rings
directions: Mix buttermilk and separated onion rings.
Set aside for 20 minutes.
Heat oven to 375°.
Spray 2 cooking sheets.
Place flour, paprika, and salt in bowl.	Place slightly beaten egg whites in second bowl.
Place crumbs in third bowl.
Dip rings in flour, then egg whites, then crumbs.
Place on baking sheet sprayed with vegetable oil spray.
Bake in single layer 15 minutes.
Do in batches.

title: bran muffins
directions: Pour water over cereal.
Set aside.
Cream sugar and oleo.
Add eggs and buttermilk.
Stir in gently flour, soda, salt and Bran Buds.
Add to water and cereal mixture.
Place in covered jar or container and store in refrigerator.
Keeps 6 weeks.
Do not stir before putting in muffin pans.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: sand tarts
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream butter; add sugar. Stir well. Add flour, nuts and vanilla. Shape into balls and crescents and bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 20 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: polish sausage with apple, kraut and noodles
directions: In crock-pot, stir together all ingredients.
Cook on low temperature setting for a minimum of 4 hours and up to 8 hours. Cook 2 cups noodles according to package directions.
Add to crock-pot 1/2 hour before serving.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Grease and flour cake pan.

title: too-easy peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place fruit in a buttered 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Cut crust from bread and cut each slice into 5 fingers.
Place over fruit.
In a bowl, mix sugar, flour, egg and oleo.
Pour over fruit and bread.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes until golden brown.
Can use other fruits like blackberries, etc.

title: chocolate chiffon cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with milk to Crisco and sugar.
Add coffee and vanilla.
Last, fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Bake in wax paper-lined 8-inch round pans at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Cool thoroughly before icing.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except chips and cheese.
Mix well.
Turn into a 1-quart baking dish.
Top with chips.
Bake 30 minutes or until hot.
Top with cheese.
Bake 3 minutes longer.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix

first 5 ingredients together. Make three holes in dry ingredients. In first hole put the vanilla, in second hole put the vinegar, in third hole put Crisco oil. Pour cold water over all and beat well. Pour into 13 x 9 inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: decadent fudge cake
directions: Cream the butter in a large mixing bowl.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Dissolve the soda in the buttermilk, stirring well. Add to creamed mixture alternately with flour, beginning and ending with flour.
Add 1 cup chocolate chips, melted chocolate, chocolate syrup and vanilla, stirring, just until blended.
Spoon batter into a heavily greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 25 to 35 minutes or until cake springs back at touch. Invert cake immediately onto a serving plate and let cool completely.

title: chimi churi
directions: Combine ingredients and put in wine bottles. Top off with red wine vinegar.
Cork, making vertical grooves in corks to make shakers out of bottles.
Will keep for years if you keep adding oil and vinegar.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and salt in hot water.
Add sauce and stir until smooth.
(Can dissolve sauce in hot water and heat again until boiling.)
Chill, then add nuts and celery.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: Melt 4 Milky Way bars.
Add 1/2 can Hershey's syrup and 1 can Eagle Brand milk and mix well.
Pour into ice cream freezer and fill with milk.
Grate 2 Milky Way bars and mix into frozen ice cream.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix butter, milk, sugar and oil.
Put yeast into this mixture.
Add enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Pour dough onto floured board.
Roll out dough to 1/2-inch thickness and cut out rolls with round cutter.
Place rolls in buttered dish and let rise 1 hour, but not more than 3 hours.
Bake at 425° until golden brown.
Makes 2 dozen rolls.

title: cookie crackers
directions: Grease a cookie sheet with butter.
Line cookie sheet with crackers.
In a saucepan, melt 2 sticks butter and brown sugar. Pour over crackers.
Bake at 450° for 3 minutes.
Cool.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over cooled crackers.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Never refrigerate!

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimentos and 1/2 can onions.
Pour into shallow 1-quart casserole dish.
Bake covered at 350° for 30 minutes or until vegetables are done.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and onions on top.
Bake uncovered 5 minutes or until golden brown.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Boil potatoes until tender, then peel.
Mash with potato masher.
Add sugar, flour and margarine.
Blend until creamy.
Add other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 9-inch deep dish pie shell.
Bake at 400° until crust is browned and pie filling is set.

title: unbelievable pie
directions: Put eggs in blender.
Blend slightly.
Add other ingredients; blend just enough to mix.
Pour into greased pie plate and bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: outdoor grilled potatoes
directions: Tear aluminum foil into 4 pieces, about 10 x 10-inch squares. Add some potatoes, onion, salt and pepper to taste and a pat of butter.
Fold foil over potatoes and seal well.
Put foil-wrapped potatoes on hot outdoor grill, keeping them away from the fire itself, as much as possible.
Take about 30 minutes to cook on a hot grill, so put these on before you throw on the hamburgers, hot dogs or steaks.

title: apple butter
directions: Remove stems and ends of fully ripe apples; cut in small pieces.
If sweet apples, add 2 tablespoons lemon juice.
Add 1 1/2 cups water.
Bring to a boil and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Crush with masher and simmer, covered, 5 minutes longer. Place in a large sieve.
Use fruit pulp for butter.
Measure 5 cups into a very large saucepan; add sugar and mix well.
Place over high heat; bring to a rolling boil.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Immediately stir in Certo; skim off foam with a metal spoon.
Stir and skim for 5 minutes to cool slightly to prevent floating fruit.
Ladle into sterilized glass jars.
Cover at once with 1/8-inch hot paraffin.

title: flank steak with fresh fruit salsa
directions: In a 12 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish, combine orange juice, chili sauce, soy sauce, 2 tablespoons salad oil, garlic, orange peel, sugar, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper sauce.
Mix well.
Add steak; turn to coat.
Cover and marinate, turning occasionally, 3 hours or overnight.
Make fresh fruit salsa.
Preheat broiler.
Place steak on rack in broiler pan.
Broil 6 inches from heat for 6 minutes on each side for medium-rare.
Thinly slice steak and serve with fresh fruit salsa.
Makes 6 servings.

title: stir and dump chicken
directions: Place all chicken parts in baking pan or dish.
Mix remaining ingredients together; pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blackberry or jam cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add beaten eggs and jam, beating until smooth.
Add soda to buttermilk and beat into first mixture alternately with flour which has been sifted with spices.
Add raisins and nuts, pour into three 8-inch well-greased cake pans and bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until cake tests done.
Frost with Caramel Frosting.

title: patio potatoes
directions: Heat margarine and soup.
Blend in sour cream, onions and cheese mixture with potatoes.
Put in 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Mix flakes with margarine and sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: reynolds wrap meal
directions: You will also need 8 (12-inch) pieces of heavy-duty Reynolds Wrap.
Use 2 pieces for each meal.
Divide meat, potatoes, carrots, soup mix, margarine and water into 4 equal parts.
Put potatoes, carrots and meat on Reynolds Wrap.
Wrap sides and bottom tightly to prevent leakage.
Add equal parts soup mix, margarine, water and pepper to each wrap.
Seal tightly.
Place them on barbecue pit close to hot coals.
Turn every few minutes until done, about 25 to 30 minutes.

title: caramel pie
directions: Have cooked prepared pie crust ready.
Mix and cook, in double boiler, next 4 ingredients, until thick.
Add last 2 ingredients. Pour into cooked pie crust.
Top with meringue.
Brown until golden.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: May use beef that is prepared for fondue.

title: penuche-candy
directions: Brown 1 pint sugar slowly in heavy skillet until syrupy. As it's melting, have remaining sugar and milk cooking slowly. Pour syrup into milk and sugar mixture very slowly, stirring constantly. Cook and stir until firm ball. Once firm ball, add soda and butter. Set off fire about 20 minutes, then beat in pecans and vanilla. Pour into greased 9 x 15 pan. Cool and cut into bite size pieces.

title: cold lemon souffle
directions: Pour water over gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add drink and lemon rind and juice.
Chill until slightly thick; beat until foamy.
Fold in whipped cream and chill until firm.
Top with fresh strawberries or raspberries if desired.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: buttermilk pecan pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add egg yolks, buttermilk, butter and pecans; beat well.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar at room temperature until stiff peaks form.
Fold into buttermilk mixture.
Pour mixture into unbaked pie shell; bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Blend oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each one.
Sift dry ingredients together and add carrots, nuts and pineapple.
Bake in 3 layers for 30 to 35
minutes at 350°.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Fry the hamburger and onion together. Drain.
Add beans.
In another pan, heat together the Ro-Tel tomatoes and soup.
Place tostada shells in greased 9 x 13-inch dish. Spread meat and bean mixture over shells.
Add half soup mixture.
Slice Velveeta cheese over soup mixture. Repeat layers.
Bake at 300° for 30 to 45 minutes until done. Serve with green salad.

title: pineapple fluff pie
directions: In saucepan, combine pudding mix and gelatin.
Stir in milk. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly (mixture may appear curdled during cooking).
Remove from heat.
Stir in pineapple juice concentrate.

Chill mixture until partially set (the consistency of unbeaten egg whites), stirring often. Fold the whipped topping into the gelatin mixture. Fold in the well drained pineapple. Chill until mixture mounds when spooned. Divide mixture between graham cracker crusts.
Chill several hours or overnight. Makes 2 pies.

title: mounds candy
directions: Mix butter and condensed milk together.
Add powdered sugar. Mix well.
Then add coconut and mix well.
Chill.
Make into balls and put on a cookie sheet.
Chill again.

title: creamy cucumber mousse
directions: Mix cucumber, 1 tablespoon salt and 3 tablespoons vinegar, let stand one hour.
Drain thoroughly.
Sprinkle gelatin over water and let stand 5 minutes.
Heat over low heat, stirring constantly, until gelatin dissolves.
Whisk gelatin into sour cream.
Beat cream cheese with cottage cheese, using electric mixer.
Gradually beat in sour cream mix.
Stir in cucumber, parsley, chives, onion, sugar and remaining vinegar.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour into lightly oiled 5-cup mold and chill until set, about 4 hours. Unmold and serve with crackers.

title: swiss chicken casserole
directions: Arrange chicken in a greased 12x8 baking dish.
Top with cheese, combine soup and milk.
Stir well.
Spoon over chicken. Mix the butter with stuffing mix and sprinkle over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 50 minutes.
Serves:

title: baked chicken italian
directions: Place chicken in baking dish. Combine other ingredients except noodles and Cheez Whiz and blend well.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake in moderate oven at 350° about 2 hours or until chicken is tender.
Cook the noodles until tender; drain. Add the Cheez Whiz and juice from the baked chicken.
Serve with noodles.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Mix thoroughly and chill. Top with whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Prepare vegetables for eating.
Cut cauliflower and broccoli into small flowerets.
Cut tomatoes in wedges.
Slice all other vegetables very thin.
Place vegetables in bowl or pan; cover with Italian dressing.
Refrigerate at least 12 hours before serving. Shake bowl occasionally.

title: country fried chicken
directions: Mix egg and milk.
Combine flour mixture in bag.
First dip chicken
in
egg
mixture,	then dip it in flour mixture. Repeat this 2 more times.	Fry as usual.

title: uncooked peanut butter chocolate candy
directions: Melt margarine.
Add vanilla.
Mix with peanut butter, coconut, cracker crumbs, pecans and sugar.
Roll into balls.
Mix and melt in double boiler the chocolate chips and wax.
Dip balls in mixture using a toothpick to hold them.
Put on wax paper to dry.

title: oven fried apple pies
directions: Use
apples
that
have been cooked down real low.
Mix apples,
salt,
cinnamon
and sugar.
Roll biscuits real thin; put about 1 1/2 tablespoons of apples on 1/2 of each biscuit. Fold over and crimp edges with a fork.
Put oil in sheet cake pan and place pies in pan 5 at a time.
Bake 6 to 7 minutes on each side or until nice and brown at 350°.

title: ring-tum-ditty for 12
directions: Fry bacon; add thinly sliced peppers and onions.
When these are brown, add tomatoes and corn.
Season to taste.
Heat thoroughly and add cheese.
Allow cheese to melt and serve on toast or with crackers.

title: great green beans
directions: Drain beans and add fresh water.
Simmer beans for 15 minutes in a saucepan.
Cut bacon in 1/2-inch strips; fry until crisp. Add bacon to beans.
Add pimento to bacon drippings.
Add vinegar, sugar, Worcestershire sauce and mustard.
Boil, stirring constantly, until well blended.
Pour over beans and bacon; mix well.

title: chocolate chip cheese cake
directions: Slice 1 roll cookie dough 1/3 inch and make crust on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: bread custard
directions: Put brown sugar in top of double boiler.
Place well buttered bread slices on top of sugar.
In a separate bowl, beat eggs.
Add milk, salt and vanilla.
Pour this custard over the bread, but do not stir.
Steam for 1 1/2 hours and serve hot or cold.

title: green beans with almonds
directions: Bring green bean to a boil in a large covered pot.
Reduce heat and simmer until crisp and tender, 3 to 4 minutes.
Drain. Toss with butter flavored buds, garlic powder and thyme.
Garnish with toasted almonds.
Serve hot.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream margarine, vanilla and sugar in large bowl until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs.
Combine bananas and milk in bowl.
Mix flour, soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with banana mixture, beating well after each addition. Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake in 350-degree oven for 1 hour and 10 minutes, or until bread tests done.
Cool for 10 minutes in pan.
Turn out of pan; cool completely.
Yield: 1 loaf.

title: good chocolate pie or pudding
directions: Put 4 cups milk on to heat (medium heat).
Mix cornstarch, sugar and cocoa.
Add gradually the 2 cups reserved milk to make a thin batter.
When milk is at the boiling point, pour batter in milk and stir constantly until it boils, 1 minute.
Beat eggs; put some of the hot pudding in the beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Pour back into the pan; boil 1 minute longer.
Take off heat.
Add salt and vanilla; stir well.
If cooling in pan, sprinkle a little sugar on top to keep it from getting a firm layer on top.
Makes 2 pies.

title: coconut snowballs
directions: Mix all ingredients but coconut.
Blend well.
Refrigerate until firm.
Mold into small balls and roll in coconut until lightly covered.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Coconut may be tinted.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Rinse drained shrimp in cold water.
Cream the sour cream and cream cheese together until smooth.
Spread on a pretty plate. Pour cocktail sauce over this, leaving 1/4 inch of cream cheese mixture showing around edge.
Arrange shrimp in single layer on top.
Eat with Ritz or Town House crackers.
This makes an attractive dish for any occasion.

title: honey baserleckerli
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs and egg yolks, molasses, white corn syrup and lemon juice.
Sift together flour, baking powder, cinnamon and cloves.
Add to mixture by hand (spoon).
By hand, add flour and walnuts.
Cover with aluminum foil and grease 1 jellyroll pan and 1 regular cookie sheet.
Dump dough on sheet and use floured hands to pat dough out 1/2-inch thick.
Bake at 300° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Toothpick test clean.
These will be chewy if not overbaked.
Cool in a pan for 3 to 4 minutes, then flop out onto wax paper and cool for 5 to 6 minutes, then peel off foil. Cut into bars 1 1/2 to 2-inches square.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Layer 1:
Mix the cracker crumbs and 1/2 cup melted butter; press into long pan (13 x 9-inch).

title: fruit salad
directions: Stir all fruits together.
Add pudding mix.
Stir and chill several hours or overnight.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Mix milk, sugar and flour together.
Pour over melted butter.
Pour peaches over this mixture.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes at 400°.

title: fruit potpourri
directions: Combine all ingredients in serving bowl.
Chill until serving time. Yields 8 servings.

title: blackberry zebra
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Measure 1 cup and pour into 4 dessert glasses or parfait glasses.
Chill until set but not firm.
Chill remaining jello until slightly thickened.
Measure 1/4 cup and blend into 1 cup thawed Cool Whip. Add blackberries to remaining jello.
Spoon creamy mixture into glasses.
Top with fruited jello.
Chill until set.

title: oreo cookie refrigerator delight
directions: Crush Oreo cookies and save 1/2 cup and set aside.
In a large bowl, mix cookies with the margarine.
Spread this on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Refrigerate for 15 minutes.
Combine cream cheese, one of the 8 ounce containers of Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Mix together by hand until almost smooth.
Spread this mixture over the cookies.
Refrigerate for 15 minutes.

title: juicy oven roasted brisket
directions: *Cut recipe in half for small brisket.
But still cook 2 to 3 hours.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and oleo until fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, then flour.
Bake at 350° in Bundt pan about 1 hour.

title: tay tris choc balls
directions: Beat eggs.
Add shortening and sugar.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add syrup to beaten eggs.
Add flour and nuts.
Roll into small balls.
Cook 8 minutes at 375°.
Ice with cookie icing. You could use chocolate icing.

title: "prissy" pecans
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat and boil 3 minutes stirring constantly.
Spread on wax paper and separate pecan halves as they cool.
Pecans will be sugar coated, but not sticky.

title: meat loaf
directions: Variation:
Have also used Knorr vegetable soup mix.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Pour melted butter or margarine in 9 x 13 inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over melted butter.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts.
Then sprinkle coconut evenly over the above.
Then pour can of milk over coconut.
Bake in 350° oven 25 minutes or until lightly brown.
Let cool in pan 15 minutes.
Cut into bars.
Makes 24 bars.

title: harold's barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in corn oil.
Add remaining ingredients and blend.

title: seven layer cookies
directions: Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan in order given.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hamburger and cabbage casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion; salt and pepper to taste.
Cook cabbage, noodles and rice and add to casserole dish.
Add tomatoes to this mixture, then boil just a few cabbage leaves and put on top.
Pour can of tomato soup over this and bake for about 30 minutes.

title: onion twist rolls
directions: Combine sour cream and soup mix; set aside.
Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Add 2/3 cup sour cream mixture, butter, sugar, salt and 1 egg; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until well blended.
Gradually stir in enough flour to make a stiff dough.
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface; knead until smooth and elastic (about 8 minutes). Divide dough in half.
Roll half to a 12 x 6-inch rectangle; spread half of remaining sour cream mixture evenly onto rectangle. Fold rectangle in half lengthwise; cut into 1-inch strips.
Twist each strip of dough; place on greased baking sheets.
Repeat procedure.

title: magic swirl cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Generously grease and flour Bundt cake pan.
In bowl, beat butter, sugar and vanilla until well blended. Add eggs; beat well.
Stir together the flour, 1 teaspoon baking soda and salt.
Add alternately to butter mixture with buttermilk. Pour 4 cups batter into prepared pan.
In remaining batter, stir in topping and remaining 1/4 teaspoon baking soda.
Spoon over vanilla batter.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over surface.
Bake for 50 minutes, or until done.
Cool 10 minutes; remove from pan. Glaze with Chocolate Drizzle.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute veggies in oleo.
Mix in rice and corn.
Season to taste.
Add 1/2 of cheese.
Mix and pour into casserole.
Cover with remaining grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: hawiian chicken stir-fry
directions: Thaw broccoli and chicken, drain well. Drain pineapple juice, Reserve juice.

title: stuffed dates
directions: Chop nuts very fine.
Stuff each date with nuts.
Roll in confectioners sugar.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Grease foil and lay in 11 x 15-inch jelly roll pan. Mix all ingredients, except nuts, together in medium bowl. Pour onto greased foil. Sprinkle with nuts. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. When done, turn out onto dish towel, sprinkled with powdered sugar. Roll up as into jelly roll.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes. Unroll and remove foil. Spread with filling and roll up again.

title: sourdough bread
directions: Stir dry ingredients; gradually add water.
Stir several times a day for 3 days.

title: old fashioned southern lemonade
directions: Slice 4 lemons thinly and set aside. Roll each of the remaining lemons, unpeeled against the countertop with the palm of your hand to release their juices. Slice each lemon in half and squeeze juice into a large pitcher. Add water and SUGAH; stir until SUGAH is dissolved. Add sliced lemons. Pour lemonade into tall glasses full of ice, and enjoy!

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Place blackberries in the bottom of a 9 inch square pan. Combine flour, 1/2 cup sugar, baking powder, melted butter, milk, and vanilla.
Pour over fruit.
Combine sugar and water and pour over flour mixture.
Bake in 350 degrees oven for about 45 minutes.
Canned or frozen fruit may be used.

title: mexican fiesta
directions: Brown chopped bell pepper and onions with ground beef.
Drain. Add taco seasoning plus water required on package.
Simmer and add 1/2 cup taco sauce.
Spray oblong pan with Pam.
Spread refried beans in pan.
Add meat mixture.
Spread chopped jalapeno peppers if desired on top.
Spread the remaining bottle of taco sauce on top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes. Serve with sour cream and chips.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown and drain beef.
Stir in tomato paste, onion and seasonings.
(Mixture will be thick.)
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes, stirring often.
Place biscuits in greased muffin tin, pressing to cover bottom and up sides.
Spoon about 1/4 cup of meat mixture into biscuit lined cups and sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 10 servings for teens and adults, an easy recipe.
Serve with a salad for a main dish meal.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Use lemon juice and grate 1/2 of peel.
Beat together lemon peel, sugar, oleo and flour.
Add egg yolks.
Slowly add milk. Beat egg whites stiff, then fold in.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lemon blusher
directions: In pitcher, mix lemonade flavor soft drink mix and nutmeg; stir in remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serve in ice filled glasses and garnish, if desired, with lemon slices.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: oven apple butter
directions: Wash apples; cut out bad spots but do not peel or remove seeds. This adds flavor and color.
Cut in quarters and cook until very soft.
Run through sieve to make applesauce.
(Sauce may be stored in refrigerator several days.)

title: rotel potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until done; cool.
Slice and place in casserole dish.
Saute onion and bell pepper in oleo.
Add cheese, Ro-Tel tomatoes and mushrooms.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake in oven until bubbly.

title: yogurt
directions: Make the instant milk, adding the extra powder.
Add the evaporated milk.
Heat until almost boiling.
Let it cool to lukewarm in a casserole dish.
Add the yogurt and cover.
Wrap in aluminum foil and a towel.
Put in the unheated oven for 24 hours. Add vanilla, honey, fruit, etc., for flavoring.
Serves 4.

title: jello punch
directions: Mix ahead all but the ginger ale and let cool. May be made ahead and refrigerated. When ready to serve, add 1 quart of ginger ale.

title: divinity
directions: Mix the syrup and water together.
Stir over medium heat until the sugar dissolves.
Cook until a small amount dropped into cold water threads to a hard crack stage.
Have ready the stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour syrup very slowly into egg whites; continue beating, using a large spoon until mixture holds its shape.
Add the vanilla and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: cream cheese coffeecake
directions: Cream together the oleo, cream cheese and sugar.
Blend eggs and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, baking powder and soda. Add creamed mixture to eggs and vanilla.
Add sifted mixture alternately with milk to creamed mixture, beating until smooth. Put into a greased and floured 10-inch pie pan or a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown hamburger, green pepper and onion until tender.
Mix in soup.
Heat through; stir in sour cream and Worcestershire sauce and heat through.
Serve over noodles, rice or mashed potatoes.

title: macaroons
directions: Mix coconut, sugar, flour and salt in large bowl.
Stir in egg whites and almond extract until well blended.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes minutes or until edges of cookies are golden brown. Immediately remove from cookie sheets.
Cool on wire racks. Makes 3 dozen.

title: southern corn pudding
directions: Put in buttered casserole dish.
Place pan in hot water.
Bake in oven for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: brownies
directions: Mix
together
the sugar, cocoa, eggs and vanilla until it
is smooth.
Add 3/4 cup flour.
Melt 1 stick of butter in the 9-inch pan that you are to bake brownies in, then pour the butter	in with
the
other ingredients.
Mix and pour batter into buttered pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and ham gumbo
directions: *Note:
To toast flour, preheat oven to very hot (500°).
Line small cookie sheet with foil, turning up foil edges.
Spread flour in thin layer over foil.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until light brown.
Cool.

title: anice springer's barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients except vinegar and Worcestershire sauce and bring to a boil.
Add vinegar and Worcestershire sauce and pour over chicken or other meat.
Bake 1 hour in a covered pan at 300°; uncover and cook another hour.

title: jerry clower's marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots in boiling water to cover in large saucepan until tender-crisp, stirring occasionally; drain.
Place in large bowl. Cool.
Add onion, green pepper and sliced water chestnuts; mix well.
Combine soup, oil, sugar, vinegar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce, salt and black pepper in saucepan; mix well.
Bring just to the boiling point, stirring constantly.
Pour over vegetables. Marinate, covered, in refrigerator for 12 hours or longer.
Drain before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Preheat
oven
Mix together until zucchini is evenly coated;
pour
into
greased pie plate and bake for 30 minutes or until golden.

title: forgotten chicken
directions: Mix together mushroom soup, celery soup and milk.
Add rice and stir well.
Pour into greased (9 x 13-inch) baking dish.
Lay chicken pieces in dish and sprinkle dry onion soup over the top. Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours in electric oven or 325° for 2 hours in gas oven.

title: ice cream scones
directions: Mix ingredients together in order given. Drop on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until golden brown. Makes 12 scones.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin. Stir in flour, baking powder, soda and spices. Add raisins. Spread on greased and floured sheet cake pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Let cool and frost.

title: susan's microwave fudge
directions: Grease an 8 x 8 or 9 x 9-inch pan.
Mix cocoa and confectioners sugar.
Place butter on top of cocoa/sugar mixture. Also add milk; do not mix.
Cook in microwave dish 2 minutes on High.
Remove.
Add vanilla.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Add nuts.
Pour in a greased pan.
Refrigerate until firm.

title: scalloped asparagus casserole
directions: Melt butter; add flour, salt and pepper.
Make a smooth paste. Drain juice from asparagus and add enough milk to make 2 cups liquid.
Add to paste and stir on medium heat until thickened.
Do not scorch.
Add chopped pimentos.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in large baking dish. Sprinkle herb stuffing mix on top. Bake at 350° until real bubbly.

title: lentil pilaf
directions: In a saucepan, saute onions, carrots and green pepper in butter.
Add broth and water.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in lentils and pepper.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Add rice and stir well. Cover and simmer an additional 20 minutes until rice is tender. Add canned tomatoes and heat through until liquid is absorbed.

title: buckwheat cakes
directions: Make a stiff batter omitting salt. Cover tightly and allow to stand overnight.

title: stuffed bread
directions: Cut bread diagonally one way, then turn and cut diagonally the other way.
Place on enough heavy foil to cover completely.
Melt butter, poppy seed, salt, mustard, garlic salt and onion.
Stuff cheese and mushrooms into slits.
Drizzle butter mixture over top. Wrap in foil.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
A little longer won't hurt.
Great appetizer or side dish!
Can be frozen and baked when needed.

title: wendy's mud pie
directions: Make pudding by directions on box.
Let sit 5 minutes.
Stir in Cool Whip and 1/2 of crushed cookies.
Place 1 tablespoon cookies into the cups.
Fill cups 3/4 full with pudding mixture; top with remaining cookies.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: pepper prune stir-fry
directions: Soak prunes 1/2 hour in sherry or soy sauce.
Saute vegetables in butter (or margarine) until tender-crisp.
Add prunes and basil.
Season to taste.
Add mint.
Serve with rice.
Serves 4.

title: snowball cake
directions: Soften gelatine in cold water; add boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Add sugar, lemon juice and pineapple.
Chill until partially set.
Fold half the Cool Whip into the gelatine mixture. Tear up the angel food cake in small pieces (not crumbs).

title: cheese-ham ball
directions: Have cheeses at room temperature.

title: cocoa brownies
directions: Grease 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into pan and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
One-half cup nuts may be added if desired.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and brown sugar together.
To this mixture, add eggs and vanilla.
Place small amounts of oatmeal in blender and mix until it turns into a powder.
Mix together flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Now mix the first mixture with the second mixture.
Add chocolate chips, Hershey bar and chopped nuts.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan, saute garlic in butter only until garlic is tender.
Add 1/4 cup water, catsup and rest of ingredients.
Continue slowly heating until boiling point.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Good on chicken, pork and beef ribs.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour boiling water over oats.
Let stand 2 minutes.
Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, oatmeal, flour and spices.
Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: southern living's fresh apple salad
directions: Combine apples, celery and raisins.
Combine mayonnaise, sugar, salt and pepper.
Stir well.
Pour over apple mixture. Toss gently. Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Sift together sugar, flour, soda and cinnamon; set aside.
In a saucepan, combine water, margarine, oil and cocoa.
Bring to a boil and pour over dry ingredients, mixing well.
Combine buttermilk, eggs and vanilla and add to batter.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Start icing about 5 minutes before cake is done and frost in pan.

title: chunky chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a small bowl, mix flour, baking soda and salt.
In a large bowl, beat oleo, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla until creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Gradually add flour mixture. Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 11 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: 64 dollar salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water. Pour juice off canned fruit and add water to make 2 cups of cold juice. Add to gelatin mixture and set aside.

title: mozzarella beef pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef and drain.
Add spaghetti sauce and let simmer.
Spray pan with Pam nonstick cooking spray.
Put one can of crescent rolls in bottom of pan and brown.
Now add a layer of meat and two cheeses until all gone. Put other can of rolls on top and cook until rolls are done. Serve hot with your favorite salad.

title: vegetarian lasagna
directions: In olive oil saute onion, garlic, green pepper, basil, oregano, bay leaves and salt.
When onions are soft, add tomato puree, tomato paste, chopped tomatoes and 1/4 teaspoon black pepper. Reduce heat and simmer for 45 minutes.
Add mushrooms, parsley, salt and pepper.
Mix Ricotta cheese, eggs, salt, pepper, spinach, nutmeg and wheat germ to make the filling.
You don't have to cook the noodles.
Spread a little of the sauce in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Place a layer of noodles next and then 1/2 of the filling.
Next add in a layer 1/2 of the rest of the sauce.
Layer the remaining ingredients in this order:
1/2 of the Mozzarella cheese, noodles, remaining filling, a little sauce, the rest of the Mozzarella cheese, another layer of noodles and the last bit of sauce. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Place half of potatoes in greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Sprinkle half of onion and parsley over potatoes.
Melt margarine in 1-quart saucepan.
Add flour, salt and pepper; blend.
Add milk. Stir constantly and bring almost to the boiling point.
Remove from heat.
Pour half of mixture over ingredients in casserole.
Repeat with remaining ingredients and sauce.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: cola salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin with cola at room temperature.
Melt cream cheese with cherry juice.
Stir constantly to help dissolve the cheese.
Add cheese mixture to gelatin.
Add pecans, cherries and pineapple.
Mix well and place in mold or flat container.
Let chill 24 hours.

title: corned beef biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put on biscuit.
Wrap in foil and heat 20 minutes at 350°.
Freezes well.

title: spaghetti gravy
directions: Cook ground chuck, bell pepper, celery and onions. Drain off grease. Add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Simmer for 2 to 3 hours.
The last 30 minutes, add 1 cup grated cheese.

title: chocolate icebox dessert
directions: Be careful in your selection.
Do not choose too young.
When selected, give your entire thoughts to preparation for domestic use.
Some wives insist upon keeping them in a pickle, others are constantly getting them into hot water.
This may make them sour, hard, and sometimes bitter; even poor varieties may be sweet, tender and good, by garnishing them with patience, well-sweetened with love, and seasoned with kisses.
Wrap them in a mantle of charity.
Keep warm with a steady fire of domestic devotion and serve with peaches and cream.
Thus prepared, they will keep for years.

title: baked pineapple pudding
directions: In a bowl, mix the flour, sugar, butter and salt with a fork until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Remove 1/2 cup.
Mix in the cinnamon and reserve for topping.
Stir baking powder into remaining crumb mixture.
Whisk egg with pineapple and its juice. Mix into crumb mixture with baking powder.
Turn into a lightly buttered 1 to 1 1/2-quart round casserole or souffle dish.
Top with the crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until center is set but not dry.
Garnish with crushed pineapple and mint sprigs.
Serve warm, spooned into dessert dishes.
Pass the cream at the table.

title: nancy's homemade pimento cheese
directions: Combine cream cheese and pimento; stir well.
Add mayonnaise and remaining ingredients.
Stir well.
Cover and chill.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.
You may add 3 or 4 dashes of hot pepper sauce, if you like, and mix well for hotness.

title: rhubarb pudding
directions: Add enough milk to the first 4 ingredients to have it pour like cake mix consistency.
Cut rhubarb up and make a 2-inch layer in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sweeten rhubarb to your taste. Sprinkle in 1/2 package of strawberry gelatin, then pour the batter over rhubarb.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: 4 layer delight
directions: Layer No. 1:
Melt margarine and mix with flour and nuts; press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mile high pie
directions: Mix butter, brown sugar, flour and nuts.
Make as crust and put in large cake pan.
Bake
minutes or less at 350°; cool. Crumble up into crumbs and leave on bottom of cake pan. Place thawed strawberries,
unbeaten
egg
whites, white sugar and lemon juice.
Beat 20
minutes with electric mixer at high speed.
Fold in 1 cup
cream, whipped.
Put on top of crumbled crust and freeze.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: mama's peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, Karo syrup, water and peanuts until brown and peanuts pop.
Take off stove.
Put in butter, soda and vanilla. Stir vigorously.
Pour into three buttered pie pans. Cool and break.

title: grandma's syrup cake
directions: Mix together egg, shortening, milk and syrup.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to first mixture.
Stir well and bake in moderate oven for 30 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and turn in buttered, covered 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat sugar, Karo and eggs.
Add vanilla and melted margarine; beat well.
Add pecans.
Bake in unbaked pie shell 40 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Add marshmallow cream and flavoring. Great for: melon balls, pineapple, apples and grapes.

title: oatmeal coconut cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Beat together butter and sugars until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Combine flour, baking soda, salt and spices; add to butter mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats, coconut and chips.
Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 9 minutes for chewy cookies or 10 to 11 minutes for crisp cookies.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix thoroughly and keep in a tight container.
If it is to be kept a long time, it is best to keep it in the refrigerator, otherwise it will taste old.

title: bacon roll-ups
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Cut off ends of bread.
Spread each piece of bread with some soup.
Slice each piece of bread in thirds.
Place 1/2 piece of bacon on bread, roll up and place a toothpick in to hold.
Place on a baking dish, standing on end. Bake 5 minutes or until bacon cooks and bread looks toasted. Serve hot.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake in a 300° oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
(I place a pan of water on lower oven rack to keep moisture in bread.)

title: champagne touch
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over ice float fruit.
Yields 24 to 30 cups.

title: krazy corn
directions: Mix and stir sugar, oleo, syrup and cinnamon.
Mix and stir over low heat.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add soda and vanilla.
Pour over popcorn, then bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: broccoli & rice casserole
directions: In mixing bowl, combine all ingredients, then place in casserole dish.
Bake in oven at 350 F 30-40 minutes or until done.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels, margarine and sugar.
Pat into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and sugar well. Fold in Cool Whip and spread over crust.
Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups boiling water.
When partially set, add thawed strawberries and pineapple.
Spread over cream cheese.
Refrigerate until firm, about 2 to 3 hours.

title: microwave cherry crunch
directions: Mix pie filling and pineapple in square glass microwave cake pan.
Sprinkle cake mix evenly over top.
Sprinkle with pecans. Microwave on High for 15 minutes, stirring at least once.

title: the real mashed potatoes
directions: In crock-pot place whole, cleaned, skin on potatoes in pot. Cook until potato comes off fork easily.
When finished cooking, add butter and evaporated milk to potatoes.
With an electric blender or mixer, mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.

title: dream frosting
directions: P.S.
Non-name brand pudding works just as good.

title: crabmeat souffle
directions: Place 6 slices of bread in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, which has been greased.
Cover bread with slices of cheese, spread with crabmeat, and sprinkle with onion.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Lay other 6 slices of bread on top of crabmeat, etc. (like a sandwich).
Pour egg and milk mixture over all.
Make sure bread is moistened.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 hours or more. Bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes until browned and puffy.

title: crackling cornbread
directions: Bring milk, 6 tablespoons of the butter and the sugar to a boil together in a medium-size saucepan.
Remove from heat.

Pour into a large mixing bowl and let cool to lukewarm (105° to 115°). Stir yeast into the milk mixture and let stand for 10 minutes. Beat 3 of the eggs well in a small bowl and stir them and the salt into the milk-and-yeast mixture.
Stir in 5 cups of the flour, one cup at a time, until you achieve a sticky dough.

title: the best pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Can put in refrigerator overnight.
Batter will be thicker and smoother.

title: fresh fruit salad
directions: Gently mix all ingredients in medium bowl so fruit is well coated with orange juice (to prevent darkening).
Chill.
Makes 4 cups or 8 servings.

title: ernie's pot roast
directions: On a large piece of heavy-duty foil, pour 1 can of soup in the middle; place the roast on top of it.
Pour the second can of soup over the roast then the dry soup mix and A. 1. sauce.
Put the potatoes, carrots, onions and parsnips around the edge of the roast.
Bring the foil up and seal all edges tightly about 6-inches above the roast to form a little tent and no moisture will escape.
Bake at 350° for 3 to 4 hours.
This roast can also be done on a grill.
Also makes its own gravy.
Serves 4 to 6. Just toss a salad and enjoy!!

title: grandma coconut cream pie
directions: Take milk and eggs; get warm (do not boil).
Mix in other ingredients plus vanilla, to toasted coconut, as much as you like. Cook until thick.
Put in a baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue and sprinkle with more coconut.
Put back in oven until golden.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Place popcorn in very large container.
In saucepan mix syrup, sugar and margarine.
Bring to boil on medium heat.
Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add vanilla and baking soda.
Begin to slowly pour mixture over popcorn, stirring until all the popcorn is well coated.
Spread popcorn in 2 buttered 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 250° for 30 minutes, stirring popcorn at least once.
Let cool and break apart. Delicious.

title: nut balls
directions: In a large bowl, beat butter and sugar together until light and fluffy. Add flour and nuts, a little at
a time, while beating. Form 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. While a little warm, dust with confectioners sugar.

title: chocolate popcorn
directions: Pop a dishpan full of popcorn.
Separate corn to remove all unpopped corn.
Mix sugar, milk and cocoa.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Pour over popcorn, cool and eat.

title: easy chicken and rice casserole
directions: Sprinkle rice evenly in 2 quart casserole dish and sprinkle a little garlic salt on top.
Lay chicken on rice.
Mix soup and water and pour over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1-1/2 hours at 325°.

title: saucy chicken dinner
directions: In
large bowl combine sauce mix, gravy mix, onion salt and a dash of pepper.
Gradually stir in 1 cup water and milk. Cook, uncovered,
at
Cook for 5 to 6 minutes, stirring after each minute.
Stir
in peas, chicken, mushrooms and pimentos. Cook, uncovered,
at
Cook,
for
minutes, stirring twice. Serve over noodles.
makes 6 servings.
Total cooking time: 10 minutes.

title: roast red bell pepper soup
directions: In blender or food processor, puree bell peppers.
In large saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in flour; then stir in half-and-half and chicken broth.
Cook stirring constantly until mixture thickens and bubbles.
Stir in bell pepper puree, salt, pepper, and hot pepper sauce.
Simmer and serve.
Serves 4.

title: apple rice slaw
directions: Combine rice, apples, cabbage and carrots; set aside. Blend remaining ingredients and pour over slaw. Toss and chill until ready to serve.

title: hot potato salad casserole(even people who hate potato salad like this!)
directions: Gently mix together in a very large bowl the potatoes, cheese and onion.
Shake mayonnaise and milk in a jar.
Gradually pour mayonnaise/milk mixture over potato/cheese mixture and toss gently, adding salt and pepper to taste.
Spread in a large (at least 9 x 13-inch) baking dish and top with crumbled bacon and sliced olives. Can be made a day ahead and stored in the refrigerator.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
These are also great as leftovers.

title: jonnie's buttered chicken
directions: Roll chicken in salt, pepper and flour and dip in margarine. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Turn over and bake an additional 15 minutes.
Add canned milk, water and cream of chicken soup.
Pour over chicken and bake an additional 30 to 45 minutes.

title: black & white cookies(yield: 8 large cookies)
directions: 1. Heat Oven to 350°.
Coat 2 baking sheets with cooking spray.
In medium-size bowl, combine flour, baking soda and salt. In large bowl with electric mixer on medium speed, beat together sugar and butter until smooth and creamy, about 1 minute.
Beat in egg until well combined.
On low speed, alternately beat in flour mixture and the buttermilk, ending with flour mixture; beat until smooth.

title: jam cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream margarine and brown sugar together.
Add eggs and buttermilk.
Sift flour and add to baking powder, salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Beat into creamed mixture. Fold in jam and nuts.
Grease and flour 9-inch tube pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes.

title: ranch-style soup
directions: In saucepan, cook onion in hot oil until tender but not brown. Stir in chicken broth, rice, tomato puree, salt and pepper. Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for 25 minutes. Stir in frozen peas; simmer 5 minutes longer.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate covered marshmallows
directions: Place chocolate chips and shortening in a glass measuring cup. Microwave for 1 1/2 to 3 minutes, or until chips are shiny and soft; then stir until smooth.
Place nuts or candy sprinkles on a shallow plate.
Insert toothpick in top of each marshmallow.
Dip marshmallow in chocolate to cover completely.
Roll in nuts or sprinkles about 3/4 of the way up the sides.
Set on wax paper and let set until firm.
Repeat until all have been dipped.
Makes 48 to 50.

title: carrot cake
directions: Spray 8-inch fluted tube pan with nonstick cooking spray and set aside.
In mixing bowl with electric mixer, beat together eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla until mixture is light and fluffy.
Using mixer at low speed, beat in milk powder, flour, baking soda and cinnamon, beating thoroughly, until combined.
Add remaining ingredients and stir to combine.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed and drain.
Combine potato soup and sour cream; add broccoli and mix thoroughly.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole and sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: texas style chili soup
directions: Brown the ground beef together with onion and garlic.
Season with salt and black pepper.
Put all ingredients in a large skillet or pot and simmer approximately for 45 minutes.
Serve with grated cheddar and mozzarella cheese.
Goes well with corn chips.

title: creamy coconut icing
directions: Mix in a double boiler.
Boil and stir until stiff (8 to 10 minutes).
Spread over cake and top with coconut.

title: elegant pumpkin dessert
directions: Mix together pumpkin, milk, eggs, sugar, salt and spices and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over all.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Pour melted butter evenly over the whole thing and bake for 1 1/2 hours in 325° oven.
Knife should come out clean when testing for doneness.
Cool and cut in serving pieces (12). Top with the whipped cream or Cool Whip.

title: spaghetti-chicken casserole
directions: Cook vermicelli.
Saute onion and green pepper in butter or margarine.
Mix remaining ingredients with vermicelli, onion and green pepper in large bowl.
Place in casserole dish and bake, covered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
This mixture freezes well.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, milk, margarine and cocoa.
Boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Blend and drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: snowball dumplings for stew
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in milk quickly to make a soft dough.
Drop by spoonful on top of hot meat or vegetable stew mixture.
Cover tightly and cook for 12 minutes.
Serve at once.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients.
Place pecans in unbaked pie shell.
Pour in mixture; mix thoroughly.
Bake 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: fudgy mocha nut pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In medium saucepan, over low heat, melt butter.
Add cocoa; stir until smooth.
Stir in sweetened condensed milk, water, eggs, instant coffee and chocolate chips; whisk until blended.
Remove from heat.
Stir in pecans and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake 50 minutes or until center is set.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Combine pudding and pineapple; mix well.
Add marshmallows and nuts.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Partially melt chocolate over a double-boiler.
Remove from heat and beat until smooth.
Stir in marshmallows and nuts. Spread in buttered 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Chill.
When firm, cut in squares.

title: smoky ham and bean bake
directions: Drain beans, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Pour into a 4-quart casserole.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Cook, covered, in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli and noodles parmesan
directions: Cut broccoli into bite size pieces.
In a covered 4-quart pan over medium heat, in 1-inch of boiling water, cook broccoli 6 minutes.
Drain well.
In same saucepan over medium heat, in hot margarine, cook onion and garlic until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in soup and tarragon, mixing well.
Add cheese and Parmesan, stirring until melted.
Stir in sour cream, broccoli and cooked noodles.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Cover, bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 8 servings.

title: tortilla rolls
directions: Cut up ham and green onions; mix together and sour cream, cream cheese, Accent and jalapeno peppers.
Spread mixture over tortilla and roll tortilla up.
Chill.
Cut tortillas into slices.

title: paw paw's chicken enchiladas
directions: Melt Velveeta with milk; set aside.
For filling, mix onion, bell pepper, cream cheese, 1/2 cup salsa, green chilies and chicken and half the Velveeta mixture.
Mix the other half of Velveeta mixture into reserved 1/2 cup salsa for topping.
Spoon filling mixture evenly into tortillas and roll up.
Place in baking dish and pour topping over all.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Cream butter, 1 1/2 cups sugar and eggs until light and fluffy.
In separate bowl combine dry ingredients and add to mix until well blended.
Refrigerate for 30 minutes or longer.

title: jiffy corn pudding
directions: Drain liquid from whole kernel corn.
Mix together corn and cornbread mix.
Add beaten eggs, shortening and sour cream.
Mix well.
Bake in a greased 9 x 9-inch pan or 1 1/2-quart casserole for 1 hour at 350°.
Diced ham may be added.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: bean soup
directions: Brown hamburger.
Combine hamburger, beans and tomatoes in a pot and heat to boiling.
Simmer for 15 minutes after adding Worcestershire sauce to taste.
This is even better the second day.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix and roll between waxed paper. Makes one 9-inch pie (2 crust) or 2 pie shells.

title: lasagna rolls
directions: Cook lasagna; pat dry.
Mix Ricotta, Parmesan, 1/2 the Mozzarella, salt, egg, pepper, parsley and fried beef (drained). Spread on lasagna noodles; roll up.
Place in baking dish; spoon 1/2 cup sauce in pan.
Cover with remaining sauce and top with Mozzarella.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour.

title: shepherd pie
directions: Broil ground beef.
Add water, mushrooms, carrots, onions and salt and pepper.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Cook cauliflower until barely tender.
Put in blender with liquid.
Add dry nonfat milk. Blend until just mashed a little.
Spray dish with Pam.
Put beef mixture in.
Top with cauliflower.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°. Serves 4.

title: fruit crumble
directions: In an 8 x 1 1/2-inch round microwave-safe baking dish, stir together fruit pie filling, lemon juice and cinnamon.
In a mixing bowl, stir together rolled oats, brown sugar and flour.
Stir in melted margarine until well combined.
Sprinkle oat mixture on top of fruit mixture.
Microwave, uncovered, for 12 to 14 minutes, giving the dish a turn once.
Serve warm.
Top with ice cream.

title: sweet and sour cole slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate.
Will keep several days and is best if let set to marinate for 24 hours.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and cut the ends off.
Put in cold pack canner. Make a mixture of vinegar and water; you may need several cups of vinegar and water.
Sweeten to taste.
Pour over cucumbers, enough to cover them.
Cook until cucumbers turn their color.
Place in jars.
Pour juice over them and seal.
Do not overcook or they will be soft, not crunchy.

title: rachel's lemon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan or 2 (8 x 8-inch) squares or 2 rounds.
Combine cake mix and Jell-O. Add next three ingredients one at a time, blending thoroughly after each addition.
Beat with electric mixer at medium speed for 3 to 4 minutes.
Pour into prepared pans and bake for 40 to 45 minutes until cake tester comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes, then turn out onto platter or platters.

title: filling for devil's food cupcakes
directions: Make devil's food cupcakes using mix.
Bake and let cool. When cold, cut circle out of top of each.
Fill with following filling and replace top.

title: nutmeg cream melon salad
directions: In large bowl stir together all ingredients except grapes, cantaloupe and honeydew.
Add remaining ingredients and toss to coat.

title: "ooma's" angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water for 5 minutes.
Warm milk and add yeast.
Let sit at least 10 minutes.
Add sugar.
Sift flour.
Cut shortening in.
Blend all ingredients together.
Roll out.
Let rise at least 10 minutes to 1 hour.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 20 minutes until brown.

title: ultimate chocolate chip cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine shortening, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Beat egg into creamed mixture.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Mix into creamed mixture just until blended. Stir in chocolate chips and pecan pieces.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of dough 3-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy cookies, 11 to 13 minutes for crisp cookies.
Let cool.
Remove cookies onto foil.

title: cowboy coffee cake
directions: Combine flour, salt, sugar and shortening; mix until crumbly. Reserve 1/2 cup of mixture.
Chopped nuts can be added to this if desired.

title: granny o'brien's brown irish soda bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients very well or you will get lumps of soda or salt.
Moisten with yogurt until it has a bendy consistency.
Work very fast or the soda will lose its snap before you get it to the oven, which you preheat for 5 minutes at 450° (gas oven 7 to 8 minutes).
The intense heat is to harden the crust and stop the gas from escaping.
Form into a high round on a floured baking sheet, mark with a cross and bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Yields 1 large loaf which freezes admirably if you want to cut it in half and keep some.

title: hot mexican bean spread
directions: Brown meat and 1/4 cup of onions in skillet or chafing dish. Stir in ketchup, chili powder and salt.
Mash in beans and heat thoroughly.
Garnish with cheese, olives and 1/4 cup onion.
Serve with crackers and chips.

title: healthy oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat egg whites and salt until stiff. Gradually fold in sugar, then fold in oats and vanilla. Moisten with the milk. Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: grandma's rolls
directions: Put yeast in cup with 3/4 cup of lukewarm water; add tablespoon of sugar and stir.
Wait until it rises.
Boil milk and shortening in boiler and let cool.
Mix yeast mixture and milk mixture together.
Knead in with flour gradually.
Let rise 2 times and make into rolls.

title: pecan turtle cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream butter, brown sugar and egg.
Add remaining ingredients except egg white and pecans.
Refrigerate. Place cluster of 3 pecan halves with points together on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Shape teaspoon of dough into small balls. Dip in egg white.
Place ball in center of pecans.
Flatten and bake 12 to 15 minutes.
Frost with chocolate frosting.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add sugar and salt gradually. Beat until eggs form stiff peaks.
Fold in nuts and chips. Preheat oven to 350°.
Place cookies by teaspoons on cookie sheet. Turn oven off.
Place cookies in oven and leave for 4 hours.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix together peaches and sugar.
Let stand while mixing batter.
Melt butter in large casserole dish.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion in 4 tablespoons butter until soft.
Stir in flour.
Add water.
Stir and cook until thick.
Blend in cheese. Add to broccoli.
Beat eggs and add gently into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover with crumbs.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: easy buffalo wings
directions: Place drumettes in a bowl and toss with the salt, paprika, garlic powder and cayenne pepper.

title: collard greens
directions: Wash each leaf of green separately.
After carefully washing several times, hold stem tightly and strip leaves from stem. Discard stems; they are tough.
Place greens in pressure cooker; add salt, water and meat.
Cook approximately 35 minutes.
Set aside.
Cool, remove cover and continue cooking at high heat for 15 minutes more.

title: turkey noodle soup
directions: Put a meaty turkey frame into a large pot.
Add 3 quarts of water and 1 to 2 tablespoons salt.
Heat to boiling; skim foam. Cover and simmer 2 hours or longer.
Strain broth and refrigerate. Remove fat from surface.
When turkey frame is cool, pick off meat. Combine broth with vegetables and seasonings.
Heat to boiling. Simmer 10 minutes.
Stir in noodles.
Simmer until noodles are tender, about 5 to 10 minutes.
Stir in turkey and heat through.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Cook and debone chicken.
Melt butter in saucepan and saute onion and celery.
Add soups and chicken broth.
Put spaghetti in baking dish; top with chicken.
Pour soups over top.
Top with cheese. Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: cream cake
directions: Beat egg yolks; add sugar, water and then beaten stiff egg whites, then vanilla, flour and baking powder.
Grease and flour 3 (9-inch) round cake pans and divide cake batter equally.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: grilled turkey sandwich
directions: Toast bread lightly on one side under broiler.
Turn over and spread untoasted side with deviled ham.
Top with slice of turkey and cheese slice.
Broil under low broil until cheese is slightly bubbly.
Serve immediately.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, salt and water.
Bring to a boil and cook until it forms a hard ball.
Stir in peanuts and cook slowly until it turns a light brown.
Remove from heat and stir in soda.
Let it foam and stir down twice.
Spread immediately in large buttered pan.
Break into pieces.

title: holiday strawberry salad
directions: Tear little pieces of angel food cake; slice strawberries and fold in bananas.
Add Cool Whip and serve.

title: 5-minute pie
directions: Whip together condensed milk and lemon juice.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust and let stand 5 to 10 minutes or until ready to serve.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Will be quite stiff.
Shape into balls.
Bake at 400° approximately 20 minutes.

title: lemon lush
directions: Mix the flour, walnuts and margarine with a pastry blender and pat into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until light brown.
Cool.

title: caramel corn (baked)
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Boil without stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in soda and vanilla.
Pour over popped corn, mixing well. Turn into 2 large shallow baking pans or cookie sheets.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes. Remove from oven. Stir, let cool. Stir again so it doesn't stick in big chunks.
Eat up!

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Scramble hamburger meat; mix creamed soups together.
Layer bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with Tater Tots, layer of soups and layer of hamburger meat.
Repeat layers.
Cover with onions and bake at 375° for about an hour.

title: chocolate or strawberry delight
directions: Combine ingredients and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until brown.
Cool completely.

title: jogger in jug
directions: Mix and store in the refrigerator.
It restores your energy quickly!

title: texas cake
directions: In a saucepan, heat to boiling 2 sticks butter or margarine, 1 cup water and 4 tablespoons cocoa, then add sugar, flour, soda, buttermilk, eggs and nuts and mix good.
Pour on large cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
While baking, make icing.

title: cool cucumber pasta salad
directions: Boil pasta until tender. Rinse in cool water; drain. Add mayonnaise and vegetables. Add salt and pepper to taste. Refrigerate until 30 minutes before serving. Serves 4.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together and bring to a boil. Boil for 1 minute, then add vanilla, cocoa and oats. Spread and cool in fridge.

title: p-nut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and milk; bring to a boil, stirring constantly, over medium heat.
Remove from stove.
Beat in peanut butter.
Spread in lightly buttered, 8-inch square pan. Refrigerate for 15 to 20 minutes.
Score.
Return to refrigerator for 2 hours.

title: cucumber sandwich
directions: Blend cucumbers and onion until fine.
Put on paper towels and squeeze out liquid, then add to soft cream cheese, Miracle Whip, lemon juice and salt.
Mix, then spread on bread.

title: "fried" bread
directions: Preheat oven and cast-iron skillet at 400°.
Mix ingredients. Pour into skillet.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes.

title: pineapple sheet cake
directions: Beat together eggs, then add flour, soda, sugar, vanilla and pineapple.
Stir with a spoon until mixed together.
Bake in a cookie sheet for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: open-faced italian pork sandwich
directions: Marinate pork chops in Italian dressing for 10 minutes. Remove pork from marinade and brown quickly in hot skillet with 1 tablespoon oil.
Season with salt and pepper; serve on Italian bread.
Serve with sliced cucumbers and cherry tomatoes to garnish.
Add lettuce and purple onions to sandwich.
Serves 4.

title: cranberry fluff
directions: Place
cranberries, sugar
and	marshmallows
in
bowl. Cover and place in refrigerator overnight.
Add apples, pecans and whipped cream.
Mix well and refrigerate.

title: sauerkraut relish
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Store in refrigerator. This will keep indefinitely.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in jackets about 30 minutes.
Chill.
Peel and grate.
Combine cheese, milk and 2 tablespoons oleo in a saucepan. Cook over low heat until oleo and cheese melt.
Remove from heat; stir in sour cream, salt and pepper.
Fold cheese mixture into potatoes.
Pour into a greased casserole.
Dot with oleo and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: chocolate date cake
directions: Mix together dates, hot water and soda.
Let cool.
Cream sugar, shortening, salt and vanilla and add date mixture.
Mix in dry ingredients and then the egg.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with the chocolate pieces and chopped nuts.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: swedish coffee twist
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water with 1 teaspoon sugar.
Bring buttermilk and butter to boiling.
Pour into large bowl with sugar and salt.
Beat in 2 cups flour and then beat in yeast mixture and egg and soda.
Gradually stir in the remaining flour until mixture cleans sides of bowl.
Turn out on floured board and knead smooth and elastic, adding more flour to prevent sticking.
Turn bowl over dough and let set for 15 minutes.
Roll into a rectangle and spread with melted butter, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Fold over and cut into strips and twist.
Raise on cookie sheet for 45 minutes in warm place.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes until lightly browned.
Frost lightly with powdered sugar glaze.
Serve warm.

title: carob pan cake
directions: Mix sugar and flour; set aside.
Boil oleo, carob, cooking oil and water.
Add to flour mixture.
Add soda in buttermilk.
Add eggs, vanilla and salt.
Pour into greased broiler pan and bake 35 minutes at 375°.

title: tuna pockets
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Stir together all ingredients, except crescent rolls and beaten egg.
Separate roll dough to form 8 rectangles, pinching dough together at perforations to seal.

title: lemon cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, lemon juice, lemon peel, vanilla and eggs.
Pour into ready-to-use graham cracker crumb crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool; refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Garnish with whipped cream and lemon slices.
Makes 8 servings.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt oleo, chocolate chips and peanut butter over low heat. In large bowl, pour melted mixture over Corn Chex.
Stir until well coated.
Pour powdered sugar in large brown grocery bag and add Corn Chex mixture.
Close bag and shake until well coated. Pour into serving dish and refrigerate.

title: nebraska city corn
directions: Mix all the above ingredients then pour into baking dish which has been sprayed with cooking spray. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour being sure to stir very well after 30 minutes in the oven.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop by teaspoonful into very hot deep fry.
Fry until golden brown.

title: chocolate chip scones
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Spray a cookie sheet.
Stir Bisquick mix, chocolate chips, 1/3 cup whipping cream, 3 tablespoon sugar, the egg and vanilla until soft dough forms.
Pat into a 8 inch circle on cookie sheet.
(If dough is too sticky, dip fingers in Bisquick.)
Brush circle with dab of additional cream and sprinkle of sugar.
Cut into 8 wedges, but do not separate.
Bake about 12 minutes or until golden brown; carefully separate.
Serve warm. Yields:
8 scones.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well with hands.
Mold into 1 large or 2 small loaves. Cover with tomato ketchup and bake at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Will serve 6 people.

title: cherry pie filling cake
directions: Combine in a large bowl the flour, sugar, oil, eggs, vanilla, baking soda and cinnamon; mix well.
Stir in cherry pie filling, chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: In large saucepan, mix together soups, Ro-Tel tomatoes, onion, green pepper and chicken stock.
In 13 x 9-inch greased pan, layer corn tortillas, chicken, shredded Cheddar and soup mixture.
Repeat layers and top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until bubbly.
I like to use Doritos instead of corn tortillas for a saltier taste.

title: homemade pretzels
directions: Mix your baking soda in your buttermilk. Mix all ingredients. Knead until dough works well. Soft dough makes a much better pretzel. Roll into pretzel. Cook in lye water (6 c. water to 2 tsp. lye) until pretzels float to top. Take out of water and drain, then salt, put in a heavily greased baking pan. Bake in a 450 - 500 degree oven until nice and brown. Change the lye water about half way through or else add more lye and water.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Cook in pressure cooker about 40 minutes.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Mix together sugar and hot water and stir until sugar is dissolved.
Heat over high heat, bringing to a boil and boiling about 1 minute.
Add coconut flavoring.

title: turkey barley soup
directions: Place turkey carcass, celery, carrots, onions, parsnips, garlic, 1 cup dill, parsley, salt, pepper and water in extra large soup pot over medium heat.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 3 hours.
Skim foam off soup as it cooks.
After 3 hours, remove carcass, cool and shred off all the meat.
Return meat to soup and add barley.
Simmer for an additional 40 minutes.
Add remaining cup of dill and serve piping hot.
Remaining soup can be frozen.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes, 1/2 cup margarine, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Stir well.
Spoon into a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish. Mix 1/4 cup margarine with crumbs.
Sprinkle over potato mixture. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: pumpkin pie filling or custard
directions: Beat egg whites with sugar.
Add the milk; mix well with pumpkin.
Add spices and pour into an 8-inch pie pan for custard or 8-inch pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: frozen apricot dessert
directions: Melt
oleo
and add almond extract and toasted almonds. Mix this
with
crushed wafers.
Put half of mixture in bottom of large
x 9-inch) oblong dish.
Slice ice cream and put half of it over wafers.
Place layer of apricot preserves (use all) over
ice
cream.
Add
another
layer of ice cream.
Add remainder of
wafers
on
top.
Freeze.
To serve, add whipped cream.
Serves 18.

title: hershey's kisses cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Roll dough into small balls. Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° until slightly golden. Place a Kiss in the middle of each cookie immediately after you remove them from the oven.

title: lib cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Pat into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 30 minutes at 325°.
Cool.
Mix the cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1/2 container Cool Whip; spread over first layer.
Mix the milk and pudding; pour over the second layer.
Add rest of Cool Whip and nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Put sliced potatoes in a lightly greased baking dish. Top with diced onions. Then arrange asparagus on top of this (canned or fresh can be used). Dot with butter; add salt and pepper. Bake 45 to 60 minutes in 325° oven until potatoes are tender. Layer cheese on top and let melt before serving.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well.
Good for cauliflower, broccoli, carrots, etc.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt, and soda.
Set aside.
Cream shortening and both sugars.
