Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients.
Add oatmeal and nuts.
Mix.
Chill overnight.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet.
350° - 10 minutes.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: rum cake
directions: Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan for 1 hour at 325°.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Mix and roll in balls.
Flatten on cookie sheet. Bake until brown at 350°.

title: "mock" chicken and dumplings
directions: In saucepan, cook soup as directed, making sure you get out the lumps.

While soup is cooking, cover bottom of deep casserole dish with unbaked biscuits, making sure you do not overlap them. When soup is done, pour over unbaked biscuits until fully covered. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until tops of biscuits are brown.
Serve hot.

title: spicy barbecue drumsticks
directions: You will need 1 oven bag, regular size.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cream together cheese, sugar and eggs.
Pour over cake dough.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chicken tenders with honey mustard sauce
directions: Honey-Mustard Sauce:
Combine honey and Dijon mustard to taste, approximately 2/3 mustard to 1/3 honey.

title: banana pudding
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk.
Fold in Cool Whip, condensed milk and vanilla until mixed well.
Layer dish with pudding, vanilla wafers and banana.
Continue to layer and end with pudding on top.
Decorate with crushed vanilla wafers or whole wafers on top.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Soften butter and margarine, then add sugar.
Beat until fluffy, then add eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour and baking powder; add.
Add vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Add milk, then mix.
Add sour cream.
Mix well.
Pour batter into cake pan and bake.

title: spinach pie
directions: Combine spinach, Ricotta, egg, nutmeg, flour, salt and 1/4 cup each of Parmesan and melted butter.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and top with remaining 1/2 cup each of Parmesan and butter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes before cutting. Serves 6 to 8.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In a greased casserole dish, place broccoli, cauliflower and carrots.
Melt Cheez Whiz and soup on low heat.
Pour over vegetables.
Top with French fried onions.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Uncover last 5 minutes to brown onions.

title: italian noodle casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion; drain.
In a large pot add remainder of ingredients except for noodles and cheese.
Let this cook for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
In a separate pot cook noodles until done.
In a large Pyrex dish (13 x 9-inches) add all ingredients; top with cheese.
Cook on 350° until cheese is melted.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: my own chicken and dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish that has been well-greased.
Bake in a 350° oven until done.

title: hungarian noodles and cabbage
directions: Mix the salt and cabbage together; let stand 30 minutes. Squeeze out as much liquid as possible. Heat the butter in a deep skillet. Add the onions, cabbage, sugar and pepper. Cook over low heat, stirring frequently, until cabbage is browned, about 45 minutes. Add the noodles and toss to blend thoroughly. Makes 8 servings.

title: romano potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes a day ahead. Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Beat 2 eggs until light and fluffy.
Add 20 ounce can crushed pineapple (undrained), 2 cups all-purpose flour, 1 cup white sugar, 1 cup brown sugar and 2 teaspoons baking soda. Mix by hand. Do not use mixer.
Stir in 1 cup chopped walnuts.
Spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and freeze.
Thaw out 10 minutes before serving.

title: chicken my way
directions: Brown chicken in butter; add cream of chicken soup and water. Let simmer about 45 minutes.
Add more water as needed.
Pepper if desired.
Doesn't need salt.

title: california raisin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into crust.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chocolate biscuits
directions: Cream together.
Spread over layer of biscuits (you can use leftover).
Cook under broiler.

title: brown rice
directions: Melt butter in casserole dish.
Add uncooked rice, beef broth and consomme to melted butter.
Cook at 375° for 1 hour uncovered.

title: cheese petit fours
directions: Cut crust from
2 1/2 loaves bread, 3 slices at a time. Beat other
ingredients until consistency of icing.
Spread on slices. Cut into 4
pieces and ice tops and sides.
Freeze on cookie sheet and
then
store in plastic bags.
Bake frozen at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Spray an 8-inch tube pan with nonstick cooking spray and dust lightly with whole wheat flour.
Blend the oil and sugar in a large bowl.
Add the egg yolks one at a time, beating well.
Add the vanilla.
In another bowl, sift together the flour, salt and baking soda.
Alternately fold the flour mixture and the yogurt into the oil and sugar mixture.
Set aside.

title: whipped cherry salad
directions: Mix ingredients and put in serving dish.
Cool and serve.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown meat in 2 tablespoons oil.
Simmer until soft.
Cut up celery and onions.
Add to meat and cook until meat is soft.
Add 1/2 cup soy sauce and cook for 10 minutes.
Add bean sprouts with juices (2 tablespoons of flour and water to thicken).
Serve with rice.

title: spinach spread
directions: Mix together.
Serve with crackers, cocktail rye or dark bread.

title: delicious veal and peppers
directions: Gently saute onions.
Add veal and stir until veal is light pink in color.
Add mushrooms and peppers.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer gently for 1 to 2 hours in covered pan.

title: cashew chicken
directions: Bone chicken breasts and remove skin.
Slice horizontally in 1/8-inch thick slices, then cut in 1 inch squares.
Arrange on a tray.
Remove the ends and strings from pea pods and chop broccoli.
Wash and slice mushrooms.
Cut the green part of the onions into 1-inch lengths and then slash both ends several times making small fans; slice the white part 1/4-inch thick.
Slice bamboo shoots.
Pour chicken broth into small pitcher. Mix together soy sauce, cornstarch and sugar; pour into a small pitcher.
Place oil and nuts in containers.
Arrange at the table with electric frying pan or wok.

title: summer punch
directions: Line a baking dish with waxed paper.
Place in refrigerator until very cold.
Using ice cream scoop, make small balls of sherbet.
Arrange in single layer in dish; freeze until hard.

title: ida's garlic mashed potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes and cut in quarters.
Cook in covered pot containing a small amount of boiling water, 20 to 25 minutes or until tender.
Remove from heat.
Drain and recover the pot.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Dip or brush chicken in yogurt.
Roll in crushed crackers. Place chicken in baking dish.
Bake for 30 minutes on each side, about 1 hour total.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: marbled cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Combine crumbs, cocoa, sugar and margarine.
Press firmly in bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Pour half the batter evenly over prepared crust.
Stir melted chocolate into remaining batter.
Spoon over vanilla batter.
With table knife or metal spatula, gently swirl through batter.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool, then chill.
Cut into bars. Store, covered, in refrigerator.

title: cheesecake tarts
directions: You will also need cupcake holders.

title: chicken dijon
directions: In large skillet over medium-high heat, cook chicken on all sides in butter until browned and tender, about 15 to 20 minutes. Remove chicken to heated platter; keep warm.
To drippings in skillet, add garlic, onion, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir until onion is soft, about 5 minutes.
Stir in half and half, parsley and mustard.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, until sauce is slightly thickened.
Return chicken to pan; heat through, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: southern chess pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour together.
Beat eggs slightly with cream, lemon juice and vanilla.
Add to sugar and flour.
Add melted butter and mix well.
Put in a 9-inch pie shell and cook at 325° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: company potatoes
directions: In a large bowel, stir in the following order: margarine, soup, sour cream, cheese and then potatoes.
Spread evenly in 12x9 inch pan. Bake for 75 min. Let stand for 10 minutes. Use salt and pepper to liking.

title: savory pepper steak
directions: Cut steak in strips.
Combine flour, salt and pepper; coat meat strips.
In large skillet, cook meat in hot oil until browned on all sides.
Drain tomatoes, reserving liquid.
Add tomato liquid, water, onion, garlic and gravy base to meat in skillet. Cover and simmer for about 1 1/4 hours, until meat is tender. Uncover; stir in Worcestershire.
Add green pepper strips.
Cover and simmer for 5 minutes.
If necessary, thicken gravy with a mixture of a little flour and cold water.
Add drained tomatoes; cook about 5 minutes more.
Serve over hot rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Dust steak strips with flour and brown in hot oil.
Remove and drain off excess grease.
Drain skillet and add soup broth and return meat strips.
Cover and simmer until tender.
Then 5 minutes before serving, add the mushrooms and sour cream. Recover.
Cook noodles and pour mess over noodles.

title: baked sliced potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes into 1/4-inch slices.
Place in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix butter and oil; brush slices and pour rest over potatoes.
Sprinkle with garlic, salt and thyme.
Makes 4 servings.

title: vegetable soup (no fat)
directions: Add onion and celery to V-8 juice.
Cook until tender.
Add other vegetables.
Cook to desired consistency.
Add any seasonings you prefer, like thyme, oregano or basil.
Very good by itself. Great in the cold months.
Very easy to make.
You can add any vegetable that has little or no fat content.

title: italian macaroni casserole(makes 8 to 10 servings.)
directions: Brown ground beef in large pan. Add onion, bell pepper, Worcestershire sauce, tomato sauce, water, salt and pepper. Add uncooked macaroni. Let mixture boil until macaroni is thoroughly mixed and coated in sauce. Bake in 350° oven about 30 minutes and until macaroni is tender. Sprinkle with cheese and bake until it melts. Great for company.

title: bacon and cheese puff pie
directions: From crust in ungreased 9-inch pie plate with dinner rolls. Sprinkle with bacon, top with tomato slices.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place cheese slices on top.
Beat egg whites until stiff and put aside.
In large bowl, combine yolks, sour cream, flour, salt and pepper.
Blend well.
Gently fold in whites until a few lumps remain.
Do not over-blend.
Pour into crust over cheese. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife comes out clean and crust is brown.
Can be refrigerated up to 4 hours before baking.
Can substitute onion salt for salt in puff topping.

title: california squash
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Alternate layers of squash, onion, tomatoes, cheese, peppers and salt and pepper.
Place in a 1 1/2-quart baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Mix dressings and seasonings in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix lightly.
Refrigerate.
Makes 12 servings.

title: baked potato soup
directions: Clean, cut and core tomatoes. Cook until tomatoes are soft enough to put through a colander. Use only the pulp and juice. Discard the skins and seeds. Clean peppers and onions. Puree in the food processor. Use tomato pulp, juice and pureed onions and peppers. Add remaining items and bring to a boil; continue cooking at medium boil for about 1 1/2 hours. Have canning jars and lids ready. Heat your flats in water. Make sure water did boil. Removing one flat at a time, dry off flat and make sure the top of jar is clean and dry. Place flat on jar and tighten flat with a band. Let sit until cool. Store at room temperature. Makes several pints.

title: "guide to modern meals" pizza dough(another foods lab special)
directions: Put shortening, sugar and salt in large mixing bowl.
Add boiling water and cool to 120°.
Sprinkle yeast over 1/4 cup lukewarm water and stir to dissolve.
Add about 1 cup of the flour and beat until smooth.
Stir in the rest of the flour as needed to make dough that is soft, but not so soft that it is sticky.
Turn dough out onto floured board, scraping bowl clean. Knead dough for 5 to 8 minutes or until smooth and small bubbles of gas appear beneath the surface.
Allow it to sit in a warm place for approximately 15 to 30 minutes, until double in bulk. Punch down dough.
Turn out on floured pastry sheet and stretch to fit a greased pizza pan.

title: dairyman's delight
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain.
Add tomato sauce and seasoning; mix well.
Combine onion, cream cheese and sour cream in a bowl, mixing well.
Layer noodles, ground beef mixture and sour cream mixture alternately in a lightly greased baking dish. Top with desired amount of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Mix together cookie crumbs, melted butter and cinnamon; press into 8-inch spring-form pan. Refrigerate until ready to use.

title: "peaches and cream"
directions: Stir together flour, pudding and baking powder.
Combine egg, milk and butter; add to dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Spread in greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.

title: potato casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Lay in potatoes.
Mix soup, paprika, pepper and cheese.
Pour mixture over potatoes.
Cover, bake at 400° for 45 minutes, uncover and bake 10 minutes.

title: baked graham cracker crumb crust
directions: In blender make crumbs. (approx 1 1/4 c.) Pre-heat oven to 375°.
Mix crumbs, sugar, and butter and press in bottom and sides of pie pan, bake 8 min.
Cool. Ready for use.

title: cake topping
directions: Put on top of cake while cake is hot.
Place in broiler.
Cook until it bubbles and browns.
(Add cup of nuts if you like.)

title: heavenly homemade wine coolers
directions: In each of 4 glasses, pour 1/2 cup wine and 1/2 cup ginger ale.
Top with frozen peach slices, cantaloupe or honeydew balls or grapes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Sift flour, baking soda and salt.
Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, beat oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla until blended.
Stir in flour mixture.
Blend in apples and nuts.
Pour in a greased Bundt pan.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Add all ingredients together and steam for 3 1/2 hours.

title: peach and berry parfait
directions: Drain peach slices, reserving syrup. Add enough water to measure 1 cup.
Heat liquid to boiling; remove from heat.
Add gelatin and stir until dissolved.
Add ice cream by spoonfuls, stirring until melted. Chill in freezer about 10 minutes or when mixture mounds
when spooned, stirring once. Divide half of the mixture among 6 parfait glasses.
Reserve a few strawberries for garnish.
Top gelatin with remaining strawberries and peach slices. Divide remaining gelatin mixture among parfaits.
Top with strawberries.
Chill until serving time.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Note:
For use during Passover, matzo meal should be substituted for the flour.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Grate potatoes and onion into milk.
Blend in flour, egg and salt.
In skillet, heat 1-inch shortening or oil.
Drop tablespoons of batter into hot fat and brown on both sides. Drain on paper towel.
Serve with applesauce or sour cream.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Saute onions with butter.
Combine cooked broccoli, rice, cheez whiz and soup.
Put in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve 6-8.

title: chipped beef on toast
directions: Melt butter, add flour and milk.
Bring to a boil.
Add chipped beef and stir constantly.
Serve over toast.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients; cook until spins a thread when dropped from a spoon.
Remove from fire.
Add the pecan halves while still hot or warm.
Toss with fork until all nuts are coated and mixture thickens.
Pour out and quickly separate with forks. Cool and store in tins.
Can be frozen in freezer, but be sure to let them thaw to room temperature.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender and mash slightly.
Mix together with first 5 ingredients.
Top with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° in greased casserole for 40 minutes or until crumbs are browned and center is firm.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Mix margarine and wafer crumbs together.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add 1 layer sliced bananas.
Combine milk with lemon juice and spread over bananas.
Spread drained pineapple over mixture.
Spread whipped topping on top with coconut and cherries.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Combine chicken, tomatoes, soups, broth, chili powder, onion and oregano in saucepan.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Layer Doritos, chicken mix and cheese in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° until heated through.

title: chocolate pineapple frosty
directions: You sill need wooden sticks or skewers.
Drain and dry chunks of pineapple between paper towels.
String on wooden sticks or skewers 4 or 5 each.
Freeze.

title: stuffed burger bundles
directions: Prepare stuffing according to package directions.
Combine milk and meat.
Divide into 5 patties.
On wax paper, pat each patty into a 6-inch circle.
Put 1/4 cup of stuffing in center of each patty.
Bring sides of patty up, seal over stuffing.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients. Heat and pour over meat.
Bake, uncovered, 45 minutes at 350°.

title: kathryn sturtz's french dressing
directions: Mix well in mixer.
Makes 1 quart.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: chicken pie
directions: Thaw hash browns.
In bowl combine potatoes, melted butter, slat and pepper.
Press mixture in bottom and up sides of 6 ungreased 10-ounce bowls (aluminum tart pans work well).

title: tangy herbed chicken
directions: To thaw, unwrap chicken and place, breast side down, on a microwave roasting rack in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Microwave at Medium-low (30% power) for 10 minutes.
Turn chicken, breast side up; shield wing tips, tail and ends of legs with foil. Microwave chicken at Medium-low for 10 minutes, or until chicken is soft but still very cold.
Run cold water inside chicken until giblets can be removed; reserve giblets for other uses.
Rinse chicken cavity with cold water until chicken is no longer icy. Pat dry.

title: texas style sheet cake
directions: Blend all ingredients except brown sugar and nuts in large mixer bowl.*
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed of electric mixer. Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly pressed and pulls away from sides of pan.
Do not underbake.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Spoon hot Butter Glaze over warm cake.
Serve warm or cool, with prepared Dream Whip whipped topping, if desired.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine in the 9 x 13-inch pan and add graham cracker crumbs.
Press in bottom of pan to make a crust.

title: country breakfast pie
directions: Cook sausage until done.
Crumble, then drain.
Prepare 9-inch premade or from scratch pie shell.
Mix cheese and sausage; sprinkle in shell.
Lightly beat eggs in bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and eggs in bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and add eggs to mixture.
Pour in shell.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool on rack 10 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix and put in ice cream freezer.
Add milk to fill line.
Use 2 bags of ice and rock salt.

title: spinach dip
directions: Squeeze spinach until dry.
Stir together spinach, sour cream, mayonnaise, soup mix, chestnuts and onions.
Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Serve with rye or pumpernickel bread cubes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook and drain broccoli.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well (you may need to use your hands). Bake in 9 x 13-inch baking dish or large casserole dish, uncovered.
Bake about an hour, until brown.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off grease.
Add seasoning mix using only 1/2 cup water.
Pour into crock-pot and add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix completely.
Keep warm in crock-pot.	Serve with nacho chips.

title: princeton cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and lightly flour 2 round cake pans.
Cream butter and slowly add sugar, beating until light.
Add egg yolks, mandarin juice and mandarin rind and beat well.
Mix flour, cornstarch, salt and baking powder.
Stir dry mixture into butter mixture, blend until smooth.
Beat egg whites in a separate bowl until stiff, not dry.
Gently stir 1/3 of the egg whites into the first mixture, then fold in remaining whites.
Spread batter in the pans and bake for 30 to 40 minutes, or until a straw comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 5 minutes before turning out onto racks. Frost with Buttercream Icing.

title: maryland fried chicken
directions: Combine flour, poultry seasonings, salt and peppers in a bowl. Whip eggs in anothe rbowl.
Crush crackers in a third bowl.
Coat each piece of chicken in flour, then egg cracker crumbs and in flour again.
Pour oil into frying pan and heat to about 350°. Add chicken, cover and fry for 15 minutes.
Turn chicken over and pour white worcestershire over chicken, cover and cook another 10-15 minutes, or until chicken is cooked through.

title: grandmother's billy goat cookies
directions: Mix and cream margarine, sugar and egg yolks.
Mix flour, baking soda, cinnamon and cloves.
Combine with creamed ingredients.
Add vanilla, buttermilk, dates and walnuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls and bake 10 to 15 minutes at 375°.
Makes a bunch!

title: easy beef and mac whip-up
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Brown meat and drain.
Mix meat, macaroni, Miracle Whip and spaghetti sauce.
Heat on medium, stirring occasionally.
Top with cheese.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Mix
together.	Grease frying pan.
Pour
mixture
into pan. Bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: meat casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Mix all the ingredients together. Form into small balls. Use an 11-inch Corning Ware pan. Pour soup over meat balls (mix 1/2 can water with soup first). Bake for 30 minutes. Top with cheese.

title: cucumber relish
directions: Chop onions, peppers and cucumbers; sprinkle with salt and let set 1 hour.
Drain.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to cucumber mixture.
Cook at rapid boil for 20 minutes.
Put in jars and seal.

title: almond turkey with peas(yield: 4-6 servings)
directions: 1. Spread almonds in a shallow pan; toast in a 350° oven until lightly browned (about 5 minutes) and set aside.

title: frosted brownies
directions: Blend all together well and set aside.

title: freezer pickles
directions: Mix the last four ingredients together.
Stir until dissolved before pouring over the pickle mixture.
Mix well and put in jars and put in freezer.

title: cherry fudge cake
directions: Mix together by hand.
Put in greased oblong cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in 9-inch pie pan.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
This makes its own crust.

title: hawg dawgs(hors d'oeuvre)
directions: Slice hot dogs lengthwise and insert a couple of strips of onion and bell pepper.
Wrap the dog with bacon and insert about three toothpicks through the side (equally spaced) to hold parts together.
Grill on barbecue grill until bacon is done.
Slice into three pieces and place in serving bowl with barbecue sauce. Keep warm when serving.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Beat together eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until thick.
Stir in remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool on rack 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Cream margarine until soft.
Blend sugar until creamy.
Add vanilla; stir in flour and pecans.
Roll dough into small balls and place on well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Roll puffs in powdered sugar while hot and again when cold.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Saute the sliced onions in the margarine until tender.
Layer in casserole dish:
1/2 onion mixture, 1 cup grated cheese, 1/2 can soup and 1/2 stack Ritz crackers (crushed).
Repeat layers. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, or until crackers are brown.

title: spiced cider
directions: Place all ingredients except cinnamon sticks and apple slices in a large saucepan.
Heat until cider starts to bubble, but do not boil. Pour into mugs and garnish with cinnamon sticks and apple slices.
Serves 8.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Place in a greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 75 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.

title: baked fish fillet casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 425° and butter casserole dish.
Lay fillets in dish.
Sprinkle sliced onion over fish.
Lay tomato slices, alternating with zucchini, down middle of fish.
Place more tomato slices around the edges of casserole dish.
Brush fish and vegetables with remaining oil.
Bake for about 20 minutes until done.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and chopped herbs.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Brown pork chops in 1 Tbsp. vegetable oil.
Remove from pan. Stir in rice and cook until browned.
Stir in water.
Bring to a boil, stirring to remove browned bits from bottom of pan. our rice mixture in bottom of a large flat casserole dish.
Place pork chops on top of rice.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper, onion salt and garlic salt.
Bake covered.

title: stuffed cucumber slices
directions: Pare cucumber with a potato peeler and scoop out the center with a corer or small sharp knife.
Beat the cottage cheese with the parsley, chili sauce and Worcestershire sauce until well blended.
Stuff the cucumber and chill.
To serve, cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Makes about 24 slices (approximately).
One slice contains 5 calories.

title: turkey and stuffing bake
directions: You may use your own stuffing recipe or use Stove Top Stuffing.
I usually add 6 or 8 slices of bread to 1 box of Stove Top.
Mix in a separate bowl; set aside.

title: chicken dijon parmesan
directions: Place single pieces on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve with wild rice (Uncle Ben's) with added cooked wild rice and slivered almonds.

title: perfectly easy dinner rolls
directions: Combine the warm water and yeast in a large bowl.
Let the mixture stand until yeast is foamy, about 5 minutes.
Stir in butter, sugar, eggs and salt.
Beat in flour, 1 cup at a time until dough is too stiff to mix (some flour may not be needed).
Cover and refrigerate two hours or up to 4 days.

title: texas hash
directions: Cook hamburger until crumbly.
Add onions and green pepper. Cook until pepper is tender.
Stir in tomatoes, rice, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover last 15 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate-covered cherries
directions: Mix oleo.
Add milk and vanilla; mix.
Add powdered sugar. Knead and roll into small balls.
Make a hollow indention with thumb.
Place cherry in the indentation; push dough up over cherry and roll into ball again.
Use a toothpick to dip each ball into melted chocolate.

title: helen's chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together except the flour.
Add flour after all is mixed well.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie crusts. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
If you refrigerate, the chocolate chips will be crunchy.
If you don't the chips will be soft.
Good either way.

title: microwave santa fe scrambled eggs
directions: Beat the eggs and spices together in a medium bowl. Stir in green pepper, onions and tomato.

Microwave mixture on High for 3 1/2 to 5 minutes or until the eggs are soft-set, stirring 2 to 3 times during cooking. Sprinkle eggs with Monterey Jack cheese. Cover and let eggs stand for 1 to 2 minutes or until the cheese melts. Makes 4 servings.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers and onions (usually a 3 to 1 ratio) and place in gallon jar.
Mix other ingredients and pour over top.
Cover and place in refrigerator.
Stir or shake occasionally.

title: griddle cakes
directions: Mix together. Will be lumpy. Fry on lightly greased griddle. Serve with maple syrup or jelly.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake yellow cake mix according to directions in a 13 x 9-inch sheet cake pan.
While cake is still warm, use a wooden spoon handle and poke holes across top of cake.
Mix cream of coconut and Eagle Brand milk together and pour over cake.
After cake has cooled and absorbed mixture, mix the vanilla pudding and milk. Beat until thick.
Spread over cake and refrigerate overnight. Spread Cool Whip over cake and sprinkle with toasted coconut.

title: florentine appetizer puffs
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a baking sheet.
Cook and drain spinach.
Add cheese and onion.
Blend in eggs.
Stir in croutons and butter.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Bake 15 minutes 1/2 inch apart.
Makes 36.
Can freeze for 1 week.
Don't thaw.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: sinful dessert
directions: Mix together and spread over butterscotch pudding.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle top with chopped nuts.

title: frozen fruit cup
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into muffin cups. Freeze until firm. Store in plastic bag.

title: dutch baby
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Place oleo in iron skillet and slide it into the oven.
Leave in oven until oleo melts.
In mixing bowl, combine flour, eggs and milk.
Beat until blended.
Pour batter into hot skillet (do not stir oleo).
Return to oven; bake 15 minutes.
Remove and sprinkle with powdered sugar and cinnamon. Return to oven for 3 minutes.
Serve with syrup.

title: french pistachio ice cream (uncooked)
directions: With an electric mixer, beat eggs in mixing bowl until fluffy. Add all remaining ingredients, except nuts, and continue beating until sugar and pistachio pudding dissolve.
Pour mixture into cream can.
Freeze as directed.
Fold nuts into mixture after processing but before
hardening.

title: egg nog
directions: Make a paste with a little milk.
Gradually add the remaining ingredients.
Chill overnight or all day.

title: chili cheese snacks
directions: Grate cheeses.
Place in buttered casserole.
Place green chilies over cheese.
Pour beaten eggs over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop onions and green peppers.
Mix together all ingredients in bowl and mix well.
Shape into meat loaf.
Place in a greased loaf pan.
Bake uncovered for 1 hour.

title: buffalo wings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dip chicken in mixture of butter, pepper sauce and vinegar.
Put in baking pan.
Sprinkle with one package of dry dressing mix.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with celery sticks and the other package prepared dressing mix.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Bring to a boil the oleo, water and cocoa.;
Mix into a large mixing bowl the sugar, flour, baking soda, salt and vanilla.
Add the eggs and sour cream.
Pour on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, nuts, baking soda, cinnamon, salt, nutmeg and baking powder. Set aside.
Beat eggs until frothy.
Add oil, sugar and vanilla, beat until foamy.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour into pans.
Bake for 1 hour (60 minutes).
Cool 10 minutes then remove from pans.

title: tenderized steak
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour and mustard.
Cut steak into serving size pieces.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper and cover with flour mixture.
Brown in hot oil.
Transfer into 8 x 8-inch dish. Combine remaining ingredients and pour over meat.
Cover and bake 2 hours or until very tender.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, then eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Sift dry ingredients together; add alternately with mix to butter and nuts.
Add vanilla.
Bake in a 10-inch tube pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: birthday cake
directions: Sift flour, baking soda, salt, and sugar; set aside. Cream margarine and blend in lemon rind. Add flour mixture, buttermilk, and vanilla; mix until flour is damp, then beat for 2 minutes at medium speed. Add eggs and beat 1 minute longer. Pour into two 9 inch cake pans that have been greased and floured. Bake in preheated oven for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chinese salad
directions: Saute butter, sesame seed, almonds and noodles until light brown.
Bring to boil sugar, oil, vinegar and soy sauce for 1 minute.
Let cool.
Just before serving, mix noodle mixture with lettuce and onions.
Pour dressing over lettuce; toss lightly.

title: cheese potato casserole
directions: Mix these ingredients in a casserole dish and heat in a slow oven (325°) for one hour or until golden brown.
Serves 12 to 16 people.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Cut peppers from top.
Remove carefully all the seeds and tongue.
Cut thin slice from bottom so peppers will stand.
Melt butter.
Add flour and seasoning, then the milk and onion juice; add meat and fill peppers with mixture.
Cover with crumbs made by stirring 2/3 cup bread crumbs into 2/3 tablespoon of melted butter.
Place the pepper in a baking pan and cover the bottom with boiling water.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mildred's fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and fruit cocktail.
After pineapple and fruit cocktail has been drained, mix all ingredients together and refrigerate.

title: liver and bacon patties
directions: Pour boiling water over liver in pan.
Simmer gently 5 minutes.
Remove liver and cool slightly; grind liver and onion together.
Mix with remaining ingredients except bacon.
Shape into 4 patties; wrap each with a slice of bacon.
Broil 3 to 4 inches from broiling unit until bacon is crisp and brown, 3 to 5 minutes on each side.

title: upside-down hamburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Brown meat in oil; drain.
Add onion, celery and green pepper; cook over medium heat for 5 minutes. Stir in tomato sauce, salt, pepper and Worcestershire.
Make biscuit dough (add parsley and celery seed to flour if desired). Roll; make into biscuits or 1 eight-inch circle.
Place on hot meat.
Bake 15 minutes.
Remove from oven; let stand 5 minutes. Invert over hot serving plate.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat eggs very well, add sugar, then alternate flour, oil and vanilla.
Place in cold pan, ungreased.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: yogurt yumsicles
directions: Simply combine all ingredients.
Children can mix these up themselves.
If using whole fruit, puree everything in a blender or food processor.
(Gelatin in the mixture retards melting on a hot day.
Soften it in water and heat slightly to dissolve.
Blend into yogurt mixture.)

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together and add rest of ingredients and beat and pour into unbaked pie crusts.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes and then 350° until knife comes out clean.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine over medium heat until it starts to boil.
Add everything else.
Remove from heat; cool 1 minute.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: orange cake
directions: Cream the first 3 ingredients together, then add the rest. Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until done.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and Cool Whip together.
Cut cake into 2 layers.
Add filling, then blueberry filling.
Top with cake, then filling, then blueberry filling.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Chill in refrigerator until served.

title: christmas rock cookies
directions: Mix together all ingredients and drop by teaspoon on buttered cookie sheet.
Bake at 335° for 15 minutes.

title: lillie's pina colada pie
directions: Mix thawed pina colada mix with lemon juice and Eagle Brand mix.
Add thoroughly drained, crushed pineapple.
Blend in Cool Whip.
Pour in pie crust.
Allow to set until firm in refrigerator.
Garnish, if desired.
Very rich.

title: slush mixer
directions: Thoroughly mix all ingredients, place in an ice cream or any large container and place in the freezer.
Mix will get slushy instead of freezing.
To use add 3/4 cup of slush mix with 1/4 cup of soda (7-up, sprite, etc) or 1/4 cup liquor (rum, tequila, etc.).

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Drain.
Season with onion powder. Drain peas and carrots.
Place in a casserole dish in this order: hamburger meat, peas and carrots, cream of celery soup and then Tater Tots.
Sprinkle with salt.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: ice cream roll
directions: Separate egg whites from yolks and set yolks aside.
Beat egg whites, cream of tartar and salt until stiff, then add 1/2 cup sugar and mix well.

title: chocolate whipped cream
directions: Combine powdered sugar and cocoa in small bowl.
Add cream and vanilla; beat until stiff.

title: egg-sausage casserole
directions: Fry sausage meat in pan.
(Drain grease.)
Beat eggs, milk and salt.
Stir in cheese and pour over sausage that has been pressed into bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle box of croutons over the top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Bake, uncovered.

title: hamburger onion pie
directions: Prepare biscuit mix according to directions on package.
Roll into a circle to fit a 9-inch pie pan.
Saute sliced onions and hamburger until meat loses its red color.
Add salt, pepper and m.s.g.
Spread on the dough in a pie tin.
Beat eggs lightly and mix with cottage cheese.
Pour over meat and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: banana yogurt pecan bread
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients in a medium bowl.
Stir well.
Combine eggs, bananas and yogurt; stir well.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture alternately with banana mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix until blended after each addition.
Stir in pecans.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt; add alternately with buttermilk.
Add extracts and flavoring.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Brush part of glaze on cake when it comes from the oven. Invert on serving plate and brush remaining glaze all over cake.

title: eggplant casserole(moussaka)
directions: Brown the onions and hamburger in half of the butter.
Add parsley, tomatoes, wine, salt and pepper to taste and cook on low flame until liquid is absorbed.
Set aside to cool, then add eggs, cheese and 3 tablespoons bread crumbs.
Mix well; season to taste. While this is being prepared, slice eggplants lengthwise.
Fry each in butter, browning each side.
Sprinkle the bottom of a 9 x 12-inch pan with bread crumbs, then place a layer of eggplants over this.
Cover with meat mixture, then add another layer of eggplants and meat again, until all is used, ending with eggplant. Top with "Krema" sauce.
Bake in oven at 375° to 400° for one hour.

title: quick apple crisp
directions: Place apple pie filling in an 8 x 8-inch microwavable baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients in a bowl until crumbly.
Pour over filling.
Cover with wax paper and cook until mixture is melted and apples are hot, about 3 to 4 minutes.
Uncover and let stand until warm.
Serve with ice cream.

title: crab cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together and refrigerate for 1/2 hour.

title: mississippi mud bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add cocoa, eggs and vanilla.
Slowly mix in flour, coconut and nuts.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Spread immediately with marshmallow cream.
Cool completely.
Frost with:

title: onion potato pancakes
directions: In a blender or food processor, place eggs, onion, flour, salt, pepper, baking powder and 1/2 cup of potatoes.
Cover and process on high until smooth.
Add parsley and remaining potatoes.
Cover and pulse 2 to 4 times until potatoes are chopped.
Pour 1 to 2 tablespoons oil onto a hot griddle or skillet.
Pour batter by 1/3 cups onto griddle.
Flatten slightly to 4 to 5-inch diameter.
Cook over medium heat until golden on both sides.
Add oil as needed until all pancakes are cooked.
Makes 6 to 8 servings (12 pancakes).
Good with applesauce.

title: spice tea
directions: Boil about 15 minutes.	Add water to make 5 quarts.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in bowl.
Stir in egg whites and almond extract; mix well.
Drop from teaspoon onto lightly greased baking sheets.
Add cherry halves.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or until edges are golden.
Remove from sheets immediately.
Makes about 1 1/2 dozen.

title: summer squash medley
directions: Prepare ingredients.
Place in large bowl and mix well.
Spoon into heavy-duty foil.
Wrap up foil completely on all sides so liquid does not escape from bottom or sides.
Cook on low heat on barbecue grill for about 30 minutes, checking liquid content occasionally.
Add water to keep bottom from burning.
Be careful of steam build up.
Serves 4.

title: breakfast muffins
directions: Beat the egg, milk, oil and sugar in a bowl.
When mixed well, add the flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir until moistened.
Put cupcake paper liners into cupcake baking pan.
Makes 10 to 12 cupcakes.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: red beet chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar and eggs.
Add salad oil, blended with beets and melted chocolate.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Blend well; add vanilla.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) layers or 1 (13 x 9 x 2-inch) pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: a good neighbor recipe
directions: Blend together the above ingredients.
Form into one being. Serve generous portions to everyone you meet daily.

title: venus de milo soup
directions: Brown hamburg and drain grease.
Add water, chicken broth, celery, mushrooms and onion soup mix; boil for 20 minutes.
Add frozen vegetables and stewed tomatoes; boil for another 15 minutes.
Add orzo or pasta; boil 5 more minutes.

title: pork chops and peas
directions: Combine all ingredients in casserole.
Cover and cook at 350° for 1 hour or until pork chops are tender.

title: sauteed chicken baked in cream and mushrooms
directions: Clean and cut into pieces 2 to 2 1/2 pound frying chicken.
Dip in milk.
Dredge with flour.
Season with salt and paprika.
Melt in a skillet 1/2 cup lard or bacon drippings.
Add chicken.
Saute it until brown.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Slice 1/2 pound mushrooms.
Saute mushrooms in skillet for 2 minutes.
Place chicken in a deep baking dish.
Place mushrooms on top.
Pour over it 2 cups hot cream.
Season with 1/4 teaspoon salt and 1/4 teaspoon paprika.
Bake chicken at 325° until tender and cream is a thick sauce (about 1/2 hour).
Good served over rice.

title: fettuccine with veggies and ham(serves 7)
directions: Cook fettuccine according to package, omitting salt and fat. Meanwhile, bring water to boil, add vegetables, and cook uncovered 3 minutes or until tender crisp.
Drain; set aside.
Place milk in small saucepan, cook over low heat until warm.
Add warm milk and cheese to cooked and drained fettuccine.
Stir until thoroughly heated.
Stir in vegetables, ham and pepper.
Serve warm.

title: sausage rounds
directions: Brown sausage and turkey in a large pot and drain well.
Cut cheese into chunks and add to the meat.
Heat over low heat and melt cheese.
Place bread slices on cookie sheets.
Spoon mixture onto each slice.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes, until cheese is melted and bread is crisp.
Mixture can be made ahead of time and microwaved to spoon on bread.

title: pineapple spread for sandwiches
directions: Drain the pineapple.
Combine juice, eggs, sugar and flour. Cook until thick.
Cool.
Add mayonnaise and stir into pineapple.

title: english triffle
directions: Bake cake as directed on box.
Cool.
Mix the boxes of pudding as directed on box.

title: self-rising biscuits
directions: Cut shortening into flour (or mix well with your hands).
Add enough milk mixture to moisten.
Roll out dough on floured surface and cut with a biscuit cutter or roll with floured hands.
Bake on an ungreased baking sheet for 12 to 15 minutes at 450°.

title: millionaire's pie
directions: Mix all together and put into crust.
Chill in refrigerator for 1 hour.

title: cheese spread
directions: Combine cheese and milk in double boiler.
Stir until melted. Remove from heat.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Store in refrigerator.
Makes 5 (4-ounce) jars.
Keeps several weeks.

title: potato doughnuts
directions: Beat together potatoes and sugar.
Beat in buttermilk, salt and eggs.
Sift nutmeg, flour and baking soda together and stir into potato mix to make a soft dough.
Roll out on floured board and cut with doughnut cutter.
Or mold into small "meatballs" to make bite-sized "munchkins".
Fry until golden.
Drain on paper towels. Sprinkle with sugar.
Serve warm if possible.
Makes approximately 3 dozen.

title: jiffy banana pudding recipes
directions: Prepare vanilla custard pudding as directed on box.
When this is ready, line the bottom and sides of a deep dish with a thick layer of vanilla wafer (not crumbled).

Next, place alternately layers of bananas, vanilla wafers that have been crumbled and vanilla custard pudding in the dish, making sure that the top layer is a generous one of the crumbled vanilla wafers (number of layers depending on quantity desired).

title: company chicken casserole
directions: Combine chicken, mushroom and celery soup.
Mix together well. Divide mixture in
half
and
spread
each
half
in bottom of a greased 8 x 8-inch
pan
or
all
of
mixture in a large baking dish.
Melt margarine and pour into broth.
Blend and add onion, celery
and
poultry
seasoning.
Bring to boil and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add
cornbread
mixture to liquid mixture and mix well. Spread on top of chicken mixture in pan or dish.
Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender and combine thoroughly. Grease and flour a 10-inch pie pan.
Pour mixture into pan or Pyrex dish and bake in a preheated oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
"Pie" will make its own crust as it cooks.
Serve at room temperature.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburg and onion.
Cook rotini and drain.
In a cake pan, layer hamburg, rotini, spaghetti sauce, cheese and pepperoni.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy potato salad
directions: Mix together mayonnaise, sour cream, salt, mustard, onion and pepper.
Stir in potatoes, eggs and celery.
Chill at least one hour (even overnight) before serving.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine cream cheese with mayonnaise until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients.
Chill.
Serve with your favorite crackers. Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: hot potato salad(or german potato salad)
directions: Cook potatoes in salted water until just tender.
Peel and cut into slices, about 1/4-inch thick.
Fry bacon and onion until tender.
Combine flour, salt, celery seed and sugar in small bowl; add water and vinegar.
Stir slowly into bacon-onion mixture; cook on low heat until mixture boils and is thick and smooth.
Add potatoes and parsley; stir gently.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: raw vegetable salad
directions: Chop broccoli, cauliflower and onion.
Mix mayo, vinegar, sugar and salt. Pour over the veggies; mix well. Refrigerate. Better after chilling 3 to 4 hours. Keeps well.

title: chili
directions: Cook spaghetti until done and drain.
Brown hamburger in skillet and drain.
Add all ingredients together and cook on low approximately 30 to 45 minutes.

title: canned apples
directions: To keep apples/fruit from turning dark after peeling, place them in the salt and vinegar water as you cut them up.

title: curried fruit
directions: Drain fruit and dry well.
Arrange in buttered dish and dot with maraschino cherries.
Melt the butter with the brown sugar and while boiling, add the curry powder.
Drizzle over the fruit. Cover with foil and bake 1 hour at 350°. Next day, heat 1/2 hour before serving.

title: apple coconut cake
directions: Combine flour, soda and salt.
Mix well and set aside. Combine oil, eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer for 2 minutes.
Add flour mixture; mix at low speed just until blended.
Fold in pecans, apples and coconut.
(Batter will be stiff.)
Spoon into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately. Drizzle glaze over cake.

title: five layer salad
directions: Tear lettuce into bite size pieces followed by bite size pieces of cauliflower. Add green onion, then the bacon crushed into small pieces.
In another bowl, mix the Miracle Whip, sugar and Parmesan cheese together.
When ready to serve, pour dressing over salad and mix well.

title: punch
directions: This has done for a lot of weddings, showers and parties.

title: shrimp creole
directions: In a 10-inch skillet saute onion, green pepper, celery and garlic in butter for 6 to 8 minutes until limp.
Stir in flour. Stir in rosemary and thyme, tomatoes and juice, water, tomato paste, bay leaf and hot pepper sauce.
Stirring, bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer, stirring occasionally for 15 minutes.
Remove bay leaf and discard.

title: german potato salad
directions: Place bacon in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes until crisp.
Remove bacon.
Crumble and set aside. Add onion to bacon drippings.
Microwave 2 to 3 minutes on High or until onion is transparent.
Stir in flour, sugar, salt, pepper and celery seed.
Microwave on High 1 minute.
Stir in water and vinegar.
Microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes or until the mixture boils.
Add the potatoes and bacon, stirring evenly to coat with sauce.
Salad may be prepared in advance.
Microwave 2 to 3 minutes on High or until potatoes are heated through.
Excellent served warm or cooled.

title: easy turtles
directions: Preheat oven to 200°.
On cookie sheet, arrange rows of pecans in three's.
Put half a caramel candy on pecans.
Melt chocolate. Put cookie sheet with pecans and caramels in oven.
Melt caramels; remove from oven.
Pour melted chocolate over caramels on pecans. Let cool.

title: hot sausage cheese dip
directions: Brown meat.
Drain.
Combine cheese, soup, tomatoes and milk in crock-pot or slow cooker.
Cook until melted.
Stir occasionally to prevent cheese burning.
Add picante sauce.

title: holiday punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
A frozen ring mold may be used to garnish and keep cold while serving.
Serves 15 to 18.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Brown meat, onions and garlic in iron skillet.
Place in crock-pot with remaining ingredients, except beans.
Cook on low setting for 8 to 10 hours.
Add beans during the last hour.

title: peanut butter snack cups
directions: Place wafers in paper or foil-lined muffin cups.
Top each with 1 tablespoon whipped topping.
In a mixing bowl, combine milk and peanut butter; add pudding mix.
With an electric mixer, beat on low speed for 2 minutes.
Fold in remaining whipped topping. Spoon into prepared muffin cups.
Cover and freeze.
Remove from freezer 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 12 servings.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Combine in order:
sugar, butter, egg, soda, soup, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, flour, baking powder, salt, raisins and nuts. Bake at 350° in an 8-inch or 9-inch square pan for about 35 minutes.

title: mulligatawny soup
directions: Saute onion, carrot and celery in butter; do not brown.
Stir in flour and curry powder; cook for about 3 minutes.
Add chicken broth and simmer for 30 minutes.
Add apples, rice, chicken and seasonings; simmer for 15 minutes longer.
Just before serving, add hot cream and stir.

title: "spaghetti and bacon"
directions: In skillet, brown bacon and onion until crisp.
Add tomatoes and tomato sauce; bring to a boil.
Place cooked spaghetti in 2-quart baking dish.
Pour sauce over.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: cheeseburger quiche
directions: Microwave ground beef and onion on High for 3 minutes, stirring half way through; drain well.
In medium mixing bowl, beat milk, mayonnaise and seasoning.
Stir in eggs.
Add 1 cup cheese, ground beef and onion mixture to bowl.
Pour into baked pie shell that is in a glass pie plate.
Microwave for 6 minutes on High or 7 minutes on Medium, rotating 1/4 turn every 3 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Microwave 3 more minutes on High or 6 minutes on Medium or until knife inserted halfway between center and side comes out clean.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Put the water in the pot. Then melt the cheese on the noodles. Then put the noodles in the pot that has the boiling water in it. Then pour the water out of it.
Let it cook for 10 minutes. Then when it is ready, you eat it.

title: blueberry tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until well blended.
Beat egg yolks and add.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour 1/2 of batter into greased rectangular pan.
Cover with floured blueberries and then remaining batter. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar while still warm.

title: chocolate dipped strawberries
directions: Melt chocolate slowly over hot water.
Dip washed and dried whole strawberries in chocolate.
Place on waxed paper and refrigerate to harden.

title: sweet and sour kielbasa
directions: Cut kielbasa in 1/4-inch slices.
Put in crock-pot with jars of chili sauce and grape jelly.
Simmer on low for 2 hours.
Stir often.

title: wedding punch
directions: First, use care in selection.
Get one that is not too young, but tender and healthy.
If you choose one recklessly it may not keep.
Do not put in hot water!
This makes them sour quickly. Sweeten with smiles and spice with patience.
All varieties will respond.

title: 20 minute spagetti sauce
directions: Stir ingredients, cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Makes four cups.
Add browned and drained ground beef or canned mushrooms for varity.

title: peanut butter and jelly smoothie
directions: In a blender combine milk, jelly, peanut butter, banana, honey and wheat germ. Blend until smooth.

title: hawaiian fruit pie
directions: Make crust according to directions on box.
Slice bananas in a layer over crust.
Mix milk, lemon juice and sugar and beat until thickened.
Pour over bananas.
Sprinkle pineapple over filling. Mix Dream Whip according to directions.
Spread over pie. Sprinkle nuts, coconut and cherries on top.
Refrigerate.

title: fantasy freeze pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and Fluff at medium speed with mixer until well blended.
Add sherbet and mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into crust.
Freeze until firm.
Garnish with Cool Whip and berries.

title: wedding bell punch
directions: Combine juice and water and keep cold.
When ready to use, add ice.
Garnish with oranges, maraschino cherries or pineapple slices.
Serves 50 (4 ounce servings).

title: no roll pie crust
directions: Put flour, salt and sugar in pie pan.
Mix milk with cooking oil and pour over flour.
Mix with fork.
Pat out as thin as desired for crust with hands.
Bake at 375° until brown if recipe calls for already baked crust.

title: lentil soup
directions: Soak lentils overnight.
Drain and rinse.
Combine lentils, stock and ham bone in large pot.
Simmer 1 hour.
Fry bacon; drain and crumble.
Cook carrots, green pepper and onions in bacon fat until soft; add to soup with tomatoes, salt, pepper and vinegar. Simmer 2 hours.
Remove bone.
Top soup with crumbled bacon.
(I usually eat this before the soup is done!)

title: shrimp appetizer
directions: Spread cream cheese on a platter.
Pour shrimp sauce over cream cheese.
Add shrimp over the top.
Serve with cracker of choice.

title: lamb kebobs
directions: Marinate lamb chunks in rest of ingredients for four hours or more. Skewer chunks onto bamboo skewers and bake over charcoal for 15 minutes.

title: jack's jello cream freeze
directions: Mix gelatin in boiling water (1 cup per 3 ounce package). Stir completely until dissolved (about 3 minutes).
Scoop in vanilla ice cream and stir mixture until diluted and creamy looking.
Pour mixture into individual containers or serving bowls.
Freeze about 1/2 hour, then place in the refrigerator for at least 2 hours; serve.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Bring pineapple to a boil.
Stir in jello until dissolved. Remove from heat and stir in buttermilk.
Cool to room temperature.
Fold in cool whip.
Pour into 2 quart mold or bowl and chill.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Use 2 1/2-quart casserole dish and place in dish in order. Mix.
Add 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Bake 2 to 2 1/2 hours at 350°, uncovered.
Stir often.
Serve with a green salad; great!

title: texas pecan pie
directions: Combine butter, corn syrup, salt and vanilla in a medium mixing bowl.
Beat well.
Add eggs; beat until thoroughly blended. Stir in pecans.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: dutch lettuce
directions: Take lettuce apart; wash, drain and dry with a towel.
Slice onion.
Cut bacon into small pieces and fry.
Remove bacon bits. Pour off all but 3 tablespoons of bacon drippings.
While still hot, add salt, pepper, sugar and vinegar.
Stir; add flour and stir well.
Pour dressing over lettuce.
Add bacon bits.

title: chicken salad
directions: Chop chicken, celery, and grapes. Add pecans, and enough Miracle Whip to moisten good.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Combine all ingredients except Cheddar and spread into 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle Cheddar on top. Cook at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves about 6.

title: "plain special" cheese ring
directions: Mix; mold with hands into desired shape (I mold into a ring). Place in refrigerator until chilled.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls on baking sheet.
Don't tear apart.
Bake as directed on package.
While your bread is cooking, mix together cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix.
Spread on baked bread. Wash and cut up vegetables in bite-size pieces and place on top. Sprinkle with cheese.

title: oatmeal pie
directions: Mix together and put into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: beef noodles with cheese
directions: Saute in 3 tablespoons butter, pepper and onion.
Add to cheese mixture that has been mixed well.
Brown ground beef; add tomato sauce.
Cook noodles.
Layer noodles, spread with cheese mixture; repeat.
Cover with meat.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: beef porcupines
directions: Mix beef, rice, onion, salt and pepper.
Form into balls and fry in hot oil, turning frequently until lightly browned.
Add tomato sauce and water; stir well.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese casserole
directions: Brown ground meat in frying pan until browned well. Cook macaroni according to package. Drain macaroni. Add package of cheese.
Stir until well coated.
Pour cooked ground meat and macaroni and cheese into large casserole bowl. Add tomato sauce and mix well. Top with 3 to 4 slices of American cheese.
Place in oven at 350°, uncovered, for 1/2 hour.

title: sauerkraut sausage casserole
directions: Place the ingredients in a 2-quart casserole and fill with water.
Bake 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 325°.

title: oven fries
directions: Scrub potatoes thoroughly. Cut each potato length-wise into 8 slices. Brush cut surface lightly with melted oleo. In a plastic bag combine parmesan cheese, garlic salt, paprika and onion powder. Add 8 potato slices. shake to coat. Potatoes will not be completely coated. Spray a 11 X 17 baking pan with nonstick spray. Arrange potatoes in baking pan. Repeat until all potatoes are coated. Bake uncovered in a 400 degrees oven 25-30 minutes.

title: carrot pecan cake
directions: Combine oil and sugar; mix well. Sift together remaining dry ingredients. Sift half of dry ingredients into sugar mixture; blend. Sift in remaining dry ingredients alternately with eggs, one at a time, mixing well after each addition. Add carrots and mix well, then mix in pecans. Pour into lightly oiled 10-inch tube pan. Bake in slow oven (325°) about 1 hour and 10 minutes. Cool in pan upright. Remove from pan and frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: mother's hearty meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl combine the catsup, brown sugar and dry mustard; stir to mix.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Shape into a loaf in a large shallow baking pan.
Bake one hour.
Recipe can be doubled and also freezes very well.

title: finnish pancakes(but they're actually swedish; international)
directions: Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Prepare spinach per package directions. Drain.
Mix rest of ingredients together.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.
Great with Ruffles and vegetables.

title: fruit dip
directions: Stirring all the time, blend flour, sugar and juice. Add egg, cream cheese and butter and heat until all is melted. (Do not boil.) Cool and add Cool Whip. Whip this together with a wire whisk.

title: new york style hot wings
directions: Add garlic and Worcestershire to plain hot sauce and heat a little bit, then add the melted margarine and shake together.
Deep fry some chicken wings.
When done put them into the hot sauce mixture and shake together.
Serve this with Blue cheese dressing and celery.
This could be served as appetizer.

title: chocolate potato cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Sift dry ingredients 3 times. Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture. Alternate with milk. Add nuts and raisins after you have mixed them with the mashed potatoes and melted chocolate. Blend well. Grease 2 lined 8 x 8-inch pans with butter and flour lightly. Bake for 35 minutes in 350° oven.

title: veggie salad-dieters delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Chill and serve.

title: harvest bread
directions: Combine sugar, oil, eggs and pumpkin.
Sift dry ingredients. Add with oats and nuts to creamed mixture.
Pour into a greased 9 x 5-inch
pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: angel biscuits
directions: In a saucepan, combine buttermilk and shortening.
Heat until shortening melts.
Cool to lukewarm. Set aside.
In a bowl, combine all dry ingredients, except yeast.
Dissolve yeast in water. Stir into buttermilk. Add to dry ingredients.
Mix well (it will be sticky).
Roll out and cut with cutter.
Let rise for 1 hour or after mixing all ingredients, you can refrigerate (for 5 days) until ready to use.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or longer, if not done.

title: punch
directions: Mix the orange juice, pineapple juice and cranberry juice. Add ginger ale and ice ring before serving. Garnish with orange slices.

title: maple veal medallions
directions: Place first 3 ingredients in a frying pan and simmer until the veal is tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer another 5 minutes.
Serve over noodles or rice.

title: corn oysters(ca 1940's)
directions: Beat the egg yolks and whites separately and add to the corn with flour, fat, salt and pepper.
Drop the batter from a spoon into hot fat (360°) and fry until light brown (2 to 3 minutes). Drain on paper bag.
Serve hot.
(Can be popped into the microwave to warm if you would like to make them ahead.)

title: green beans with cashews
directions: Trim ends off beans.
Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil.
Add beans.
Bring water back to a boil and slowly boil the beans, uncovered, for 8 to 12 minutes or until tender but still crunchy and firm.
Immediately pour into colander and run under cold water for 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove to paper towels and dry. (May be refrigerated covered overnight.)
Before serving, bring to room temperature.
Melt butter or margarine in a large skillet or wok.
Add beans, lemon juice and cashews.
Cook over moderately high heat, stirring and tossing gently until heated through. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Serves 10.

title: cream of vegetable soup
directions: In a large boiler, saute onion in butter until tender.
Add flour.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Gradually add broth.
Cook and stir until thickened, about 5 minutes.
Stir in the milk, cream, basil, salt and garlic powder.
Add the vegetables.
Cook gently until heated through.
Makes about 3-quarts.

title: candied beets
directions: Mix sugar, flour and spices together.
Cook awhile with beet juice to thicken.
Then add beets until warm.

title: chewy dunking snaps
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, egg and syrup together.
Mix rest of ingredients together and add to creamed mixture.
Shape into 1-inch balls; roll in sugar.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet in a 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Combine first eight ingredients, adding sour cream alternately with dry.
Pour 1/2 mixture into a prepared Bundt pan.
Sprinkle combined brown sugar, cinnamon and nuts over cake filling.
Pour remaining filling over the brown sugar mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream the sugar, applesauce, Crisco and eggs.
Add dry ingredients, mixing well. Fold in your fruits and baking soda. Bake in a 350° oven for 60 minutes, using a 10-inch tube pan. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: zucchini and tomato sauce
directions: Clean and cut zucchini into 1/4-inch rounds.
In frying pan, heat vegetable oil and brown garlic.
Pour in tomato sauce and zucchini, reduce heat to low and let simmer.
Serve over pasta or rice.

title: strawberry muffins
directions: In bowl, stir together the flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Make a well in the center.
Combine eggs, oil and buttermilk; pour into well.
Stir just until moistened.
Do not overmix.
Gently fold in jam.
Place in well-greased or paper lined muffin tins.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: chole(a spicy food)
directions: Cut tomatoes and onions into big pieces.
Crush tomatoes and onions in blender together.
Heat butter in a pot.
Put crushed tomatoes-onion mixture into pot and add water.
Cook 2 minutes. Add ginger, lemon juice and channa masala; cook 3 minutes.
Add chickpeas and salt to taste.
Add garam masala and cook for 5 minutes.
Decorate with tomatoes, green chilies and coriander. Serve hot with middle eastern bread.

title: peanut patties
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients together.
Bring to a hard ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Stir in powdered sugar, butter and red food coloring.
Stir and drop on foil.

title: coconut cream jello
directions: Crust:
Mix together flour, butter and walnuts.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 15 minutes at 300°.
Let cool.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time and mix well until blended.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk and vanilla.
Add blueberries and fold in by hand.
Using cupcake liners, pile mix 3/4 full into each muffin cup.
Sprinkle sugar over top.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Saute onion in oil until soft.
Add milk, flour, cloves and bay leaves.
Cook over medium-low heat until thick and creamy. Add turkey with salt and pepper to taste.
(Fry turkey before adding.)
Serve over spaghetti.
Serves 3 to 4 people.

title: hot dogs in sauce
directions: Heat jelly to liquid.
Stir in mustard.
Simmer until all is mixed well.
If using hot dogs, cut into 1-inch pieces and add to sauce.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
May use cocktail wieners, whole, in sauce.

title: country fresh broccoli
directions: Combine broccoli, cheese, bacon and onion.
Toss together and then set aside.
In small bowl, mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar. Blend into broccoli mixture until evenly coated.
Garnish with more cheese and bacon, if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
From Mary Ralston's recipe collection.

title: butterscotch pie
directions: Mix all ingredients, except egg yolk, butter and vanilla. Bring to a boil.
Add yolks mixed with 1/2 cup or more of pudding. Cook until thick.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites and 1/2 cup sugar slowly.
Place on pie and bake until done.

title: easy chicken and broccoli
directions: In 10-inch skillet, heat margarine over medium heat until bubbly and hot.
Add chicken and cook, turning when necessary, until lightly browned, 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove from skillet and set aside.
To same skillet, add broccoli, garlic and ginger; saute for 1 minute.
In a bowl, combine broth and cornstarch. Stir until cornstarch is dissolved.
Add to broccoli mixture and return chicken to skillet.
Reduce heat to low; add pepper and cook, stirring occasionally, until sauce is thickened, 5 to 10 minutes.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding and nuts.
Beat eggs well; add oil and beat 4 minutes.
Mix dry ingredients into egg mixture.
Pour into greased tube pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix ingredients, adding Jiffy mix last.
Bake in lightly greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 400° for about 25 minutes.

title: no peek chicken and rice casserole
directions: Place rice in bottom of glass baking dish.
Lay chicken on top.
Pour soup and water mix over top.
Sprinkle with Lipton dry soup.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chimi-cheese dogs
directions: Soften tortillas for 45 seconds in microwave.
Place 1 slice of cheese, 1 hot dog and 1 heaping tablespoon of chili on side of a tortilla nearest you.
Roll away from you approximately 2/3 the width of the tortilla.
Fold the ends in and roll the rest of the way.
Fry in enough oil to cover 1/2 of the burrito.
Fry, flap side down, first to avoid burrito opening up.
Fry on both sides until golden brown.
Yields 10 chimis.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Put all juices into a 9 cup percolator.
Place spices and brown sugar into basket.
Bring to a boil and percolate for 10 minutes at simmer position.
Remove spices before serving.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain beans, put in deep serving bowl.
Dissolve sugar in small bowl with Italian dressing.
Pour over beans and chill overnight.

title: mother's banana pudding
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in top of double boiler or heavy pot (to keep from sticking or burning).
Beat egg yolks and gradually stir in egg yolks in hot mixture.
Add vanilla at end. Cook until thick, about 15 minutes.

title: chocolate layer dessert
directions: First Layer:
Mix well flour, pecans and margarine.
Spread and press in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake until brown.
Let cool completely.

title: "italian" eggplant parmesan
directions: Spray eggplant slices lightly with olive oil cooking spray and place on nonstick baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 400°. Combine sauce, onion, pepper, mushrooms and seasonings.
Mix well. In a casserole dish, place 1/2 of eggplant slices.
Pour half of tomato mixture over eggplant slices.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of cheese mixture.
Repeat these layers.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, 45 minutes.
Makes 2 servings with 250 calories each.

title: popovers
directions: Mix margarine, milk, flour and salt until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Don't overbeat.
Grease and flour muffin tins or popover pan.
Fill half full.
Bake in preheated oven at 450° for 15 minutes and then 350° for 20 minutes longer.
Take out of oven and immediately make a slit in top.

title: yule cake(fruit cake)
directions: Grease bottom and sides of a loaf pan.
(Pam can be used.) Put nuts, dates, cherries, with juice, and raisins in bowl.
Stir in sugar.
Combine all dry ingredients.
Set aside.
Beat eggs and add vanilla.
Combine with nut mix and add flour mix.
Mixture will be thick.
Stir well and spoon into loaf pan.
Bake in slow oven at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes. Then remove from pan.
Keeps well in refrigerator.

title: cranberry waldorf
directions: Grind and drain cranberries.
Mix the rest of ingredients and chill.

title: goofy bars
directions: Place cake mix in mixing bowl.
Put eggs in measuring cup and add water to 2/3 level.
Add to cake mix with the brown sugar. Beat until blended and spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle with chocolate chips and marshmallows on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, or until tests done in center.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Add meat and rice.
Boil cabbage leaves 3 minutes or until limp.
Drain; place 1/2 cup of meat mixture on cabbage leaf (1/4 cup for medium leaf).
Fold sides under and roll up.
Place in baking pan.
Mix soup, brown sugar and lemon juice.
Pour over rolls.
Bake 1 1/4 hours, uncovered, in 350° oven.
Baste occasionally.

title: chile-cheese squares
directions: Mix together the cheeses.
Sprinkle half of the cheeses into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer the green chilies over the cheese.
Top with remaining cheese.
Pour beaten eggs over the top and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Let stand for at least 10 minutes before cutting into squares to serve.
Can be served at room temperature.

title: microwave bacon-and-egg casserole
directions: Place bacon in 9-inch glass plate.
Cook on High for 3 minutes.
Drain off fat, reserving 1 tablespoon of fat.
Stir pepper and mushrooms into bacon.
Cook over High 3 minutes.

title: minted carrots
directions: Combine butter, honey and mint.
Heat and add butter; continue heat until melted.
Add hot carrots.
Heat and stir occasionally until glazed.
Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: bread and bacon hors d'oeuvres
directions: Cut crust off slices of bread; flatten with hand.
Spread about 1 tablespoon soup right from can on each slice of bread. Roll up tight.
Wrap with 1/2 piece of bacon and hold with toothpick.
Refrigerate or freeze about 4 hours.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cut into thirds and serve.

title: freda mcclure's deluxe baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Fry bacon and drain.
Cook onion and pepper in bacon and ground beef until tender.
Drain all beans and save juice.
Mix the next eight ingredients and add half the juice from the vegetables.
Add the meat mixture.
If too dry add more of the juice from the vegetables.
Bake at 350°, stir occasionally, for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Can be frozen.

title: stuffed tomatoes
directions: Mix chicken or tuna, apples, peppers, celery, Miracle Whip and sugar together in a big bowl and toss well.
Cut the tomatoes in sections 3/4 of the way down and stuff with mixture.
Serve on lettuce and garnish as you wish.

title: david's sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well, using hands is the easiest way to do it.
Make rounded teaspoonful size balls.
Place on cookie sheets. Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes until browned.
These freeze well; before cooking, freeze balls on cookie sheet, then put in Ziploc bag until ready to use them.
Bake, increasing time to about 15 minutes.

title: chicken-rice bake
directions: Boil rice for about 5 minutes; drain well.
Mix together cream soups and add rice.
Put mixture in baking pan.
Place chicken pieces on top, skin side up.
Dot with paprika.
Pour onion soup over entire casserole.
Bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: hope's congealed salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O with boiling water and refrigerate until it is ropey or slightly congealed.
Mix soft cream cheese and half and half together, then add pineapple and nuts.
Stir into Jell-O mixture and return to refrigerator until firmly congealed.

title: shrimp or crawfish mold
directions: Boil shrimp in crab boil bag; peel and chop, or chop fresh or frozen crawfish (thawed).
Dilute gelatine in 1/4 cup water (mix and stir).
In Magnalite, bring soup to a boil.
Remove from fire. Add cream cheese and gelatine mix.
Let cool.
Add celery, onion, mayo and meat.
(Add red pepper and salt if not boiling in seasoning bag.)
Spray mold with Pam.
Pour in mold.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve on tray with decorated lettuce.
Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: autumn apple salad
directions: In a saucepan, combine pineapple and sugar; bring to boil and boil 3 minutes.
Add jello; stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese; stir until mixture is thoroughly combined.
Cool.
Fold in apples, nuts, celery and Cool Whip. Pour into 9-inch square pan. Chill until firm.
Cut and eat or serve on lettuce leaves.
Yields 9 to 12 servings.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Stir in salt and pepper; drain; spread in greased baking dish.
Beat milk, Bisquick and eggs until smooth.
Pour over meat and onions.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Top with tomatoes.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Bake at 400°.

title: company strata
directions: From bread, cut 12 shapes with a cookie cutter.
Fit scraps of bread in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Layer sliced cheese, cooked broccoli and ham or sausage over bread.
Arrange cut-outs on top.
Combine eggs, milk, onion, 1/2 teaspoon salt and mustard.
Pour over bread.
Cover with refrigerator for 6 hours or overnight.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes.

title: fried rice with leftovers(very good!!!)
directions: Fry rice in skillet over high heat, stirring all the time, until brown.
Scrape into 4-quart pan with lid.
Add all ingredients, bringing to a boil.
Boil for 1 minute. Turn to low heat and cover tightly.
Don't lift lid for 25 minutes.
Stir and serve.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix chicken, chicken broth, soup and melted butter together; put in casserole.
Mix Bisquick and milk and pour on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or 325° in glass casserole dish.

title: low-fat classic chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In medium bowl, combine mixed vegetables, chicken, soup and thyme. Pour vegetables into greased 2-quart casserole. In small bowl, combine biscuit mix and milk with a fork. Drop a tablespoon at a time over vegetable mixture. Bake, uncovered, for 30 to 35 minutes or until crust is golden brown and filling is hot. Makes 6 servings.

title: cake cookies
directions: Cream the cream cheese and butter.
Blend in egg and vanilla. Add cake mix.
Cover and chill 30 minutes.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375° until light brown.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach and drain.
Mix spinach with remaining ingredients and mix well.
Form into small balls (teaspoon).
Put on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
If mixture is too thin, add a little more stuffing.
This can be frozen before or after cooking.

title: hawaiian wedding cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on package.
Put in a jelly roll pan. Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix pudding as directed on box and fold in pineapple.
Spread over cooled cake.
