Spread Cool Whip over filling.
Sprinkle with coconut.

title: almond munch
directions: In a large skillet over a medium heat, cook the almonds with the margarine, sugar, corn syrup and water, stirring constantly until mixture starts to boil.
Cook and stir for 10 to 12 minutes longer, or until almonds start to brown.
Remove from heat. Carefully stir vanilla extract and almond flavoring into the hot mixture.
Add the cereal; gently stir to coat cereal.
Spread mixture onto a foil lined 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet that has been sprayed with nonstick vegetable spray.
Cool completely, then break into pieces.
Store in an airtight container.
Yields about 7 cups.

title: fresh brisket
directions: Mix spices together and rub into meat.
Pour liquid smoke over meat.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 250° for 4 to 5 hours.
Pour off liquid.
Cool. When ready to use, slice and pour barbecue sauce over all and reheat.

title: cheese and pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple (keep 6 tablespoons juice).
Mix sugar and flour slowly.
Stir in pineapple juice.
Add cheese and pineapple chunks, mixing well.
Put into a 2-quart dish.
Combine butter and crackers.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese, in dish.
Bake in a 350° oven for one hour (plus or minus).
Add cheese.
Bake in oven for 10 minutes to melt cheese.

title: pizza rolls
directions: Sprinkle flour on waxed paper.
Place pizza crust on floured surface in rectangular form.
Spread on sauce.
Cover with pepperoni, top with Mozzarella and gently roll up from one side to the other.
Brush with melted margarine and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix seasoning, cream cheese and sour cream.
Spread on bottom layer of broiler pan.
Put shredded lettuce on top, then diced tomatoes, then layer of onion, then layer of peppers.
Top with black olives.
Scoop with chips and enjoy.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Beat together lemonade, topping and milk until well blended. Pour into crust and refrigerate.
Sets up in 20 minutes.
Use limeade or orange-pineappleade in place of lemon.
Decorate with fruit or whipped topping.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Mix together pudding, milk and Cool Whip.
Put 1 layer graham crackers in 13 x 9-inch Pyrex dish.
Pour pudding over graham crackers, then put some crackers over pudding.
Keep doing this until you end up with crackers on top (2 or 3 layers).
Frost top with Fudge Frosting.

title: avocado sandwich
directions: Toast 2 slices of bread.
Slice avocado and place on bread. Top with Mozzarella cheese and tomato.
Broil in oven open-faced until cheese melts.
Top with alfalfa sprouts.
Add mayonnaise, if desired.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside. In a mixing bowl, blend the shortening and sugar and mix in the egg.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and lemon extract and blend thoroughly.
Chill dough overnight.

title: chocolate pies(makes two)
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour and cocoa.
Mix together.
Add milk and margarine; stir until mixed together well.
Cook on medium heat until thick.
Pour into two baked 9-inch pie shells. Cover pies with meringue.
Bake in a 300° oven until lightly browned.

title: creamy bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix, eggs and margarine (will be very thick). Spread into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla until smooth.
Spread over yellow cake mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: honey bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients together until evenly blended. Press into a well-greased cookie sheet. Bake for 20 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: pineapple-lemon upside-down cake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Line an oblong cake pan with wax paper. Spray with cooking oil.
Spread drained pineapple in bottom of pan. Sprinkle with dry mixture.
Beat egg white and egg substitute on high until thick.
Add lemon color.
Change to low speed.
Add sugar and reserved pineapple juice (1/3 cup).
Add vanilla.
Slowly add flour dry mixture with baking powder and salt.
Beat slowly until batter is well mixed.
Pour into pan.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Loosen side of cake.
Place on plate.
Remove paper.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream of your choice.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Mix all ingredients together except butter and egg whites. Just before cooking, fold in beaten egg whites.
Melt butter in skillet over medium heat.
Form the mixture into patties.
Fry 4 or 5 at a time in melted butter until golden brown.
Turn once.

title: fresh tomato pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle tomatoes lightly with salt and drain on a cooling rack for 15 to 20 minutes.
Layer tomatoes, onions, salt, pepper, basil and chives in pie shell.
Blend mayonnaise and cheese together in a mixing bowl.
Spread over top of pie.
Bake for 30 minutes or until top is lightly browned.

title: egg yolk pastry
directions: Combine dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Place egg yolks in cup and stir with fork.
Stir in enough cold water to fill cup. Toss with fork to make a soft dough.
Makes three 2 crust pies.

title: peach bavarian
directions: Dissolve jello, sugar and salt in cup hot water.
Drain peaches well.
Add 1/2 cup peach juice to jello mixture.
Pour 1/4 cup jello in bottom of mold.
Arrange 8 peach slices in jello. Chill until firm.
Mix Cool Whip in remaining jello.
Spread on top.

title: easy sweet bread
directions: Melt margarine in baking pan at 425°.
Mix together flour, milk and sugar.
Drop by spoonfuls, side by side, in the baking dish of margarine.
Bake at 425° until brown.

title: molded cranberry salad
directions: Make one package of Jell-O according to directions on the package.
Set Jell-O aside.
Refrigerate and begin to mold. Grind the cranberries and quarter and remove the seed of the oranges; grind them also.
Mix the cranberries and oranges together and add the sugar.
Mix well.
When Jell-O begins to form, add the cranberry mixture and chill until firm.

title: baked corn
directions: Heat corn and milk.
Gradually stir in egg.
Add seasonings and cracker crumbs.
Place in greased baking dish.
Sprinkle buttered crumbs over top and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: broccoli and chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and remove from bone.
Mix together remaining ingredients and bake in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Spray dish with Pam before using.

title: pork chops and brown rice
directions: Brown pork chops.
Place all ingredients in casserole.
Bake 1 hour (or until rice is done) at 350°.

title: fresh fruit compote
directions: Mix all
fruits
in your prettiest bowl.
Add to it the mixture of	honey,	orange juice and ground ginger.
Blend and refrigerate.
Serve
in sherbets or can be used over ice cream with plain cake.

title: strawberry romanoff
directions: Wash and stem berries; let set.
Sprinkle berries with powdered sugar 1 hour before serving.
Fold in cream, whipped and flavored with almond extract and Cointreau.
Spoon into sherbet or parfait glasses and serve immediately.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Mix water and noodle soup.
Bring to boil; add broccoli and let come to boil.
Cook until tender.
Add cheese; let melt and add milk.
Heat, but do not boil.

title: homemade pot pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Mix together and pour into pie shells.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Might need a little longer. Cook 10 minutes and serve.
(I use almost 2 cans of mixed vegetables.)

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Put in pie shell and bake.

title: chili cheese log
directions: Blend cheese with mixer.
Add garlic powder, onion salt, Tabasco and Worcestershire sauce to taste.
Form into a log and roll in chili powder.

title: chocolatetown pie
directions: Prepare pastry shell.
Set aside.
In small mixer bowl, cream margarine.	Add
egg
and
vanilla.
Combine
sugar and flour; add
to
creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into unbaked pastry shell.	Bake 45 to 50 minutes. Cool about an hour.
Serve warm.	Garnish with festive whipped cream, if desired.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: seasoned hard pretzels
directions: Sifted is the key word.
If the word sifted is before the word flour, it means the flour should be sifted before measured.
If the word sifted is after the word flour, then it should be measured and then sifted.
Sifted flour means to sift, then measure flour.
Sifted means to measure and then sift.

title: chewy cookies
directions: Bring sugar and margarine to a boil, then let cool.
Add eggs to sugar mixture, then flour, vanilla and nuts.
Gradually stir in each ingredient.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan and pour in mixture. Bake at 300° until done, about 30 to 45 minutes.
When cool, cut into bars.

title: apple harvest pudding
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and egg.
Add dry ingredients and spices alternately with 1 cup milk.
Add fruit and nuts.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish and bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: hot tamale pie
directions: Combine water, cornmeal and 1 teaspoon salt over medium heat, stirring often, until mixture is very thick.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Set aside to cool.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt and mustard.
In a 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish, arrange in layers, bread cubes, bacon and cheese.
Pour egg mixture over the top. Bake in a 350° oven for about 45 minutes.
Cut in squares and serve.
Sausage may be used for the bacon.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Heat oil in skillet.
Saute onion, pepper and garlic over medium heat 2 to 3 minutes.
Add mushrooms and cook 2 more minutes.
Spray a 3-quart casserole with vegetable oil spray; drain macaroni and combine with cheese packet, sauteed vegetables, turkey and milk.
Pour into casserole dish; cover and cook 30 to 45 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with Cheddar cheese.
Cover until cheese melts.

title: chicken breast or pork chops
directions: Sprinkle meat with dry ingredients.
Drizzle with melted butter and splash of lemon juice.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix well over low heat until well blended.

title: baked rice pilaf
directions: Combine all ingredients in 8 inch square dish.
Cover and bake 40-45 minutes at 375°F.
Stir after 25 minutes.

title: tomato juice cocktail
directions: Combine ingredients.
Chill 1 hour.
Strain and serve in cocktail glass.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: In a small bowl, combine walnuts, cinnamon and 1/2 cup of sugar until well mixed.
Set aside.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Using a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish, mix together sugar and syrup.
Microwave 3 1/2 to 4 minutes on High.
Stir in 1 cup peanuts.
Microwave 3 1/2 to 4 minutes or until light brown.
Add butter and vanilla; stir until blended.
Microwave 1 1/2 minutes. Add soda; stir until light and foamy.
Pour on greased (butter) cookie sheet.
Put in freezer 10 minutes, then break into pieces.

title: mock liver knishes
directions: Trim crusts from bread and flatten with a rolling pin.
Spread each slice of bread with the chopped liver and top with another slice of bread to form a sandwich.
Cut each sandwich diagonally into triangles.

title: really quick hors d'oeuvre
directions: Put the cream cheese "cube" on a really nice plate.
Place the shrimp over the cream cheese, after draining.
Lay the crackers around the cream cheese and serve.
Serves 6.

title: mint brownies
directions: Melt together.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Spread on mint layer.
Refrigerate 20 minutes.

title: cinnamon pancakes
directions: Mix and cook on griddle.

title: (baccala) cod or stockfish (stewed)
directions: Cook onion, garlic and celery in butter and oil.
Add tomato paste, fish and parsley, then add the spices.
Add water, if needed.
Salt and pepper to your taste.

title: maple syrup frosting
directions: Boil maple syrup to a firm ball, 242°, and beat into syrup mixture the stiffly beaten egg whites.

title: mexican dip
directions: Spread refried beans in a casserole dish.
Add sour cream; spread on top of refried beans.
Add Cheddar cheese on top of sour cream; top off with jalapeno peppers, tomato and black olives (for taste).
Use tortilla chips (Food Lion) to dip with.

title: honey burgers
directions: Mix all ingredients (except oil) in bowl.
Shape into patties 1/2-inch thick.
Heat oil in skillet over medium heat.
Place patties in oil 6 to 8 minutes, turn as needed, until brown.
Serve on buns, with rice or noodles.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Line baking sheet with wax paper or easy release aluminum foil.
Mix peanut butter, butter, vanilla, and sugar in bowl with hands until forming a smooth dough.
Mixture will be stiff; shape into small balls and place on baking sheet, refrigerate until chilled.
In a small bowl melt bark in microwave in small batches, start putting a few balls in the bark one at a time, using a spoon to cover them with chocolate.
Lift balls out with spoon; place into miniature cupcake papers to harden.
Recipe makes about 6 dozen.

title: chicken breasts stuffed
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 375 degrees. 2. Combine first 6 ingredients; stir well. 3. Place each chicken breast half between 2 sheets of heavy-duty plastic wrap; pound to 1/4 inch thickness using a meat mallet or rolling pin.
Top each breast with 2 tbsp. cheese mixture; roll up jelly roll fashion.
Tuck in sides; secure each roll with wooden toothpicks. 4. Heat a large skillet coated with cooking spray over medium-high heat.
Add chicken to pan and cook 3 minutes on each side or until browned.
Remove from pan and place in baking pan sprayed with PAM.
Bake at 375 degrees for 15 minutes or until chicken is done.

title: blueberry surprise jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water. Drain blueberries and pineapple and measure liquid. Add enough water to make 2 cups. Add to Jell-O. Stir in blueberries and pineapple and pour in 2-quart dish; cover. Put in the refrigerator until firm.

title: graham cracker pie
directions: Fold all ingredients together and pour into the pie shells. Chill before serving.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes in microwave and cut in half. Carefully scoop out potatoes and reserve shells. In a large mixing bowl, beat potatoes and margarine until creamy. Gradually add milk, salt and pepper. Spoon mixture into reserved potato shells. Sprinkle with cheese. Arrange in baking dish. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: kraut salad
directions: Mix sugar and vinegar; pour over other ingredients.
Let stand overnight; keep in the refrigerator.

title: corn rarebit
directions: Cut green pepper into small pieces.
Cook and stir for 5 minutes in melted butter.
Add cheese, cut into small bits.
Stir constantly until melted.
Add can of corn and salt and stir until blended.
Add beaten eggs to tomatoes and then add to hot mixture until hot.
Serve at once.

title: cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Store in airtight container.
To Use:
Combine 1 cup hot water and 1/3 cup mix; stir.

title: hot wings
directions: Cook margarine, vinegar and seasonings in pan on top of stove until liquid is reduced.
Fry chicken wings until done.
Pour liquid over wings.
They may be frozen and reheated.

title: butter baked potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Peel and wash potatoes. Dice potatoes to desired thickness. In glass bowl, melt butter. When butter is completely melted, spray bowl with Pam around the edges. You can spice the potatoes with pepper or Mrs. Dash original seasoning blend. Keep potatoes turned. Cook until tender.

title: crunchy squash casserole
directions: Mix together prepared squash, sour cream and chicken soup. Add sauted onions and water chestnuts.
In a separate bowl, mix stuffing and season mix together.
Melt 6 tablespoons butter and add to mixture; mix well.
Add 3/4 stuffing mixture to squash mixture.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish. Top with remaining stuffing mixture.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mile high frosting
directions: Slowly add
milk to flour and salt in small saucepan to make a smooth
paste.
Cook
over
medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick.
Cool completely (may be refrigerated). If mixture becomes lumpy, beat until smooth.
In small bowl of electric mixer,
cream
sugar, shortening and margarine until fluffy.
With mixer running at slow speed, add flour mixture a tablespoon at
a time.
Add	vanilla
and
beat at high speed until stiff and fluffy.

title: smoked salmon dip
directions: Finely chop salmon.
Stir together with salmon, cream cheese, milk, lemon juice and pepper.
Add dill and serve.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Combine and mix the first 5 ingredients.
Next, combine and mix remaining ingredients.
Grease 8-inch square casserole. Combine the Bisquick mixture and zucchini mixture in casserole. Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Stir sugar and oil together in large bowl, then stir in canned pumpkin.
Combine flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Using slow speed on mixer, add dry ingredients alternately with the eggs.
Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in 325°
oven for approximately 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and squeeze spinach until dry.
Stir together remaining ingredients.
Blend well, cover and refrigerate several hours. Stir before serving.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix sugar, Crisco and egg together.
Add salt.
Mix soda in flour.
Add milk and flour alternately to mixture, then add mashed bananas and add nuts last.
Bake in two loaf pans which have been greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.
You can freeze this.

title: easy homemade soup
directions: Brown ground beef in large pot and drain grease off.
Chop tomatoes and add to pot.
Add all other ingredients except shells and cook on high until hot.
Lower heat and cook for 20 minutes with lid on pot.
Add shells and continue cooking for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small saucepan, melt 1 cup margarine. Stir in cocoa, then water.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
In large bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Add cocoa mixture and beat well.
Stir in 1/2 cup Eagle Brand milk, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into greased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan and bake 15 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well and shape into a ball.

title: paul's chili
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Mix all ingredients together with ground beef.
Cook at 250° for 3 to 4 hours.

title: applesauce brownies
directions: Melt Crisco and chocolate over hot water.
Blend in the sugar, eggs, applesauce and vanilla.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Fold into chocolate mixture and add the nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 9-inch pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°. Cut while hot.
May ice, if desired.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Butter a large casserole dish and place first layer of potatoes sliced and then layer of cheese and onions.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Repeat layers and pour milk over all.
Bake for 1 hour at 350° until potatoes are tender.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Place chicken breasts, which have been skinned and boned, in baking dish.
Bake, covered, 15 minutes in preheated 425° oven; drain.
Combine tomatoes, cornstarch, oregano and pepper sauce (optional).
Cook, stirring constantly, until sauce is thickened. Pour heated sauce over chicken.
Top with cheese.
Bake 5 minutes, uncovered.

title: copper pennies
directions: Peel and cut carrots into "pennies".
Cook carrots until crisp, not mushy.
Drain and cool with cold water.
Peel onions and separate into rings.
Cut green peppers into strips or rings.

title: fruit and yogurt cream pie
directions: Arrange fruit in crust.
In small saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over water.
Let stand 1 minute.
Stir over low heat until dissolved.
In blender, process cottage cheese and yogurt on high speed until smooth.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Blend well. Gradually add gelatin mixture.
Blend well.
Pour over fruit in crust.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Garnish with additional fruit before serving. Makes 8 servings; contains 190 calories per serving.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Place ingredients in a saucepan and bring to boil.
Simmer 20 to 30 minutes.
Place shrimp in a shallow baking dish and pour sauce over.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Plan on 1 pound of shrimp per person.
Use unpeeled large shrimp.

title: hot apricot casserole
directions: Drain apricots and put in buttered casserole dish.
Put brown sugar over apricots.
Melt oleo and mix with crushed mixture on top.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Serve with a main dish.
This casserole is not considered a dessert.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Combine all ingredients in saucepan.
Simmer 30 minutes, covered.
Uncover and continue cooking to desired consistency. Serve with noodles, pasta or rice.

title: waffles
directions: Preheat waffle iron, grease lightly.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into a large bowl. Combine milk, eggs, oil in a medium bowl.
Stir liquid ingredients into dry ingredients until moistened.

title: cheesecake squares
directions: Melt the margarine and combine it in a bowl with 1/4 cup of the sugar and flour.
Press the mixture firmly into the bottom of pan (ungreased, 8 x 8-inch square baking pan).
Prebake the crust for 10 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Cream together sugar, eggs and oil.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Mix together, then add fruit cocktail to batter.
Mix well.
Bake in long pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sand tarts
directions: Cream oleo and sugar together.
Add flour, vanilla and pecans. Dough will be stiff.
Roll in small balls and bake at 350° until light brown.
When cool not cold, roll in extra powdered sugar.

title: after school snack
directions: Mix according to directions on box.
Using graham crackers, make sandwiches with the pudding and freeze on cookie sheet. After frozen, pack in airtight container.

title: chili-roast chicken
directions: In a large glass baking dish, whisk the yogurt, cinnamon, chili powder, hot pepper sauce and garlic.
Add the chicken and coat with the marinade.
Cover the dish and refrigerate for at least 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 500°.
Place chicken skin side up on a raised broiler rack and place in oven.
Immediately reduce the temperature to 350° and roast until the chicken breasts are cooked through and tender, about 45 minutes.
Serve 4.

title: congealed orange salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1/2 cup juice from pineapple.
Add orange juice.
Add drained pineapple.
Pour in oblong dish and chill.
Prepare lemon pudding according to directions on package.
Prepare Dream Whip according to directions.
Stir together and put on top.
Put grated cheese on top.

title: cinnamon apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange apple slices in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Pour water over top.
Combine cake mix, brown sugar, melted butter and cinnamon.
Stir until thoroughly blended; mixture will be crumbly.

title: baked beans
directions: Bake at 300° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: chocolate marshmallow pie
directions: Bake and cool pastry.
In top of double boiler, combine marshmallows and milk.
Place over hot water; stir mixture until marshmallows melt.
Add broken chocolate bar.
Stir until mixture is smooth.
Cool to room temperature.
Whip the whipping cream. Fold into marshmallow mixture.
Turn into pastry shell.
Cover with waxed paper or clear plastic wrap.
Refrigerate at least 6 hours or overnight.

title: peppery lamb
directions: Cut boneless lamb in cubes.
Saute in wok at 375°.
Add soy sauce and cornstarch.
Mix well.
Add clove or grated garlic, onions and pepper.
Simmer for 5 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: swiss cheese bread
directions: Make diagonal cuts at 1-inch intervals in loaf of bread, cutting to, but not through, the bottom crust.
In bowl, combine all ingredients and then spread between the slices of bread. Place bread on baking sheet.
Cover loosely with foil.
Bake at 425° for about 15 minutes.
Uncover and bake 5 minutes longer or until browned.

title: pecan pie 1
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add salt, slightly beaten eggs, flour, vanilla and white syrup. Stir well. Add pecans. Pour into pie crusts. Cook 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon ginger sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended; chill.
Serve over fresh fruit.

title: linda's wonderful cheese ball
directions: Soften all the cheeses at room temperature.
Mix all ingredients, except for the pecans.
Chill the cheese mixture several hours or overnight is best.
Take mixture out and form the cheese ball.
Roll cheese ball in the chopped pecans.
Serve. Very good served with Pepperidge Farm Butterfly crackers.
Makes 1 large ball.

title: rice krispy trees
directions: Put them into a ball and stir.
Put them in the oven for 10 minutes at 9 degrees.
When it is finished, cut them up and eat them.

title: steak marinade
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Reserve 1/4 c. for basting. Marinate steak several hours or overnight.
Discard marinade and grill or broil.
Baste last 3 minutes of cooking.

title: corn casserole
directions: Do not drain corn.
Mix everything together as listed.
Pour in greased round dish or cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Corn bread will come to top.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: Layer in a 13 x 9 pan the pineapple, blueberries, 3/4 cup sugar and cake mix. Drizzle oleo, sugar and nuts on top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Remove from oven and punch holes in it, then bake again until brown.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat at medium speed for 5 minutes.
Pour into greased Bundt pan and bake at 350°.
Cool. Sprinkle powdered sugar on top.

title: french coconut pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except pie shell. Pour into the pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 40 minutes, or until top is golden and the center is almost set.
When cool, store in refrigerator. Yields 8 servings.

title: orange pudding
directions: Mix sugar, salt and flour well.
Mix milk and orange juice and add to first mixture.
Cook in a double boiler. Add orange pieces and cook until thick.

title: honey poppy seed dressing
directions: In a screwtop jar, combine all ingredients, except last one. Cover and shake well.
Store in the refrigerator until ready to use.
Serve over fresh fruit or mixed greens.
Yields 3/4 cup.

title: easy lasagne
directions: Brown
ground
beef and
drain.
Cook
lasagne	as
per instructions, do not overcook.
In baking pan or dish, 14 x 10 x 2-inches, spread some sauce
to moisten bottom of pan.
Then a layer of lasagne
noodles
(approximately
4), then layer of ground beef, cheeses and spaghetti sauce.
Start another layer same as before, until
pan	is
full (approximately 2 layers). Top with lasagne noodles
and
spaghetti
sauce.
Cook at 300° about 40 minutes.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Combine all ingredients well and chill.
Good served with any cake, especially pound cake.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together and bake in one pan in moderate oven for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: cabbage-beet relish
directions: Mix together vegetables, horseradish and salt.
Heat vinegar and salt; stir until dissolved.
Add to the vegetables and boil 12 minutes.
Pack in hot jars and seal.

title: spiced walnuts
directions: Coat the walnuts with the egg white.
Mix the sugar and cinnamon together.
Sprinkle over nuts, stirring until evenly coated.
Spread on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 300° for about 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal toll house cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars together.
Add eggs, water and vanilla; beat.
Add soda and salt; stir.
Stir in oatmeal.
(Add more if the batter is not stiff.)
Drop from a teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 12 minutes or until they raise back when touched.

title: cherry pepper chicken casserole
directions: In a 12 x 8-inch casserole dish, layer chicken.
Set aside. Discard 1/2 juice of olive condite.
Add remaining juice and olive condite to tomato paste and cherry peppers.
Mix well and pour over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Serve over cooked rice. Yields 6 servings.

title: broccoli salad(serves 8)
directions: In large Pyrex dish, layer broccoli, onion and cheese.
Mix mayo, sugar and vinegar together and spread on top.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.
To serve, toss together in large salad bowl and sprinkle crumbled bacon on top.

title: low carb breakfast smoothie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender. Blend until smooth. Add ice if using fresh fruit and blend again until slushy.

title: yummy barbecue spareribs
directions: Mix sauce ingredients together.
Place spareribs in roasting pan.
Pour 1 cup of water in pan.
Baste ribs with about half of the sauce.
Roast in oven at 350° for 2 to 3 hours, turning and basting every half hour.
Serve when ribs are very soft when poked with a fork.

title: gabriele's fried ham and cheese spatzle
directions: Cook bag of spatzle according to directions; drain off the water.
Chop onion and ham.
Fry onion and ham in butter or margarine for 5 minutes.
Add spatzle and fry until they are brown. Season with salt, pepper and paprika.
Add 1/2 pound grated Swiss cheese.
Let it melt.
Serve with any type of salad.

title: pot pie
directions: Unfold pie
crust
and	place in a large Corning baking dish. In	a
bowl,
tear meat into chunks. Add Veg-All, mushrooms, onion soup and celery soup.
Mix all. Add to pie crust. Top with other pie crust. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, bananas, zucchini and vanilla.
Add flour.
Mix all.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.
Double or triple recipe and freeze.

title: prune cake(aka spicy fruit and nut cake)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 12-cup Bundt pan. Combine prunes and nuts with 1/2 cup flour in a bowl.
Sift together remaining flour, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice and salt in large bowl.
Add sugar, oil, buttermilk, vanilla and eggs. Beat with mixer for approximately 1 minute or until smooth.
Add prune mixture and fold lightly but thoroughly.
Pour into prepared pan and cook for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Invert onto plate and prick with toothpick all over cake.
Slowly ladle glaze evenly over cake.
Cool thoroughly. Serve with whipped cream, if desired.

title: campers cocoa
directions: Mix all ingredients together (will be a dry mix). Store in a plastic container.

title: elegant chicken
directions: Cover the bottom of greased 8 x 12-inch pan with chipped beef. Arrange chicken on top of this.
Place parcooked bacon on top of chicken.
Blend soup and sour cream, then pour over bacon and chicken.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, for 3 hours at 275°.

title: glazed blue cheese meatballs
directions: Combine beef with Blue cheese, onion, Worcestershire sauce, salt and seasoned salt.
Shape into 12 meatballs.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add meatballs and brown on all sides.
Cover skillet. Cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Remove meatballs with a slotted spoon and put in serving dish.
Add cream to drippings.
Cook over medium to high heat, stirring for about 2 minutes or until satiny.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Soak poppy seed in milk for 2 hours.
Cream butter and add sugar, then add milk and poppy seed.
Add dry ingredients and then fold in egg whites.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan or 2 (9-inch) round cake pans.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°. Frost when cool.

title: mexican 5 layer dip
directions: Spread bean dip on 12-inch round dish.
Mix avocado and lemon juice; spread over bean dip.
Blend sour cream, Miracle Whip and taco seasoning.
Sprinkle tomatoes and onions on top.
Sprinkle cheese on top of that.
Garnish with olives.
Serve with tortilla or corn chips.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt chocolate chips, margarine and peanut butter together in a large bowl.
Stir until coated.
In a paper bag, place 2 cups of confectioners sugar and the coated cereal.
Shake and serve.
Store in airtight container.

title: crunch bottom pie
directions: Melt butter in baking dish.
Add flour, brown sugar and pecans.
Mix well and press down in pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Lightly brown.
Cool completely.

title: marsha's cheesecake
directions: Preheat the oven to 300°.
Generously butter a 10-inch spring-form pan.

Wrap a double layer of heavy-duty aluminum foil tightly around the bottom and sides of the pan, crimping and pleating the foil so that it conforms to the shape of the pan. Fold the top edge of foil down so that it is even with the top edge of the pan.

title: simple salisbury steak
directions: In bowl, mix thoroughly 1/4 cup soup, hamburger, bread crumbs, egg and onion.
Shape firmly into 6 oval patties.
In skillet over high heat in 1 tablespoon hot fat, cook the patties until brown. Spoon off fat.
Stir in remaining soup and mushrooms.
Return patties to skillet.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes or until done, turning occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: yum-yum cake
directions: Cook raisins, sugar, water, lard and cinnamon in pan for 5 minutes.
Let cool.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Mix well.
Bake in 8 x 8-inch greased pan for 45 minutes at 375°.
Test with toothpick.

title: baked corn pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Lightly grease 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
In large bowl, combine corn, eggs and onion.
Mix well.

title: chicken and sausage jambalaya
directions: Brown seasoned chicken in hot oil, preferably in black iron pot, or at least a cast aluminum pot (works real well in my stainless stock pot). Next brown sausage well. Remove meat and most of the oil, and add onions, bell pepper, garlic powder and shallots (I like to add some cajun seasoning to this step). It is EXTREMELY important to BROWN these vegetables well. You may have to add a little water from time to time to keep them from sticking. Now put the chicken and sausage back in the pot along with all the water and the tomatoes. Add seasonings to your desired taste. When mixture comes to a rolling boil, add minute rice. When this reaches a good boil again, stir well and lower heat; cover and let cook until rice soaks up all the liquid. This should take about 20 to 30 minutes. Stir as little as possible.

title: peach cobbler supreme
directions: Combine peaches, sugar, flour and nutmeg.
Set aside until syrup forms.
Bring peaches to a boil and cook over low heat for 10 minutes or until tender.
Remove from heat.
Add almond extract and butter, stirring well.

title: pineapple upside down cake
directions: Melt 1/3 cup butter in 10-inch baking dish. Sprinkle brown sugar over butter. Arrange pineapple and maraschino cherries in the butter and sugar.

title: split pea soup
directions: Heat peas and water to boiling in a large kettle. Boil 2 minutes. Remove from heat. Cover and let stand 1 hour. Add remaining ingredients to peas. Heat to boiling. Reduce heat. Cover and simmer about 2 hours or until soup is thick enough to stand a spoon in. Serve with pumpernickel bread. If desired, slice a ring of "lite" kielbasa and add to soup for the last 15 minutes of cooking.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift
the flour and all dry ingredients together into a large bowl.
Separate yolks and whites from eggs.
Add yolks, grated carrots, nuts and salad oil to dry ingredients, mixing well
with beaters.
Mixture
will
be very thick.
Fold in 3 beaten egg whites.
Pour into greased tube cake pan.
Bake for 50
minutes in a 350° oven.
Frost with cream cheese frosting. Decorate with pecans.

title: cherry oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift
flour,
soda
and
salt
together.
Combine
with rolled oats and set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, cherry liquid and vanilla and beat well.
Stir in dry ingredients, cherries and nuts.
(Additional oats and cherries may be added.) Shape
into
small
balls, using 1 rounded teaspoonful for each. Coat
with
oats
or chopped nuts, if desired.
Top each with cherry
half.
Place
on
greased
cookie sheets and bake in moderate oven
at
350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 6 to 7 dozen.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Boil first 4 ingredients for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Drop by spoonfuls onto foil and allow to cool.
Store in covered container.

title: scalloped corn with green peppers
directions: Combine white sauce and egg; add corn, sugar and green peppers.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Cover with bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° in oven until browned.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Heat chocolate and milk in sauce pan on medium heat, about 20 minutes; add vanilla.
Pour into blender-fill only half way, blend until frothy.

title: spinach tortilla bites
directions: Defrost chopped spinach and squeeze very dry.
Mix all filling ingredients together.
Spread thin layer of filling over tortillas.
Roll jelly roll style.
Refrigerate overnight in airtight container.
Cut into 1/2-inch bites with sharp knife before serving.

title: aging cake
directions: Mix cake as directed and cook.
Cut into 4 layers with a thread.

title: peach dumplings
directions: Combine peaches, water, sugar and lemon juice in a 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
In a separate bowl, combine remaining ingredients and stir lightly.
Drop batter by tablespoonfuls into boiling peach mixture.
Reduce heat, cover pan and cook 15 minutes without lifting cover.
Serve warm with ice cream.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Mix milk, eggs and lemon juice.
Pour into pie crust and bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
Chill and top with Cool Whip.
Makes 1 pie.

title: apple-pineapple slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.

title: day before breakfast
directions: Saute sausage, drain.
Beat eggs with milk and salt.
Cut bread in triangles and lay in pan.
Put sausage, cheese and onion on bread and pour eggs on top.
Let stand overnight in the refrigerator.
Put in 350° oven next morning for 45 minutes.
Great for Christmas or New Year's Day morning.

title: vegetarian hamburgers
directions: Saute onion and green pepper and add to burger.
Mix all ingredients together. Fry in patties, 1/2 cup per bun.

title: easy-as-a-mix brownies
directions: Melt margarine and cocoa in a 2-quart saucepan on top of the stove.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar, eggs and vanilla; stir well. Add flour, baking powder and salt; mix well.
(All this can be mixed right in the saucepan.)
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry trifle
directions: Crumble angel food cake into medium-sized pieces in bottom of large glass bowl.
Pour a layer of pudding, then arrange a layer of strawberries and a layer of Cool Whip.
Repeat layers with Cool Whip at top of the bowl.
Garnish top with 3 or 4 strawberries. Strawberries can be substituted with your favorite fruit.

title: cabbage caper
directions: Chop cabbage and place in saucepan.
Add small amount of water and cook for 10 minutes.
Drain.
Combine soup and milk.
Combine bread crumbs and margarine.
Place alternating layers of cabbage, soup mixture and cheese in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: vicki's lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add spaghetti seasoning mix, tomato sauce and tomato paste.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer 3 noodles on bottom of pan.
Top with 1/2 meat mixture; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese, 3 more noodles, cottage cheese, remaining noodles, Mozzarella cheese and rest of meat mixture.
Sprinkle heavily with Parmesan cheese.
Bake 1/2 to 3/4 hour at 350°.

title: pig pickin cake
directions: Bake cake by package direction in a 9 x 13-inch pan or large sheet pan.
Poke holes in baked cake with fork.
Cook sugar and pineapple until sugar is dissolved.
Pour over warm cake and let sit until cake cools.
Mix pudding with 3 cups milk until sets. Then add to Cool Whip.
Ice cake with mixture.
Keep refrigerated.

title: cheese "souffle" casserole
directions: Lightly grease crock-pot.
Alternate layers of bread and cheese and, if desired, meat.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt and parsley.
Pour over bread and cheese in crock-pot.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Cover and cook on low for 3 to 4 hours.

title: okra patties
directions: Chop finely both okra and onion.
Mix well with salt, pepper, water and egg.
Mix flour, baking powder and cornmeal; add to previous mixture.
Drop in hot grease and brown over medium heat. Drain on paper towels.
Yields 8 patties.

title: taco casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400° and spray a 9 x 13 pan with Pam. Cook rotini as directed on package and drain.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Cut berries in halves; rinse and drain well.
Place in baked pie shell.
Boil water, sugar and cornstarch until thickened and clear, about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour over berries and refrigerate 2 to 3 hours. Top with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: easy jello salad
directions: Mix above in large bowl.
Serve chilled.

title: rice pudding
directions: Butter pan. Set oven at 350°. Bake 30 to 35 minutes. Shake pan. If soupy, cook a little longer.

title: double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Hint:
Soften cream cheese in microwave on High 15 to 20 seconds.

title: microwave peanut brittle(never fails!)
directions: Note:
If raw peanuts are used, add before microwaving to the sugar-syrup mixture along with 1/8 teaspoon salt.

title: parmesan baked potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes; lightly grease skins.
Bake in a 400° oven for 1 hour until done.
Cut thin slices off top of potatoes; scoop out inside and mash.
Add onion, eggs, 1/3 cup Parmesan, margarine, salt, pepper and enough hot milk to make proper consistency (about 1/4 cup).
Beat until fluffy.
Carefully pile mixture into potato shells.
Brush tops.

title: low-fat chocolate-amaretto cheesecake
directions: Sprinkle chocolate wafer crumbs in bottom of 7-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside.
In food processor, put cream cheese and next 7 ingredients.
Process until smooth.
Add egg and process just until blended.
Fold in chocolate morsels.
Slowly pour mixture over crumbs in pan.
Bake at 300° for 65 to 70 minutes or until set. Let cool in pan on wire rack.
Cover and chill at least 8 hours. Remove sides of pan and place on serving plate.
Garnish with chocolate curls or morsels.

title: pickle relish
directions: Remove seed from peppers.
Put peppers, tomatoes, cucumbers and onion through the food chopper, using coarse blade.
Stir salt into vegetables.
Let set overnight.
Next morning, place vegetables in colander and press down firmly to force out as much of brine as possible.
Shred cabbage very fine, then chop across shreds, chopping fine.
Combine all the vegetables.
Place over low heat and slowly heat only to simmering, stirring gently from time to time.
This heating makes vegetables slightly tender.
Add sugar, vinegar and spices and heat to the boiling point.
Boil 3 minutes. Pack in sterilized jars and seal at once.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Place cake in the bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. In a mixing bowl, beat pudding mix and milk on low 1 1/2

minutes. Add ice cream; beat on low 1 minute. Pour over cake; chill. Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add cold water and strawberries. Mix until partially set. Spoon over pudding layer. Cover and chill overnight.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix the peanut butter with vanilla and salt.
Mix the remaining ingredients together.
Combine mixtures thoroughly. Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 10 minutes at 450°, then turn down to 325° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: oyster cracker snacks
directions: Mix together and pour over two boxes oyster crackers.

title: deerburger meat loaf
directions: Mix all well with hands.
Shape into flat loaf and bake in glass dish for 40 minutes at 450°.

title: venison stew
directions: Salt and pepper meat; brown in butter.
Add all ingredients to crock-pot.
Cover and cook on low 9 to 12 hours.
Serve over noodles.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook, drain and cool spinach.
Add Lipton onion soup mix and sour cream.
Pour in greased casserole.
Sprinkle stuffing mix. Melt margarine and pour over top.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: elegant chicken
directions: Spread dried beef on bottom of large glass baking dish.
Wrap a slice of bacon around each piece of chicken and place on top of dried beef.
Mix soup and sour cream together; pour over chicken. Sprinkle generously with paprika.
Bake uncovered at 275° for 3 hours.
If too much bacon fat collects, spoon off.
This can be made the day before and refrigerated overnight.

title: hush puppies
directions: Sift the corn meal, baking powder, salt and flour together. Add onion and egg, then add buttermilk mixture.
Shape into small balls and fry in deep fat until brown.
Serves 6.

title: cream chicken and noodles
directions: Boil chicken until tender, then cut into small pieces.
Add noodles to pot with broth.
Cook until noodles are done.
Return chicken to pot and add soup.
Stir and simmer on low for 15 minutes.

title: honey chicken wings
directions: Season chicken with pepper.
Place wings in baking dish.
Mix together honey, soy sauce, oil, ketchup and garlic powder until well blended.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 45 minutes, until chicken is well done and sauce is thick.

title: coral shrimp dip
directions: Finely chop shrimp.
Combine the shrimp, cheese, chili sauce, lemon juice, onion juice and Worcestershire sauce with electric mixer or rotary beater or blender.
Gradually beat in enough milk to give good dipping consistency.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix and serve on crackers or party rye.

title: pork chops on rice
directions: In skillet, brown pork chops on both sides.
Season with salt and pepper.
Place rice in baking dish.
Pour orange juice over rice. Pour chicken soup over all. Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes more.
Serves 6.

title: cleaning solution for walls
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bucket.
Work from bottom up to clean walls.
No rinsing necessary.

title: baked corn
directions: Melt butter in 2-quart saucepan.
Sprinkle in flour; gradually add milk and bring to boiling point.
Add corn, salt, pepper and sugar.
Heat thoroughly; remove from heat and add beaten eggs.
Pour into 2 1/2-quart buttered baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: baked lemon pudding
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt in a bowl.
Stir in lemon juice, rind, beaten egg yolks, butter and milk.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Fold into lemon mixture.
Pour into buttered 6-cup casserole.
Place in larger pan; pour hot water to about 1-inch depth.
Bake in 350° oven for about 40 minutes or until topping is set and golden brown.
Serve warm.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Rinse broccoli under cold water to thaw.
Drain thoroughly. Mix broccoli, 2 cups cheese, ham or chicken and onion.
Place in casserole.
Beat milk, eggs, Bisquick mix, salt and pepper until smooth (15 seconds in blender on high or 1 minute with hand mixer).
Pour over mixture.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 45 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese. Bake just until cheese is melted.
Cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: sugarless apple cookies
directions: In a large saucepan, combine dates, apple, raisins and water. Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; cool.
Combine flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt, if desired.
Stir into apple mixture and mix well.
Combine eggs and sweetener; add to batter.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto a nonstick baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yield: 2 dozen (54 calories).

title: zucchini pie
directions: Mix all together.
Put in square or rectangular pan. Top with grated Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix creamed corn, eggs (beaten), milk, sugar, salt, pepper and flour together. Sprinkle 5 broken soda crackers on top.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: ole settler beans
directions: Fry hamburger, onion and bacon (leave grease).
Mix all the beans together and add the first mixture.
Mix together, then add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (crock-pot works well).

title: peanut butter krispies
directions: Bring
sugar
and Karo to a boil.
Remove from heat and add peanut
butter,
vanilla,
cornflakes
and Rice Krispies. Stir and spoon on wax paper.

title: dried beef dip
directions: Saute beef in stick of butter until dark and crumbly.
Add cream cheese and mix.
Add horseradish to taste.
Serve with medium size pretzels.

title: swedish coffee cake
directions: Mix the first dry ingredients well.
(Reserve about 1/2 cup to sprinkle on top later.) Add
butter
and mix well, then add milk, egg and soda.
Beat well.
Pour
in
a
greased
9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle dry ingredients on top and bake at 325° to 350° for 30 minutes.
(I
add
about
tablespoons
brown sugar to my topping.)

title: apple orchard bean bake
directions: In large skillet, brown meat; drain off fat.
Stir in beans, soup and pepper.
Pour into casserole dish.
Arrange apple slices on top.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake, uncovered, at 450° for 25 minutes.
Let stand 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: pig picking cake
directions: Mix all batter ingredients and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes in two 9-inch cake pans.

title: bacon-n-beans
directions: Dice bacon.
Fry until crisp.
Add tomato sauce and beans. Simmer 10 minutes.
Serve with rolls or brown bread.
Makes 4 servings.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix the last 5 ingredients thoroughly and then add cooked macaroni; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch.
Add 7-Up or ginger ale.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add Jell-O.
Mix well.
Cool until slightly jelled.
Add berries.
Refrigerate 2 or 3 hours.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: crock-pot chili
directions: Brown meat.
Add chopped onion, garlic, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Add tomato juice.
Put in crock-pot and add beans.
Heat on medium 5 or 6 hours, stirring every hour.

title: super cherry dessert
directions: Line oblong dish with graham cracker squares, fitting them in to cover the bottom.
Combine pudding mix and milk and beat well. Allow to stand 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped topping.
Put one half (1/2) pudding on crackers.
Add another layer of graham crackers. Top with remaining pudding and another layer of crackers.
Spoon cherry pie filling on top.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: harry's barbecue pork steak
directions: In saucepan, combine soup mixes, salad dressing and vinegar. Gradually stir in water. Add remaining ingredients except steaks. Bring mixture to boil and let simmer 10 minutes.
Cool.
Marinate steaks overnight for better taste.
Broil over medium heat for 10 to 12 minutes; turn and baste with sauce and broil additional 10 to 12 minutes longer.
Baste both sides before removing.
Enjoy!

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Cream all ingredients, except tortillas and picante sauce, until well blended.
Thinly spread on 12-inch flour tortillas. Roll tortillas and place in refrigerator overnight in sealed container.
When ready to serve, slice rolled tortillas to desired thickness and serve with picante sauce for dipping.

title: tunaroni salad
directions: Mix the following ingredients and pour cabbage mixture:

title: quick mayonnaise rolls
directions: Heat oven to 450°. Grease muffin tins or spray with Pam. Mix ingredients and spoon into muffin tins. Bake 15 minutes until golden.

title: cherry yum yum
directions: Mix
with
mixer
the Dream Whip, sugar, milk and cream cheese until stiff.
Melt margarine and mix with crumbs.	Put a layer of crumbs, a layer of Dream Whip, layer of cherry pie filling and a
layer
of Dream Whip in pan.
Top with rest of crumbs and
let stand
for 1 hour in refrigerator.	Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: barbecue beef sandwiches(sloppy joes)
directions: Brown beef, sausage and onion.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well and simmer for 1 hour or longer.
This recipe can be cooked in a crock-pot.
Brown beef, sausage and onion first.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add fruit.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in mold or dish.
Leave rest of mixture on cabinet.
Refrigerate first partially congealed.
Add rest of mixture.
Return to refrigerator until congealed.
Top with Cool Whip or sour cream, if you wish to serve.

title: baked grits casserole
directions: Add grits to water and salt. Cook 15 minutes. While still hot, stir in oleo and garlic cheese. Stir. Cool 15 or 20 minutes. Then add eggs and mix. Sprinkle top with Fritos. Bake 30 to 45 minutes. Press Fritos down. Use medium pan, 7 x 10.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix together cornstarch, sugar and boiling water and stir well.
Place over medium heat and boil until it thickens.
Add butter, egg yolks, salt, lemon juice and grated rind of lemon. Cook three minutes, then pour into a baked shell.
Cover with meringue and brown.

title: homemade condensed milk
directions: Mix well in blender.
Makes 1 1/4 cups condensed milk.

title: pear dumplings
directions: Combine cornstarch, brown sugar, vanilla, butter

and pear juice in medium sauce pan. Cook until thickened. Roll 1 pear half in 1 crescent roll and place in a buttered 13 X 9 pan. Pour cooked caramel sauce over pear dumplings. Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon. Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes. Serve warm in individual serving dishes and top with ice cream then drizzle sauce over ice cream.

title: dill batter bread
directions: Combine 1 cup flour and the yeast.
Heat and stir cottage cheese, sugar, dill seed, margarine, onion, 1/2 cup water and 1/2 teaspoon salt until warm (120° to 130°) and margarine almost melts.
Add to flour mixture along with egg.
Beat with an electric mixer on low speed for 30 seconds, scraping bowl constantly.
Beat on high speed 3 minutes.

title: sloppy joe hamburgers
directions: Chop the onion and green pepper in small pieces; heat oil over medium heat and add the onion and green pepper. Cook about 5 minutes, don't let them brown. Add the hamburger and continue to cook until pink in hamburger is gone. Stir occasionally to bring the pink meat up from bottom of skillet until all meat is browned. Add the ketchup, salt, pepper. Cook slowly until flavors and ingredients are blended. Simmer for 10 minutes, be sure to stir occasionally. Serve on hamburger buns.

title: blueberry salad(a first prize winner in dallas)
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Drain blueberries and pineapple; measure liquid.
(If necessary, add enough water to make 1 cup liquid and add to jello mixture.)
Stir in drained blueberries and pineapple.
Pour into a 2-quart flat pan.
Cover and put in refrigerator until firm.
Combine cream cheese, sugar, sour cream and vanilla.
Spread over congealed salad.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts (preferably pecans). Serves 10 to 12.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook onion and broccoli in butter until tender. Remove from heat. Add the mushroom soup, rice and cheese.
Season to taste. Put in greased casserole. Dot
with butter.
Cover with cornflakes. Bake about 15 minutes at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Layer can of corn, then green beans, pour celery soup over top.
Mix sour cream with shredded cheese and pour over soup mixture.
Mix ritz crackers with melted margarine and pour over sour cream mixture.
Bake at 350 F for 30 minutes in a 9 x 9 ungreased pan.

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add alternately, while blending the whipping cream and flour.
Add 2 teaspoons vanilla and continue to blend. Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press rolls
in pan and bake according to directions on can. Cool.

title: chilled fresh tomato soup
directions: Wash tomatoes, place on cookie sheet.
Add onion halves. Roast in preheated 400° oven 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool.
Transfer tomatoes to bowl, catching juices.	Slip off skins. Reserve juice. In 2 batches, puree tomatoes and onions in food processor until very smooth.
Heat 2 tablespoons olive oil in heavy soup kettle. Saute garlic until soft; add pureed tomatoes and juice.
Stir in broth and salt.
Bring to a simmer for 15 minutes, uncovered. Remove from heat, stir in cream.
Chill.
In food processor, puree basil and 1/2 cup olive oil.
Serve with basil puree drizzled over each bowl of soup.	Pretty and delicious!

title: lemon chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. With a double-tined cooking fork, pierce lemon almost through all over, 20 to 30 times.
Set aside any juice that leaks out.
Rinse chicken; remove and discard fat. Place lemon and any juice in cavity of chicken; truss with string or metal skewers.
Season with lemon pepper.
Place chicken in small roasting pan; roast 70 minutes.
Remove from oven; let stand covered 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tom's own spaghetti sauce
directions: Saute garlic and onion in olive oil.
Mix tomato paste and water or red wine.
Add to garlic-onion mixture along with remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Roll chicken, ham and cheese together.
Use a toothpick to secure.
Roll in egg and bread crumbs to coat.
Saute in butter. Place in baking dish. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Combine mushrooms, wine, bouillon and water in saucepan.
Simmer.
When half has evaporated, add flour, cream, salt and pepper to taste. Stir until thickened.
Pour over chicken and bake 10 more minutes. Enjoy!

title: five hour stew
directions: Cover and cook 5 hours in oven at 275°.
Don't take lid off.

title: "kota riganato" - baked chicken oregano
directions: Rub chicken with lemon, then oil.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Season generously with oregano and sliced garlic cloves.
Add water (just enough to cover bottom of baking dish). Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and broil last 5 minutes or so until golden brown.

title: crowd-pleasing potato salad
directions: Place potatoes in large bowl.
Separate eggs; chop whites and put in the bowl, along with the onion.
Toss gently.
In another bowl, mash yolks.
Add dressing, cream, vinegar, sugar, mustard and salt.
Pour over potatoes; stir to coat.
Cover and chill.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together and place in casserole dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 300 degrees.
Last 15 minutes sprinkle canned onion rings on top.

title: a.1. chili
directions: In large heavy pot, over high heat, cook beef, green pepper, onion and garlic, stirring frequently, until beef is browned, about 15 minutes.
Stir in chili powder; cook, stirring for 1 minute.

title: fried rice
directions: Heat oil in wok or large skillet over high heat. Add salt. Break eggs into wok and scramble quickly until egg is cooked and in small particles. Add onions and green onions and stir-fry for 2 minutes.

Add bean sprouts and stir-fry for 1 minute. Add remaining ingredients and stir-fry until thoroughly hot. Serve with any Oriental entre or add chicken, pork or beef (already cooked) as you choose for a complete meal.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Bake on greased baking sheet at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.
Be sure baking pan has sides or grease will drip into oven.
Good party food!

title: reuben sandwiches
directions: Take 2 slices of buttered bread to make sandwich and add corned beef, Swiss cheese, dressing and sauerkraut.
Fry in skillet until cheese is melted.

title: jack-o-lantern bread
directions: Combine sugars, pumpkin, oil and eggs; beat until well blended.
Sift together the flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add and mix well.
Stir in raisins, nuts and water.
Bake in loaf pan at 350° for 65 minutes, or until done when tested.

title: german chocolate upside down cake
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 pan.
Line with wax paper and spray. Sprinkle coconut and pecans in bottom of pan; set aside.
Combine cake mix, eggs, water and oil in large bowl; mix according to package directions.
Spoon batter over coconut and pecans. Combine cream cheese and butter in a saucepan; cook over low heat, stirring often until butter melts and mixture is smooth.
Stir in powdered sugar.
Spoon mixture evenly over batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool in pan on a wire rack for 10 minutes; invert onto a serving plate.
Remove and discard wax paper.

title: easy golden punch
directions: In a 1-gallon container, mix all ingredients.
Add enough water to make almost a gallon.
You may also add some ginger ale to this to make it go further (as when pouring it in a punch bowl).

title: squaw bread
directions: Combine dry ingredients in bowl.
Add milk slowly, stirring to form a ball.
Turn dough onto floured surface.
Knead lightly. Roll dough 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Drop into deep hot fat.
Fry until golden brown.

title: aunt jessie's apple pie
directions: Place apples in pie shell, enough to heap up.
Mix cornstarch, sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg together and pour over apples.
Dot with butter.
Place top crust over apples; seal edges. Bake at 400° until apples test done and crust is golden brown.

title: texas cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, eggs, sour cream and soda together. Bring margarine, water and cocoa to a boil.
Add to the dry ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in a 17 x 11 x 1-inch pan (cookie sheet).

title: deviled pecan ball
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients except pecans.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Divide mixture to make 2 balls or maybe leave together to make 1 large ball.
Roll in pecans and chill until ready to serve.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: peppernuts
directions: Heat syrup, sugar, butter and Crisco mixture, bringing mixture to a boil.
Cool mixture to warm.

title: dianne's favorite dessert
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients for pie crust.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
Blend cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread mixture on crust. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Mix pudding by directions.
Pour over cream cheese layer.
Set in fridge until firm.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 12 to 15 (plus) servings.

title: crock-pot bean casserole
directions: Brown together	the
first 3 ingredients; drain and put into crock-pot.	Add
the
remaining ingredients and mix well. Cook on low in crock-pot 4 to 9 hours.

title: autumn apple salad
directions: In a saucepan, combine pineapple juice and sugar.
Boil for 3 minutes.
Add jello; stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese and stir until blended.
Cool.
Fold in apples, nuts, celery and Cool Whip.
Pour into 9-inch square baking pan.
Chill and cut into squares to serve.

title: cheese pumpkin pie
directions: In medium bowl mix cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar, vanilla and 1 egg.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
In medium bowl mix pumpkin, 1/2 cup sugar, cinnamon, salt, milk and 2 eggs.
Mix and pour over cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: oven baked beef stew
directions: Cut meat into 1 inch cubes, sprinkle with salt and pepper, and dredge with flour.
Melt shortening in skillet, and brown meat in it.
Transfer meat to a 2-quart casserole.
Lightly brown onion in hot shortening, add to meat.
Heat water with tomato soup, pour over meat.
Add seasonings and sliced celery.
Cover, bake in 325° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Add sliced carrots, potatoes (cut in eighths), add peas.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper, mix with beef and gravy.
Cover and bake 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: okra medley
directions: Cook okra, squash and carrots with salt in water, enough to cover slightly, covered, for 7 minutes.
Add onion and pepper; cook for 3 or 4 minutes, until all are lightly crisp.
Remove from heat; drain in colander.
Pour in dish and toss with melted margarine.

title: deep-dish meat pie
directions: In medium saucepan, cook potato and onion in butter over medium heat, stirring constantly, for 5 to 6 minutes or until onion is tender, but not brown.
Stir in flour, thyme and 1/8 teaspoon pepper.
Add broth all at once.
Stir in peas and carrots.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Stir in meat.
Transfer mixture to 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with pie crust; trim crust to 1/2-inch beyond rim.
Turn under and flute edges.
Cut slits for steam.
Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes or golden.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 4.

title: no bakes
directions: Bring cocoa, sugar, milk and butter to a full boil, stirring constantly.
Cook 5 minutes until when dropped in cool water, it forms a soft ball.
Take off burner and add oats and peanut butter; stir until it starts to cool.
Spoon off onto wax paper or foil until hardened.

title: scallop-vegetable-stir-fry
directions: Dissolve bouillon cube in 1 cup of boiling water.
Combine cornstarch and 1/4 cup water, stirring well.
Stir into bouillon mixture; set aside.
Bread and brown veggie scallops; cut into 1-inch pieces.
Set aside.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown sirloin, dice whole white potatoes in bite size chunks and pour juice in pan.
Add taco seasoning and Hidden Valley Ranch; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: loaf bread
directions: Add butter, salt and sugar to milk.
Add eggs and yeast dissolved in warm water.
Add flour to this mixture.
Turn out and knead while adding more flour.
Let rise until double in size. Punch down and knead to remove air bubbles.
Divide into 3 loaves. Put in well-greased loaf pans.
Let rise again until double in size.
Bake at 350° until brown, 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hamburger-rice hot dish
directions: Brown hamburger and onions together; drain. Spread into bottom of cake pan or casserole dish. Mix remaining ingredients. Add to the dish. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until rice is done.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients into cream cheese.
Beat with beater until smooth.
Chill 1/2 hour.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Beat together and pour into two greased flour tins.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: zucchini frittata
directions: Slightly beat the eggs.
Combine all the ingredients and mix well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes, until lightly browned.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Combine sugar and butter; melt over low heat.
Cool.
Add an egg at a time; beat well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add.
Add chocolate bits, nuts and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Makes 2 to 3 dozen.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook frozen broccoli as directed on package.
Drain.
Mix all of the ingredients, except cheese crackers.
When you've mixed all the ingredients, then crumble up the cheese crackers and spread or sprinkle them on top of the casserole so top of mixture is covered completely.
Then bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Dressing:
Microwave first 3 ingredients in tall open jar on Auto.
Reheat.
Will separate.
Stir and return to microwave for short time or bring to a boil on stove in a saucepan.
Cool and refrigerate for 30 minutes or longer.

title: hungarian coffeecake
directions: After second rising, cut dough into pieces the size of walnuts. Form into balls.
Roll each ball into melted butter then in the mixture of sugar, cinnamon and walnuts.
Place 1 layer of balls so they barely touch in well-greased tube pan.
Sprinkle with a few raisins.
Add another layer of balls, sprinkle with more raisins, pressing them in slightly.
Let rise 45 minutes.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 375°.
Invert pan so butter-sugar mixture runs down over cake.
To serve, break apart with 2 forks.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Whisk together mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar and set aside. Cut broccoli into florets and combine in large bowl with cheese and bacon.
Toss with mayonnaise.
Cover and chill overnight before serving.

title: chocolate spice cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Combine oleo, shortening, cocoa and water in pan.
Bring to boil, pour this mixture over sugar and flour and stir well.
Add eggs, buttermilk, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: bill rice iii favorite casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles.
Combine with all but last ingredient.
Cover with Pepperidge Farm dressing.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: vermont corn chowder
directions: Cook diced pork, stirring so that pork browns, but not too dry.
Remove from pan.
Saute onion in fat until tender.
Add water, potatoes, corn and salt.
Cook, uncovered, until potatoes are soft.
Add milk.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Taste for seasoning, add a dash of pepper.
May be thickened, if desired. To serve, sprinkle top with salt pork.

title: apple brownies
directions: Melt shortening and beat in sugar and vanilla.
Stir in eggs. Sift dry ingredients and mix them in.
Stir in apples and nuts. Spread in greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut while warm in 2-inch squares.
Makes about 16 brownies.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together and put in baking dish.
Cover with topping.

title: party snack crackers
directions: Put dry ingredients in a plastic bowl and shake; mix well. Add oil and shake.
Let stand overnight.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix syrup, water and sugar together and boil to 250°.
Add remaining ingredients, then pour on cookie sheet.
Will spread by itself.

title: crab casserole
directions: Saute onion in 3 tablespoons of oil until transparent.
Add flour and cook, stirring for 1 minute.
Pour in milk and cook until thickened.
Add celery flakes, orange peel, parsley, green pepper, pimento and Tabasco.
Remove from heat and add sherry. Add a little sauce to beaten egg whites, then add egg mixture to sauce slowly, stirring constantly.
Add pepper and finely cut up crab meat.
This will make 8 individual crab dishes or you can make 1 large casserole.
Sprinkle crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, uncovered.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs, then add sugar, Karo, butter, salt, vanilla and pecans.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: mexican stuffed shells
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Combine picante sauce, water and tomato sauce.
Stir 1/2 cup into ground beef along with chilies, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can French fried onions; mix well.
Pour 1/2 of remaining mixture onto bottom of 10-inch round or 8 x 10-inch baking dish.
Stuff cooked shells with ground beef mixture; arrange in baking dish.
Pour remaining sauce over shells.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and French fried onions.
Bake an additional 5 minutes, uncovered. Serve.

title: old virginia breakfast
directions: Fry bacon; drain.
Make gravy using bacon drippings, flour, salt, milk, and water to desired consistency.
Dip tomatoes in cornmeal and fry.
Make fritters using oil, self-rising flour, cornmeal, egg, and buttermilk.
Fry on hot griddle in thin round cakes or fritters.	On huge platter, place corn fritters, then top with alternate layers of gravy, fried tomatoes, and bacon.	Start the stacking of layers again.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender in water. Bone and skin chicken. Grease casserole. Cook the spaghetti in chicken broth where chicken was cooked. Mix together soups and mushrooms. Layer spaghetti, then chicken. Cover with soup mixture. Use all ingredients, then grated mild Cheddar cheese to cover top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: friendship cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 300° for 1 hour and 25 minutes or until done.
Serve with whipped cream and additional Brandied Fruit if desired.
Freezes well.

title: creamy chicken primavera
directions: In large skillet, brown chicken in butter.
Add vegetables and pasta and water.
Cover and simmer 7 to 9 minutes until vegetables are crisp-tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in sour cream and heat thoroughly.
Preparation time is 20 minutes.

title: vanilla sauce
directions: Combine sugar, salt and flour.
Add water slowly stirring constantly.
Cook over hot water (double boiler), stirring constantly for 8 minutes.
Serve over steamed or baked pudding.

title: ham florentine wreath
directions: Open crescent rolls and roll out flat. Cut into triangles. Arrange triangles to make a double ring or wreath. One package of triangles will have points facing inward. The other package will have points facing out.

title: pistachio squares
directions: Melt oleo.
Add Ritz crackers.
Spread evenly into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat together until well mixed:
1 large can Carnation evaporated milk and 2 boxes instant pistachio pudding.
Add 4 cups softened vanilla ice cream (1/2 of 1/2 gallon).
Pour over cracker crust.
Chill and serve with whipped cream.

title: quick hamburger fix
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until heated through.
Serve over rice or on a baked potato. Serves 4.

title: carrot-apple salad
directions: Mix everything together in a bowl and let marinate in the refrigerator for at least an hour or more.
This softens the raisins and blends the flavors.
Change the ratio of ingredients to suit your taste.
Pineapple can be added or substituted for the apple.
Other good additions are golden raisins, dates or orange sections.

title: hot spiced cider
directions: Combine apple juice, cloves, 2 cinnamon sticks and orange in saucepan.
Bring to boil and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Remove orange slices, cloves and cinnamon sticks.
Stir in Equal.
Pour into mugs.
Garnish with cinnamon sticks if desired. Makes 4 (8 ounce) servings.

title: mississippi mud river
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Immediately after removing from oven, spread 1 (7 ounce) jar marshmallow cream on cake.

title: baked stuffed shrimp
directions: Peel shrimp. Fry garlic and onion. Do not let it brown. Turn off heat, add parsley crackers and crumbs. If consistency is dry add a little water.
Bake shrimp 15 -20 minutes at 400° until pink.
Lay shrimp on pan individually and spread crumb mixture on top.

title: sugarless fudge
directions: In top of double boiler, melt chocolate chips. Remove from heat; add milk, vanilla, salt and nuts. Stir until smooth.
Pour into wax paper lined 8-inch square pan. Chill until firm; cut into small cubes and store in an airtight container.

title: alice's jumbo shells
directions: Cook shells.
Mix dressing, chicken, onions, mayonnaise and peas.
Fill cooled shells with mixture, about 1 tablespoon each shell.
Mix soup with about 3/4 cup water; pour over shells.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Can be microwaved.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix in order.
Grease two bread loaf pans, put waxed paper cut to fit bottom amd grease paper also.
Bake at 350° F.
for 1 hour.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Saute cloves, chopped garlic, onion and bacon.
Put all ingredients in casserole and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix with buttermilk, leaving mixture thick.
Drop from spoon into hot grease.
Cook until brown.

title: hot cocoa cake
directions: Combine the oleo, oil, cocoa and water.
Add the sugar and flours.
Add buttermilk, vanilla and eggs.
Bake in greased 9 x 13-inch pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: moo goo gai pan
directions: Slice chicken in thin pieces.
In medium bowl, mix well the chicken, cornstarch, sherry, ginger and salt.
In a 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat in hot oil, cook walnuts about 3 minutes, stirring constantly.
Spoon onto paper towels.

title: chicken vegetable soup
directions: Cook chicken tender and remove from bone.
Add soup and Veg-All.
Simmer until flavor is just right.

title: mystery pie
directions: Beat egg whites until very stiff.
Beat in baking powder and sugar and beat until very stiff.
Remove from mixer; add vanilla, crushed crackers and nuts.
Pour into pie pan that has been generously greased with margarine.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Let cool 30 minutes and pour whipped cream on.
Set in refrigerator until served.

title: carrot relish
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate; keeps 2 weeks if kept cold.

title: best harvard beets
directions: Combine all ingredients except beets in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add beets. Cook on low until beets are heated through.

title: seafood salad
directions: Break meat into small pieces in a medium sized bowl.
Add all other ingredients and toss.
Serve with crackers, as a sandwich or eat plain.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add 2 remaining ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Chill until set. Cut into 2-inch squares and serve with Cool Whip on top.

title: mary's italian cream cheese cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco.
Add sugar; beat until mixture is smooth.
Add eggs; beat well.
Combine dry ingredients.
Add to mixture, alternating with buttermilk.
Stir in vanilla and flavoring.
Add nuts.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour batter into 3 greased and floured 8-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with cream cheese frosting.
Sprinkle with chopped nuts.

title: yummy crackers
directions: Place crackers in large roaster, deep enough so mixture can be stirred easily.	Pour hot oil over crackers.
Sprinkle remaining
ingredients
over this portion.	Stir.
Bake 1 hour at 225°.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: pedro's favorite brownies
directions: Mix together in a large bowl the chocolate cake mix, egg and oil.
Put half of mixture into greased 8 x 8-inch baking pan and press lightly into pan.

title: cracklin' bread(from the kitchen of mom beatrice taylor.)
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour in greased pan. Bake at 250° for about 10 minutes. Turn oven up to 275° and cook until brown.

title: sour cream potatoes
directions: Saute the onion in butter, add parsley, cook slowly, add sale and pour over potatoes in a casserole dish.
Mix in the sour cream lightly and top with the cheese.
Cover and bake at 350 degrees until it bubbles or the cheese is melted.

title: chicken and biscuits casserole
directions: Use one 2 1/2 or 3 lean chicken fryers, cut up.
Boil about 20 minutes.
Mix Crisco, 1/4 cup Bisquick, salt, pepper and milk. Put on to boil for a couple of minutes. Line chicken in a casserole for baking.
Add gravy mix over chicken real good.

title: chinese lobster sauce
directions: In a wok, brown the hamburger.
Drain fat.
Add beaten eggs, garlic and sugar.
Mix well.
To the dissolved bouillon cubes, add the cornstarch, soy sauce, ginger and Gravy Master and pour over meat mixture.
Simmer for 10 minutes, uncovered.

title: pineapple delight
directions: Boil sugar and pineapple in saucepan for five minutes.
