Dissolve lemon Jell-O in one cup cold water; pour into hot mixture.
Add cheese and nuts.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into mold; let set.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt butter.
Stir in sugar, vinegar and eggs.
Add coconut, raisins and pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: cheap quick coffee cake
directions: Bake 10 minutes in large floured cookie sheet.

title: southern banana nut cake
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add sugar, butter and oil.
Sift dry ingredients into wet mixture.
Stir in bananas, raisins and nuts. Beat thoroughly.
Bake in tube (flat Bundt) at 275° for 2 hours. Do not preheat oven.

title: lemon delight cake
directions: Mix well and bake in greased, floured pan at 350° for approximately 30 to 40 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Slice zucchini 1/4 inch thick.
Parboil for 10 minutes; drain well.
Grease 2-quart casserole with margarine.
Put half of squash in dish.
Add 1/2 can cream of mushroom soup and half of medium onion, diced.
Cover with 1/2 cup grated Cheddar cheese and salt and pepper to taste.
Add other half of squash and repeat layers. Top with 1 cup crumbled cheese crackers.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: caramel apple dip
directions: Bring brown sugar and oleo to boil; let cool completely.
Beat in cream cheese.
Add vanilla.
Serve with sliced apples.

title: easy bake pork chops
directions: Place pork chops in long baking dish.
Sprinkle all ingredients over them.
Spread on sauce.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: dip for fruit tray
directions: Cook ingredients until they are thick.
Let completely cool in refrigerator overnight.
Next day fold in Cool Whip.
Ready to serve as a dip for any fruit.

title: kansas fried steaks
directions: In shallow dish beat eggs with milk. Dip steaks in mixture; coat with flour seasoned with salt and pepper. In large skillet, over medium high heat, saute steaks in oil and butter, turning once; cook 5 minutes for medium rare. Remove to serving platter; spoon milk gravy over steaks.

title: cioppino
directions: *Peeled, cleaned shrimp, sea bass, sword fish, lobster meat or scallops, any firm fish will do.

title: fudge cake
directions: Cream the margarine with the sugar. Beat in the eggs, one at a time. Add chocolate syrup, flour and baking powder.
Bake in a 13 x 9 1/2-inch oblong pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Leave cake in pan and while still hot, spread marshmallows and pecans on top.
Have the sauce ready and spread over cake.
Chill overnight.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower into small pieces.
Add frozen peas.
Mix in dry Good Seasons dressing mix.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Add shredded Cheddar cheese.
Moisten with Miracle Whip salad dressing.

title: c.h.s. home economics department's delicious angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm (not hot) water.
Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender until mixture looks "crumbly".
Stir in yeast and buttermilk; mix well.
Roll out onto floured surface.
Cut with biscuit cutter. Place on baking sheet.
Bake at 500° until brown (about 10 minutes).
May store dough in refrigerator in covered container up to a week and use as needed.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in two cooked and cooled pie shells (prefer deep dish shells).
You may substitute graham cracker crust.
Makes 2 pies.

title: delicious macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil noodles al dente (slightly undercooked).
Melt Velveeta cheese with milk in heavy, nonstick pan.
Add one cup Cheddar cheese, mixing until all melted.
Drain noodles well.
Mix noodles and cheese thoroughly.
Pour into one or more casseroles (or freezing containers).
Sprinkle top(s) with remaining Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: new potato
directions: Cook potatoes for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cube them.
Pour dressing over them while warm.
Mix in green onion and salt and pepper to taste.
Garnish with sliced black olives.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix well.
Pour in an unbaked pie shell and bake at 300° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: glazed popcorn
directions: Place popcorn in large bowl.
Heat butter and syrup in small saucepan over low heat.
Stir in brown sugar and gelatin; bring to a boil over medium heat.
Reduce heat to low and gently simmer for 5 minutes.
Pour syrup immediately over popcorn, tossing to coat well.
Spread popcorn into aluminum foil lined 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan, using forks to spread evenly.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Remove from pan and break into small pieces. Makes 2 quarts.

title: chocolate pie(makes enough for two frozen crusts)
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa.
Then with mixer, mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no bake lemon pie
directions: Mix well and pour into pie shells.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Marinate chicken, chilies and salsa for at least 2 hours.
In shallow pan or plate, dip tortillas in whipping cream to soften. Fill with chicken mix and roll.
(You can add some cheese inside too.)
Place rolled tortillas in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1 1/2 cups cheese and leftover whipping cream.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: easy fixed baked beans
directions: Mix all together in pan.
Bake, uncovered, in 325° oven for 2 1/2 hours or in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cream beef, cheese, sharp cheese, Worcestershire sauce, pickle relish, Tabasco sauce and onion salt. Mix well; form into ball and roll in parsley or cracker crumbs. Serves 12 to 15.

title: 60 minute yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Place sugar, milk, salt and butter in pan.
Heat until lukewarm.
Cool.
Add yeast and flour.
Put in warm place for 15 minutes or until you see risen twice its size. Turn out on floured board.
Roll 3/4-inch thickness.
Cut with cutter and place on cookie sheet.
Turn in 1/2.
Butter 1/2.
Let rise again 15 minutes (or double in size).
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: parmesan chicken(yields 6 to 8 servings)
directions: Combine bread crumbs, parsley flakes, cheese, salt, pepper and garlic powder.

title: glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 425 degrees.
Cut sweet potatoes into 1/2 inch thick slices; place in a 1-quart casserole coated with cooking spray.
Combine cornstarch and next 3 ingredients in a bowl; stir well.
Pour over potatoes.
Cover; bake at 425 degrees for 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Yields:
5 servings, (1/2 cup), 2 points.

title: taco pie
directions: Bake pie shell in 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven. Set oven on 350°.
In skillet, brown meat and onion drain well. Add seasoning to meat.
In small bowl, combine refried beans, 1/3 cup taco sauce and mix well.
Layer 1/2 bean mixture in pie crust; top with half of meat and 1 cup of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Bake on cookie sheet 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven, slice as pie. Top with tomatoes and lettuce.

title: hot spice tea
directions: To make good tea, use plenty of water.
Pour boiling water over tea twice, steeping 3 to 5 minutes each time.
No extra water will be needed.

If tea is sweetened with sugar or saccharin when made, it can be stored when cool in refrigerator without clouding. The native tea countries make tea with cold water; let it steep in sunshine several hours.
Will not cloud unsweetened in refrigerator.

title: classic sour cream cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine crumbs and margarine; press firmly on bottom of 9-inch baking dish.
In large bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk, eggs, sour cream and vanilla.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes or until lightly browned around edge.
(Center will be slightly soft.) Cool.
Chill.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: rice beef casserole
directions: Brown beef; cook rice according to directions.
Add these ingredients along with the rest of the ingredients in a casserole dish.
Place cheese on top and put in oven until cheese is melted.

title: ham salad puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In saucepan, heat water and butter to rolling boil.
Stir in flour.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball, about 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, all at once, until smooth and glossy.
Drop dough by slightly rounded teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake for about 25 minutes, or until puffed, golden brown and dry.
Place on wire rack.
Cool.
Cut off tops.
Remove soft dough.
Fill each puff with rounded teaspoon of ham salad.
Makes 5 or 6 dozen.

title: plain and pleasing
directions: Pat out 4 equal sized patties.
Place in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch dish.
Broil 10 minutes on each side.
Mix gravy according to package directions.
Pour over broiled patties.
Place onion and potato slices on top.
Cover; bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour, baking soda, and cinnamon.
Stir in the oats.
Combine egg whites, brown sugar, oil, milk, vanilla and raisins and add flour mixture.
Mix well.
Drop batter, a teaspoon at a time on to an oiled cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes, depending on texture desired.
Shorter baking time equals softer cookie.
Longer baking time equals crisper cookie.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: sugar-free cheese cake
directions: Combine first 2 ingredients.
Press into an 8 x 8-inch pan. Chill.
Dissolve Jell-O in 1 cup boiling water and cool.
In a blender thoroughly mix the cottage cheese until smooth.
(May use processor instead of blender.)
Slowly add Jell-O and blend well. Pour into crust and chill until set.
Slice fresh berries or frozen on top and let set at least an hour.
Serve.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Blend all ingredients except brown sugar and nuts in large mixing bowl.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Spoon hot butter glaze over warm cake.

title: chicken breast bake
directions: Put bacon around chicken and brown in butter. Place dried beef, cut up, in greased pan. Put chicken on top with bacon. Blend soup and sour cream. Add mushrooms with liquid. Pour mixture over chicken. Cover with foil and bake at 270° for 3 hours.

title: spinach and pepperoni quiche
directions: In medium skillet, cook red pepper in hot oil until it is tender. Drain.
Separate rolls into triangles.
Press rolls over bottom and 3/4-inch up sides of a 9 or 9 1/2-inch quiche dish, pressing dough together well at the perforations.

title: spiced muscadine grapes
directions: Wash grapes and slip pulp from the skins of grapes.
Steam pulp over hot water in double boiler until they can be mashed through a coarse sieve or food mill to remove seeds.
Combine skins and pulp.
Add vinegar, sugar and spices (tied loosely in a cheesecloth bag and lightly pounded).
Cook together until very thick.
Remove spice bag.
Pack into hot pint jars leaving 1/2 inch headspace.
Wipe jar mouths and adjust lids.
Process in boiling water bath canner for 5 minutes.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes.
Serve over noodles, rice or mashed potatoes.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Toss together and bake in greased pan 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In a heavy saucepan, heat sugar, syrup, water and salt to a rolling boil, add peanuts.
Reduce heat to medium and stir constantly.
Cook until syrup spins a thread (293°).
Add butter, then baking soda.
Beat rapidly and pour on a buttered surface spreading to 1/4-inch thickness.
When cool, break into pieces.

title: stove top macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni; drain and set aside.
In a medium size pan melt margarine.
Stir in flour, salt, Worcestershire sauce and mustard. Cook, uncovered, for 30 seconds.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook, uncovered, for about 3 minutes.
Stir in cheese until melted.
Add cooked macaroni to sauce and continue to cook for 3 to 4 minutes, until macaroni is hot.

title: good and easy stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cover and cook at low setting for 10 to 12 hours.
If desired, thicken gravy.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and fruit (reserve pineapple juice).
Combine Tang and pudding with pineapple juice.
Combine fruits and dressing.
Chill well.

title: cheese cake
directions: Make crust.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Let cool.

title: petite strawberry shortcake
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt; set aside. Cream together the shortening and sugar until light and fluffy using an electric mixer at medium speed.
Add eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Alternately add dry ingredients and milk to creamed mixture, beating well with an electric mixer on low speed after each addition.
Spoon batter into paper-lined 3-inch muffin pan cups.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until done.

title: easy sweet pickles
directions: Pour juice from pickles.
Slice pickles.
Return sliced pickles to jar.
Cover with the sugar.
When sugar begins to melt, invert jar.
Turn jar twice a day for 3 days.
Pickles may then be put into smaller jars.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Boil sweet potatoes until done.
Cool and peel.
Slice in half and arrange in baking dish.
Pour sugar over potatoes.
Drizzle syrup on top.
Cover with pats of butter.
Sprinkle very lightly with salt.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: red snapper
directions: Cook garlic, butter, mushrooms and peas together in wok or deep pan until sauce is clear.
Add scallions and stir.
Cook over fish and serve over dish of prepared wild rice.

title: crab imperial
directions: Remove all cartilage from crab meat.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Cream butter; beat in sugar, vanilla, flour and pecans.
Roll in palm of hand the size of butter ball.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Melt oleo.
Combine with all cracker crumbs.
Put 1/2 crumbs into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pat over bottom.
Chill.
Stir candy bar crumbs into other 1/2 cracker crumbs.
Combine milk and instant pudding; chill until set.
Add ice cream; stir until mixed well. Chill.
Pour over crumbs in pan.
Spread Cool Whip on top. Sprinkle remaining crumbs over top.
Chill.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies in blender until it resembles dirt; set aside. Cream together cream cheese, oleo and powdered sugar; set aside. Mix pudding with milk, then fold into cream cheese mixture.
Add whipped topping.
Alternate layers of cookie crumbs and pudding mixture; be sure to finish with "dirt" cookie mixture on top. Chill several hours.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Chop onions and garlic and cook in salad oil.
Put in spices, sugar, salt and sliced tomatoes.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Put in jar and seal up.
Brown 1 pound hamburger and use for spaghetti sauce.

title: new england clam chowder
directions: Fry bacon and onion together until lightly browned.
Add clam liquor and potatoes.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Add clams.
Cool chowder for a few minutes, then return to heat.
Add milk in a slow stream, stirring constantly.
Add salt and pepper and continue stirring until chowder is hot, but not boiling.
Garnish with parsley.
Add a small lump of butter to each individual soup bowl and serve.
Serves 6.

title: french (egg) pancakes (crepes)(tomahawk's version of crepe suzette)
directions: Mix thoroughly until smooth, using just enough milk to make batter a little thicker than heavy cream.
Fry in shortening or cooking oil over high heat.
(Pour about 1/4 cup of batter in center of a 10-inch heavy skillet, tilting pan so that batter forms a thin layer over entire bottom of pan.)
Fry for about 1/2 minute or until light brown and edges start to curl.
Flip over and fry for another 1/4 minute.
Spread with about a tablespoon of butter, let melt and sprinkle with sugar.
Roll up and enjoy!

title: hot red cabbage
directions: Heat oil.
Add all ingredients and cook until apples are tender.

title: fried chicken
directions: Mix salt, pepper, oregano, garlic, bread crumbs and cheese. Beat eggs and milk.
Dip the chicken pieces in the egg-milk mixture; roll in seasoned bread crumbs.
Heat oil in a skillet and fry the chicken pieces over medium heat until golden brown.
Place in a roasting pan and bake, uncovered, at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Cut potatoes in half and scoop out the pulp.
Place in mixer and whip until smooth.
Add butter (as much as you like), milk to moisten and cheese to taste.
More the better.
Beat until well mixed and place back into skins.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes and garnish with shredded American cheese.
Bake several more minutes until cheese melts.

title: frozen slaw
directions: Mix and boil for 1 minute.
Let cool; pour over cabbage.
Put in container to freeze.
Does not turn dark.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: In microwave, cook sausage 4 minutes, stirring halfway through cooking time.
Break into pieces and drain well.
Add other ingredients and stir well.
Cook on full power for 14 minutes, stirring halfway through.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix together; roll into small balls and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
These freeze well before baking.

title: fruit-crab cocktail
directions: Alternate crab meat and grapefruit sections in lettuce-lined glasses.
Combine mayonnaise, catsup, lemon juice and hot pepper sauce.
Chill.
Pour over crab and grapefruit.
Makes 8 servings.

title: life's recipe
directions: Mix thoroughly and add tears of joy and sorrow and sympathy for others.
Flavor with love.
Fold in 4 cups of prayer and faith to lighten other ingredients and raise the mixture to greater heights of living.
After pouring all of this into your daily life, bake well with the heat of human kindness.
Serve with a smile.

title: stew "n" cornbread bake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Empty stew into 2-quart baking dish. In mixing bowl, beat egg.
Add oil, milk and corn meal.
Mix thoroughly.
Stir in cheese, green onions and pepper.
Pour batter over stew.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: apple goodie
directions: Sift together sugar, flour, salt and cinnamon and combine with sliced apples. Mix together well and place in greased pan.

title: cucumber potatoes
directions: Mix together cucumbers, onion, salt and pepper.
Let stand 1 or 2 hours.
Brown bacon; add hot bacon to vinegar.
Cook potatoes and mash.
Squeeze out juice from the cucumbers and add to the hot mashed potatoes.
Then add the hot bacon vinegar mixture to the potatoes.

title: noodles alfredo
directions: Cook noodles according to directions and drain.
Meanwhile, heat margarine or butter with half and half in saucepan over low heat, just until the butter is melted.
Stir in all ingredients except noodles.
Heat 5 minutes, do not boil.
Toss sauce with noodles.
Serve immediately.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: jello salad
directions: Combine ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Use for a side dish or dessert.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix together in a bowl with ice cubes to chill.
Just before serving, add 2 large bottles of ginger ale.

title: herbed new potatoes
directions: Steam halved potatoes, covered, over boiling water until fully cooked, about 15 minutes.
Test potatoes for doneness using a skewer to avoid splitting them.
Toss potatoes with melted butter, herbs, and salt until coated.
Serve hot.

title: country pie
directions: Mix beef, bread crumbs, onions, green peppers, seasonings and 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Spread in greased 9 or 10-inch pan.
Mix rice, cheese and remaining sauce.
Sprinkle top with additional cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until done.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: cucumbers and vinegar
directions: Cover cucumbers with cold water and sprinkle salt over them. Let set for 1/2 hour.
Drain.
Then press with paper towels.
Mix sugar and vinegar and pour over cucumbers.
Sprinkle with pepper. Add onion.
Best when refrigerated 2 to 3 hours before serving.

title: jan's banana bread
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients until fluffy.
Add yogurt and bananas.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Mix until just moist. Pour into 9 x 5 x 3 pan.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: flag cake
directions: Cut pound cake or angel food cake into 1-inch thick slices. Line the bottom of a 12 x 8-inch dish (glass) with cake slices. Top with blueberries and strawberries, then a layer of Cool Whip. Arrange strawberry halves and blueberries to the likings of a flag. Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Makes 15 servings.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, salsa, sour cream and taco seasoning together until creamy.
Place in refrigerator until firm.
Best made the night before.
Right before you serve it, top with chopped lettuce, onion and Monterey Jack or Cheddar cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Combine tuna, onion, soup, peas and corn if used.
Mix together well.
Add cheese last.
Put noodles in after the cheese.
Once mixture is together, salt to taste.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Put crumbled chips on top before baking.

title: onion casserole
directions: Saute sliced onions in margarine.
Put all in casserole. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes or 1/2 hour in 350° oven.

title: pinwheels
directions: Select the crisp white tender stalks of celery.
Wash with a brush.
Fill with a highly flavored cheese which has been creamed until smooth, combined with mayonnaise and beaten until light and fluffy.
Chill well before serving.
Creamed cheese works good like Philadelphia creamed with chives.

title: mama's pound cake(maggie gardner)
directions: Cream
sugar
and
butter
until fluffy; add egg yolks, salt and
flavoring.
Beat egg whites until stiff;
alternate with flour.
Fold into batter of sugar, butter and eggs.
Bake in greased
and floured tube pan approximately 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: squirrel in gravy
directions: Cut each squirrel into 4 pieces.
Place the pieces in a cooking pot and cover with water.
Add salt, pepper and the bay leaf and cook until tender.
Remove squirrel from the pot and roll each piece in flour.
Bring the stock to a boil again and add the floured squirrel and the garlic.
Add margarine and cook until thickened to a gravy.
Serve over rice.

title: pizza by the scoop
directions: Spread cream cheese on 12-inch pizza pan.
Spread with chili sauce.
Sprinkle with ham, onion, green pepper, cheeses and tomato.
Serve with Scoop Fritos.

title: barbecue
directions: Fry hamburger and onion.
Mix sugar, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Add to drained hamburger and onion; simmer about 20 minutes.

title: cherry and pineapple fruit cobbler
directions: Pour canned fruits with juice into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Sprinkle cake mix over fruit evenly.
Pour margarine over, then sprinkle with coconut and nuts.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Quick and easy!

title: cherry pudding
directions: Mix first three ingredients real well.
Add rest of ingredients into the first three ingredients.
Add cherries in last.
Mix by hand.
Grease and flour bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet and sour sauerkraut
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt butter in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add onion and apples; saute until softened, 3 to 8 minutes.
Combine onion and apples with sauerkraut in large mixing bowl.
Stir in tomatoes, brown sugar and wine.
Season with caraway seed and black pepper.
Transfer mixture to a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake 1 hour.
Uncover and bake another 1/2 hour.
Serve as a side dish.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix all together; refrigerate.
Before serving, add salt and pepper to taste, bacon bits and salad dressing.

title: ernie's quick and easy chili
directions: Brown ground meat; stir in tomatoes, onions, sauce and contents of your favorite chili seasoning.
(Mine is Texas chili; Brother Tommy McLean prefers his hot, so add extra crushed red pepper for him, but can also be either mild or medium.)
Bring to a boil; simmer 20 minutes, if time allows and you aren't hungry by now. You can place mixture in crock-pot and cook slowly.
The longer it cooks the better it tastes.
Kidney beans can be added for a variation or to serve a larger amount.

title: skillet supper
directions: Place diced Spam in large skillet or pot that has been coated with spray coating or margarine.
Add green pepper and onion. Saute until onion is clear.
Add tomatoes and rice.
Mix well. Add water as needed until rice is done.
Serve hot.
Use medium heat while cooking and cover with a lid.
You may add your spices, if you like.

title: overnight ham sandwiches
directions: Trim bread crusts.
Butter both sides of bread.
Make 6 sandwiches with buttered bread and ham.
Place close together in a long buttered Pyrex dish.
Sprinkle grated cheese over sandwiches. Add beaten eggs, milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Cover with foil tightly; refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before baking.
Uncover; bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cut into 3 x 3-inch squares.
It puffs up like a souffle.

title: fettucini with garlic and clam sauce
directions: Saute onion and garlic in olive oil for a couple of minutes on low heat.
Add wine and clam juice.
Reduce by 1/4.
Add cream and simmer until reduced by one-half its volume.
Add clams, salt and pepper.
Combine with fettucini.
Garnish with basil and Parmesan cheese.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chewy oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix in order given. Pour into a large buttered cookie sheet. Flour hands and press dough out evenly over sheet about 1/4-inch thick. Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 375°. Cut into squares while warm.

title: class recipe
directions: One tablespoon of girls.
Toss in a teacher.
Stir for 40 seconds.
Add a cup of math facts, 1 cup of brains, 15 cups of Science.
Let it cook in stove for one hour.
Take it out and enjoy.

title: seven flavor pound cake
directions: Sift flour and baking powder together.
Cream butter and margarine with sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well with mixer.
Add flour and milk alternately and beat well after adding each ingredient.
Fold in flavorings with spoon; do not beat. Grease and flour tube pan.
Pour in pan and place in 350° oven. Do not preheat oven.
Bake for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Do not open oven before 1 hour has passed.
Test cake with toothpick.
If toothpick comes out clean, cake is done.

title: baked sauerkraut and pork spareribs
directions: Broil spareribs on both sides to brown.
Pour off drippings. Put spareribs in bottom of a large Dutch oven.
Put potatoes on top of spareribs.
Spread sauerkraut on top of potatoes.
Scatter brown sugar evenly on top of sauerkraut.
Add 1/2 can water.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Bake until spareribs fall off one.
Feeds 4 people.

title: double chocolate cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, beat butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Stir together flour, cocoa, baking soda and salt; add to butter mixture.
Stir in chocolate morsels and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes or just until set.
Cool slightly and remove from cookie sheet to wire rack.
Cool completely.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen.

title: fruit juice sippers
directions: You will also need 6 straws and 6 zipper-top pint-sized freezer bags.

title: jiffy cake dessert
directions: Mix Jiffy cake mix according to directions, using 1/2 cup pineapple juice instead of liquid.
Bake as directed and cool completely.
Mix pudding, cream cheese and milk and layer on cooled cake.
Layer crushed pineapple on cake next.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: orange blossom muffins
directions: Combine egg, sugar, orange juice and salad oil.
Add biscuit mix and beat vigorously for 10 seconds.
Stir in marmalade and pecans.

title: honey oat bran muffins
directions: Baking Temperature: 400°.
Baking Time: 18 to 20 minutes.

title: baptist pound cake
directions: Beat together shortening, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well after each addition.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together and add alternately with milk to first mixture.
Add flavoring.
Grease and flour a Bundt pan or a 10-inch tube pan.
Place in cold oven.
Turn to 350° and bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand for 3 to 5 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Melt butter in 13 x 9 1/2-inch pan. Sprinkle brown sugar evenly in pan.
Arrange pineapple slices on sugar.
Add cake mix, mixed according to directions on box.
Bake for 45 to 55 minutes.
Turn upside down on platter.

title: broccoli-cheez casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli in refrigerator or microwave or pour boiling water over it and let sit for 5 to 8 minutes. Drain broccoli and combine with all other ingredients. Place in greased casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: double chocolate crumble bars
directions: Cream butter
and
sugar.
Beat
in
eggs
and vanilla. Stir together flour, nuts, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Mix well and spread
in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to
20 minutes.
Remove
from oven and spread marshmallows evenly on top. Bake about 3 minutes more.
Cool.

title: beef casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and place in a heavy, covered casserole dish.
Bake in a 325° to 350° oven for about 2 1/2 hours.
Stir 2 or 3 times during baking time.
Add more water if needed.

title: the "now famous" cheese ring
directions: Combine all ingredients except preserves and mix well.
Chill and mold into ring or ball with deep indentation in the middle. Fill with strawberry preserves and serve with crackers.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Add to cooked and well drained mashed squash. Add remainder of ingredients.
Mix together.
Pour in greased casserole dish and top with crumbled Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spinach rice casserole
directions: Put spinach in microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes.
Drain. Add small chopped onions.
Set this aside and mix milk, eggs (beaten), rice, cheese (cubed), salt and pepper.
Put in microwave on High until cheese starts to melt.
Stir one time, then put in microwave for another 5 minutes.
Mix cheese sauce and spinach together.
Put back in microwave for another 10 to 12 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix eggs, broccoli, corn and onion with 1 cup herb stuffing. (If too dry, add a little milk.)
Pour into casserole (2-quart greased) and sprinkle with other cup of stuffing.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: green river punch
directions: Place Kool-Aid in punch bowl.
Add pineapple juice.
Mix well. Spoon in sherbet and pour ginger ale over.
Yields: 35 punch cups.

title: mandarin orange pork
directions: Brown pork.
Drain oranges.
Reserve 1/2 cup juice.
Combine reserved juice with rest of ingredients, except oranges.
Mix until completely blended.
Add oranges.
Drain excess fat from pork cubes.
Pour orange sauce over pork.
Cover and simmer gently 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: barb taft's butter cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Spread in 10 x 15-inch jelly roll pan.
Mix next 3 ingredients and pour over top.
Bake 25 minutes or until top is light brown.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: shrimp and asparagus casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spread cooked rice in buttered baking dish, 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inches.
Spread asparagus over rice. Cover with shrimp.
Melt butter; stir in flour and cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in milk and cheese.
Bring to boil; boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Season to taste with salt and paprika.
Pour sauce over shrimp in baking dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 20 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well and shape into ball.
Roll ball in parsley flakes, chopped fresh parsley, finely chopped nuts or paprika.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: molded vegetable salad
directions: Dissolve jell-o and salt in boiling water.
Add cold water and vinegar; chill until partially set.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 4 c. mold that has been lightly coated with non-stick spray.
Chill until firm.
Serves 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and chop. Mix sour cream and soup together, then mix with the chicken. Crumble the crackers and add the butter that has been melted. Mix and put on top of mixture. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: turkey tofu loaf
directions: Mash together turkey, tofu and egg until well blended.
Very finely mince vegetables.
You can use a food processor.
Combine vegetables and seasoning and mash; mix well.
Spread in a baking pan sized anywhere from 8 x 8-inch to 9 x 12-inch.
Grate the cheese, mix with bread crumbs and melted margarine; drizzle over the mixture.
Sprinkle bread crumb mixture over top of bread loaf. It may be quite thick.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until it pulls away from the sides and is golden brown on top.
Cut into 8 pieces.

title: texas smothered steak
directions: Saute meat
in oil until brown on all sides.
Add onion and garlic;
cook
minutes longer.
Stir in tomatoes, broth and seasonings.
Cover	and
simmer
for
45 minutes, or until meat is tender.
If
desired, thicken gravy.
Serve over beds of fluffy rice.
Makes 6 servings.

title: party potatoes
directions: Boil peeled potatoes until tender.
Beat sour cream and cream cheese together; add hot potatoes and beat until creamy.
Add oleo, chives, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour into a well-greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Dot with oleo; sprinkle paprika on top. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: green pepper squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, pepper, onion, salt, pepper and cheese together. Pour in a buttered casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs and sliced butter.
Bake in a 350 degree oven for 20 minutes or until golden brown and bubbly.

title: pat-a-pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Separate the dough into 10 sections. Place on a cookie sheet.
Pat each one into a circle.
Spread a spoonful of sauce on each circle.
Top with cheese and your favorite toppings.
Bake until light brown (about 10 minutes).

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Place chicken in Dutch oven and cover with water; add bay leaves.
Bring to boil.
Cook, uncovered, until juices run clear. Remove chicken and cut in cubes.
Place chicken and next 11 ingredients.
Mix.	Place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Yield:
16 servings.

title: fettucine with pepper sauce
directions: Cut chicken into strips.
Stir-fry for 3 to 4 minutes: broccoli, pepper and onion in oil.
Remove from skillet.
Stir-fry chicken until no longer pink.
Add soup, water and seasonings to skillet; mix thoroughly.
Stir in vegetables.
Bring to boiling, reduce heat.
Add cheese; cook and stir until cheese is just melted.
Serve over hot cooked pasta.

title: tangy skillet potato salad
directions: In medium skillet, combine soup, milk, relish, vinegar, onion, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir until boiling.
Stir in potatoes and franks.
Heat through.
Top with snipped parsley, if desired. Serves 4 or 5.

title: apricot and pineapple dessert
directions: Combine pineapple and gelatin in a small saucepan; stir over low heat until gelatin is dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar, baby food and cream cheese.
Mix well, but do not beat. Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in whipped topping and spoon into an 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle with pecans and chill until firm. Yields 8 servings.

title: carrot souffle
directions: Drain carrots and pour into food processor or blender to puree in 2 or 3 batches.
(Just mash if you do not have a food processor.)
Melt butter in 2 qt. casserole dish.
Pour carrots into a large mixing bowl.
Add all ingredients and mix well.
Pour souffle into dish used to melt butter.
Bake at 400 degrees for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350 degrees and bake for 40 more minutes.

title: cheese scalloped potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water, salted, until tender.
Drain. Combine soup, sour cream sauce mix, milk, salt and pepper.
Place half of the potatoes in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Top with half the soup mixture.
Repeat with remaining potatoes and soup mixture.
Combine melted butter and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle on top.
Cover and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Uncover and bake for an additional 10 to 30 minutes.

title: lennie's soup
directions: Bring all
ingredients to a boil.
Reduce to simmer and cook about
or
3 hours or until tender.
When done, remove meat and bones.
Cut meat into bite-size pieces and return to pot. Discard
bones, skin and fat.
Freeze any remaining soup in single-serving containers for future meals. Serve with hot cornbread.	Makes 12 bowls full.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: diet cranberry poppy seed muffins
directions: Lightly spray a 12-cup muffin pan or use paper muffin cups. Stir together flour, oat bran, cranberries, sugar, baking powder and poppy seeds in large bowl.
Make a well in center.
In another medium bowl, whisk remaining ingredients and pour into the well in the flour in the large bowl.
Stir enough to moisten flour.
Do not overmix.
Batter should be lumpy.
Fill muffin cups about half full.
Bake at 375° for 14 to 15 minutes or until toothpick inserted in middle of muffin comes out clean.
Remove from oven and cool.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: tortellini soup
directions: In a large 5-quart pan, bring chicken broth to a boil.
Add celery and carrot.
Cook until veggies are tender.
Add spinach and tortellini.
Continue cooking until pasta floats.

title: pork chops creole
directions: Saute pork chops until brown.
Add all other ingredients. Cover and simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: sour cream dressing
directions: Stir vinegar and milk together.
Add sugar, a little at a time.
Stir in salad dressing until smooth and creamy texture.

title: helen's leftover pork
directions: Julienne pork.
Add to soy sauce, ginger and mustard.
Toss and set aside.
Slice onion.
Brown pork about 6 minutes.
Add onion.
Cook about 2 to 3 more minutes.
Add pineapple and bring to a boil.

title: green chili casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, salt and pepper. Drain. Add soup, sour cream and green chilies.
Heat thoroughly.
Crumble the Doritos into casserole dish and stir in ground beef mixture.
Top with grated cheese and bake at 400° until cheese melts.

title: simple beef 'n noodles
directions: Mix instant gravy as directed and add soup.
Mix well on low heat, then add roast beef.
Simmer, uncovered, in saucepan for 10 to 15 minutes.
Pour over cooked noodles.

title: prize winning chocolate balls
directions: In a heavy 2-quart saucepan melt chocolate bar pieces over low heat, stirring often.
Cool to room temperature.
Fold in Cool Whip (mixture will thicken).
Cover and chill at least 1 hour. Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in crumbs.
Chill thoroughly.
Makes 66 balls.

title: hermit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks well beaten.
Sift flour with cinnamon twice, then add to creamed mixture.
Dissolve baking soda in lemon juice and add to mixture.
Beat well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Stir in walnuts, dates and vanilla. Bake in a wax paper lined tube pan at 250° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours or until baked through.

title: corncob jelly
directions: Wash corncobs good (cut both ends off the cob to be sure there are no insects in the cobs).
Place the cobs in large container and completely cover them with water.
Boil 30 minutes.
Remove cobs and strain juice through a heavy cloth.
Mix 3 cups of the juice with the sugar and pectin.
Boil following directions on pectin package.

title: tex-mex dip
directions: Peel, pit and mash avocados in medium bowl with lemon juice, salt and pepper. Combine sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning in bowl.

title: grapefruit zinger
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend at high speed until foamy.
Pour into tall glasses and serve.
Makes 4 (8-ounce) servings.

title: chess bars
directions: Mix cake mix, margarine, vanilla and one egg together and press in greased pan.
Mix sugar, two eggs and cream cheese together and pour over mix in pan.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°. Cut into squares.

title: cooked chocolate fudge frosting
directions: Combine sugar, milk, corn syrup and chocolate squares and cook to soft ball (234°).
Add margarine and vanilla.
Cool to lukewarm before beating.
Beat until creamy and shiny appearance has disappeared.
Spread on cake.

title: crown cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese until fluffy. Beat in powdered sugar. Add chopped nuts. SPREAD ON CAKE WHILE CAKE IS HOT!

title: ma's dessert(also known as clair cake)
directions: Mix everything together except for graham crackers and chocolate icing.
In a 9 x 13 pan:

layer bottom of pan with graham crackers, cover with half of pudding mixture, second layer of graham crackers, cover with remaining mixture, last layer of graham crackers and put chocolate icing on top of last layer.
Put in refrigerator.
Let stand overnight.
Can enjoy in the morning.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Spread 1 heaping tablespoon on each tortilla.
Roll tightly.
Place seam side down on cookie sheet.
Chill 2 hours. Slice each tortilla roll into four pieces.
Yields 4 dozen roll-ups.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Have all ingredients room temperature.
